1
00:00:51,690 --> 00:00:55,070
1957年10月 苏联将
In October 1957, the Soviet Union launched

2
00:00:55,070 --> 00:00:59,450
世界上第一颗人造卫星 斯普特尼克1号送入轨道
the world's first artificial satellite, Sputnik 1, into orbit.

3
00:00:59,450 --> 00:01:04,580
这一成就加剧了美苏两国之间的太空竞赛
Their achievement fueled a space race between the United States and the Soviets.

4
00:01:04,580 --> 00:01:07,410
之后发生了什么 人们说法不一
There has been some debate about what followed

5
00:01:07,420 --> 00:01:12,380
但我亲身经历过 所以接下来讲的都是真事 基本上是吧
but I was there, and this is the real story. Mostly.

6
00:01:12,380 --> 00:01:13,750
直到两天前
Until two days ago,

7
00:01:13,760 --> 00:01:16,090
地球上的人才头一次听到这个声音
that sound had never been heard on this earth.

8
00:01:16,090 --> 00:01:19,840
(苏联人将卫星送进太空)

9
00:01:19,840 --> 00:01:22,810
(《生活》 太空竞赛)

10
00:01:24,220 --> 00:01:26,310
(美国卫星一败涂地)

11
00:01:26,310 --> 00:01:28,270
美国尝试发射自己的卫星 结果惨不忍睹

12
00:01:29,270 --> 00:01:31,560
(美国火箭计划启动失败)

13
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:34,980
苏联成功地将一个人送入太空
The Soviet Union has sent a man into space

14
00:01:32,480 --> 00:01:34,980
(第一个进入太空的人)

15
00:01:34,980 --> 00:01:36,110
并把他活着带回地球
and brought him back alive.

16
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:38,070
苏联人在全世界范围内
The Soviets made the most of the flight

17
00:01:38,070 --> 00:01:41,620
大肆宣传这次航天行动 其国内自然也是举国欢庆
in their worldwide propaganda. Naturally, there was jubilation in Russia.

18
00:01:42,870 --> 00:01:46,580
在认识到苏联人取得领先后
Recognizing the head start obtained by the Soviets,

19
00:01:46,580 --> 00:01:51,000
我认为我国应致力于实现一个目标
I believe that this nation should commit itself to achieving the goal,

20
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,130
即在这个十年内
before this decade is out,

21
00:01:53,130 --> 00:01:57,010
把一个人送上月球并让他安全返回地球
of landing a man on the moon and returning him safely to the earth.

22
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,010
(美国宇航员环绕地球飞行)

23
00:02:12,020 --> 00:02:15,070
我们选择在这个十年登月
We choose to go to the moon in this decade

24
00:02:15,070 --> 00:02:18,280
并完成其他壮举 不是因为这个目标轻而易举
and do the other things, not because they are easy,

25
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,990
而是因为它困难重重
but because they are hard.

26
00:02:19,990 --> 00:02:23,530
因为这个挑战是我们愿意接受
Because that challenge is one that we are willing to accept,

27
00:02:23,530 --> 00:02:26,330
不愿推迟 并准备大获全胜的
one we are unwilling to postpone, and one we intend to win.

28
00:02:26,330 --> 00:02:28,500
指挥飞行员 一 二 三 四 五
Command Pilot. One, two, three, four, five.

29
00:02:28,500 --> 00:02:30,160
五 四 三 二 一
Five, four, three, two, one.

30
00:02:31,830 --> 00:02:32,670
着火了
Flame!

31
00:02:32,670 --> 00:02:34,880
驾驶舱里失火了
We've got a fire in the cockpit.

32
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:37,960
快出去 我们要烧死了
Let's get out! We're burning up!

33
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:42,130
宇航员维吉尔·格里森 爱德华·怀特 和罗杰·查菲不幸遇难
Astronauts Virgil Grissom, Edward White and Roger Chaffee have been killed.

34
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:44,220
媒体官员称 因为此次悲剧事件
Press officials say because of the tragedy,

35
00:02:44,220 --> 00:02:47,640
阿波罗1号飞行任务将被无限期推迟
the Apollo 1 flight has now been postponed indefinitely.

36
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,430
我... 登月之旅很有吸引力
I... It's, uh... It's a groovy trip,

37
00:02:49,430 --> 00:02:53,100
但在美国 还有很多更重要的事情要先做
but there are a lot more important things to do first in the United States.

38
00:02:53,100 --> 00:02:55,940
也许把这些事情都搞定了 我们才能登月
Maybe when all that's taken care of we can afford to go to the moon.

39
00:02:55,940 --> 00:02:59,570
我们发现自己物质丰富 士气低下
We find ourselves rich in goods but ragged in spirit.

40
00:02:59,570 --> 00:03:02,320
雄心勃勃地想要登月
Reaching with magnificent precision for the moon

41
00:03:02,320 --> 00:03:04,570
却在地球上陷入一片混乱
but falling into raucous discord on earth.

42
00:03:04,570 --> 00:03:06,700
我们想要和平 却被卷入战争
We are caught at war wanting peace.

43
00:03:06,700 --> 00:03:09,200
我们想要团结 却四分五裂
We're torn by division wanting unity.

44
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,120
这个巨大的土星号火箭
This giant Saturn rocket

45
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:14,960
以及这里的其他设备 最初都是这场竞赛的一部分
and the rest of the equipment here began as part of a race

46
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:14,960
(国家航空航天局预算削减)

47
00:03:14,960 --> 00:03:17,210
为的是战胜苏联人 它们肩负着
to beat the Russians with the national goal

48
00:03:17,210 --> 00:03:19,840
我国在这个十年内把人类送上月球的目标
of putting a man on the moon in this decade.

49
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:23,220
但登月之旅的花费将超出所有人的预期
But their trip will cost more than anyone thought it would.

50
00:03:23,220 --> 00:03:28,260
而在1960年代成功登月的几率愈加渺茫
And their chances of landing on the moon in the 1960s are increasingly slim.

51
00:03:33,060 --> 00:03:35,060
(国家航空航天局)

52
00:03:49,490 --> 00:03:51,870
斯图 你当主管第一周 听着情况不妙啊
First week as manager, Stu. Doesn't sound like it's going great.

53
00:03:51,870 --> 00:03:54,920
要么是计量表不准 要么是某个储存罐漏了
So either our meters are off or there's a breach in one of the tanks.

54
00:03:54,920 --> 00:03:57,880
但这种情况没有规程 我们也找不到泄漏源头
But there's no protocol for this. And we can't source the leak

55
00:03:57,880 --> 00:03:59,420
因为是液态... 液态氢
because it's liquid hyd... Liquid hydrogen.

56
00:03:59,420 --> 00:04:01,840
它是无色无味的 所有人都出去 快
It's colorless and odorless. Everybody out! Let's go!

57
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:03,420
里德 凯尔 放下铅笔
Reed, Kyle, pencils down.

58
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:05,720
可能已经在燃烧了 我们却不知情 找门出去
It could be burning, and we wouldn't know it. Find a door.

59
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:08,760
快 跑起来 别慢吞吞的
Come on! Run, run! No walking.

60
00:04:16,230 --> 00:04:17,520
他在干什么? 打扫吗?
What's he doing? Is he cleaning?

61
00:04:17,520 --> 00:04:20,480
不... 这是... 一种检查泄漏的老办法
No, no. It's an... It's an old-school leak detection process.

62
00:04:20,480 --> 00:04:21,570
他用的是把扫帚
It's a broom.

63
00:04:22,240 --> 00:04:25,610
斯图 你很聪明的 再想想 干麦秆加上液态氢等于...
Stu, you're better than this. Come on. Straw plus liquid hydrogen equals...

64
00:04:33,660 --> 00:04:35,580
好 没事了 别担心了 来吧
All right, we're good! Don't worry about it. Come on.

65
00:04:35,580 --> 00:04:37,040
我们还有工作呢 快点
We got work to do. Let's go.

66
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:49,640
新的规程是用扫帚检查泄漏
Uh, the new protocol is the broom method.

67
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:53,640
我们需要一把新扫帚
We need a new broom.

68
00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:02,980
我刚才真以为他死了
I for sure thought he was dead.

69
00:05:02,980 --> 00:05:04,440
拜托
Come on.

70
00:05:06,900 --> 00:05:08,160
这还是
It's still broke

71
00:05:08,160 --> 00:05:11,410
你上次发脾气时弄坏的 是的 我能看出来
from the last time you were in a mood. Yeah, I can see that.

72
00:05:11,410 --> 00:05:14,410
波音又来电话了 亨利 打给议会 别找我
Boeing called again. Call Congress, Henry, not me.

73
00:05:15,580 --> 00:05:16,790
我没有他们的电话号码
I don't have their number.

74
00:05:16,790 --> 00:05:20,290
每天... 这里都有东西坏掉
Every day, every day, something is breaking around here.

75
00:05:20,290 --> 00:05:24,420
或者爆炸 我们资金不足 人手不足
Or blowing up. We're underfunded, under... understaffed.

76
00:05:24,420 --> 00:05:26,760
但没错 他们还期望我们吊打苏联人
But yeah, we're still expected to beat the pants off the Russians.

77
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:29,260
你能告诉我到底该怎么做到吗?
You mind telling me how the hell we're supposed to do that?

78
00:05:29,260 --> 00:05:31,720
就从善待自动售货机开始吧
Could start by being a little nicer to the vending machines.

79
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,430
快看 在那里
Ooh! There it is!

80
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:35,930
什么? 有一只猫
What? There's a cat.

81
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:38,810
那又怎么了? 是一只黑猫 亨利 代表霉运
So what? It's a black cat, Henry. It's bad luck.

82
00:05:40,190 --> 00:05:42,360
好吧 不见了
Okay, it's gone.

83
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:46,490
好 谢天谢地 好吧 我们走
All right. Thank God. Okay. Let's go.

84
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,740
叫保安 不要
Call security. I won't.

85
00:05:48,740 --> 00:05:50,070
我不叫 这... 你要去叫
I will not. It... Yes, you will.

86
00:05:50,070 --> 00:05:53,740
我们这里最不该出现的就是一只黑猫
The last thing that we need around here is a black cat.

87
00:05:53,740 --> 00:05:55,700
保安又不管这种事
They don't deal with things like this.

88
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,410
他们管的 现在管了
Yes, they do. They do now.

89
00:05:57,410 --> 00:06:00,960
你反应过头了 不 是你反应迟钝
Y-You're overreacting. No, you're not overreacting enough.

90
00:06:01,460 --> 00:06:03,800
立刻叫保安 马上去
Call 'em right now. Right now.

91
00:06:17,890 --> 00:06:19,140
我看起来如何?
How do I look?

92
00:06:19,140 --> 00:06:21,140
容光焕发 加油
You're glowing. Good luck.

93
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:23,610
下午好 小伙子们
Good afternoon, boys.

94
00:06:23,610 --> 00:06:26,480
走错房间了 亲爱的 我们不需要笔录
Wrong room, sweetheart. We don't need dictation.

95
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:28,440
我叫凯莉·琼斯 今天的会议由我主持
I'm Kelly Jones. I'll be running the meeting today.

96
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:30,400
你们一定是菲尔·亨利 尼尔·布朗和...
You must be Phil Hunley, Neil Brown and...

97
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:34,320
扎克·坦纳 不介意我坐下吧?
Ooh. [chuckles] Zack Tanner. You don't mind if I sit down, do you?

98
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:37,450
恕我直言 琼斯太太 我们是一家进步的公司
Uh, all due respect, Mrs. Jones, we're a progressive company.

99
00:06:37,450 --> 00:06:40,160
我们的速记员团队有16名女性
We employ 16 women in our steno pool.

100
