00:09:45,640 --> 00:09:50,150
显然他们对我给他们拍广告的方式有意见
Apparently, they have issues with the way that I am shooting their commercial.

152
00:09:50,150 --> 00:09:52,360
他们真是这么说的 “他们的” 那可是我的广告
They actually said that. "Their." It's my commercial.

153
00:09:52,360 --> 00:09:55,030
不就是做吸尘器的嘛 我可是搞艺术的
They make vacuums. I make art.

154
00:09:55,030 --> 00:09:56,900
抱歉 我们约了见面吗? 没有...
Sorry, did we have a meeting set? No. No.

155
00:09:56,900 --> 00:09:58,820
不好意思 我没意识到还得约时间
I'm sorry. I didn't realize I had to set a time

156
00:09:58,820 --> 00:10:00,320
才能跟最亲爱的朋友说话
to speak to one of my dearest friends.

157
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:02,740
上次我们说话时你把我炒了 我现在不为你工作了
The last time we spoke, you fired me. And I don't work for you.

158
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:05,040
我跟你讲 凯莉 我不是来听你训斥的
You know what, Kelly, I didn't come in here to be berated.

159
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:06,120
我是来找你支持我的
I came in to be agreed with!

160
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:09,830
你十分钟后要向雀巢推销 这很重要
You have that Nestle pitch in ten. Very important.

161
00:10:09,830 --> 00:10:11,710
骗人的 再见
That is a lie. Goodbye.

162
00:10:11,710 --> 00:10:15,460
兰斯 给你拿到这份导演工作 堪称圣诞奇迹
Lance, getting you this directing gig was a Christmas miracle.

163
00:10:15,460 --> 00:10:18,050
你搞砸了那个果冻广告拍摄后 我用了三周时间
It took me three weeks to convince them that you were stable

164
00:10:18,050 --> 00:10:21,840
才说服他们你并非喜怒无常 果冻广告那事不怪我
after your Jell-O shoot from hell. Jell-O was not my fault.

165
00:10:21,840 --> 00:10:24,470
那个演员... 才五岁 你把他弄哭了
Ugh. That actor wa... Was five. You made him cry.

166
00:10:24,470 --> 00:10:26,930
我是帮了那孩子一把 好莱坞可不好混
Well, I did that child a favor. Hollywood is no cakewalk.

167
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:30,520
那亨氏食品广告呢? 你超了预算四万块 只是个番茄酱广告而已
What about the Heinz commercial? You went 40,000 over budget. It was about ketchup.

168
00:10:31,060 --> 00:10:34,360
才不是 重点是番茄酱带来的希望
It was not about ketchup. It was about the promise of ketchup.

169
00:10:34,360 --> 00:10:36,730
没有人看到我在为他们的产品做什么
No one sees what I'm doing for their products.

170
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:37,990
我在提升产品价值
I am elevating them.

171
00:10:37,990 --> 00:10:40,360
我现在应该在拍电影了
I should be in film by now.

172
00:10:40,360 --> 00:10:43,030
我拒绝了执导《娃娃谷》的机会
I passed on directing Valley of the Dolls.

173
00:10:43,030 --> 00:10:46,160
那事怪我 但我还是该拍电影 好了 我们是怎么称呼你的?
That is on me, but still. Now, what do we call you, right?

174
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:48,950
广告界的库布里克 好了 天啊 斯坦利是半吊子
The Kubrick of commercials. All right. Oh, my God. Stanley is a hack.

175
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,000
拍出一部好电影就突然成了天才
He does one good movie, and suddenly he's a genius.

176
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:54,540
你是传奇 好吗? 创意天才
You are a legend, right? Creative genius.

177
00:10:54,540 --> 00:10:57,130
但你也脾气暴躁 反覆无常 永远不能按预算拍摄
You're also hotheaded, mercurial and can't stick to a budget for shit.

178
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:59,010
谢谢 这不是夸你
Oh, thank you. That wasn't a compliment.

179
00:10:59,010 --> 00:11:02,590
这时就该当耳旁风 你若不跟胡佛合作 以后就没人请你了
It is when you stop listening. If you quit Hoover, you'll be unhirable.

180
00:11:05,100 --> 00:11:06,260
好吧
Okay.

181
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,850
兰斯 不如你回片场吧
Lance, why don't you march your ass back to set,

182
00:11:08,850 --> 00:11:10,600
不管发什么脾气 都道个歉 好吗?
and you apologize for whatever fit you threw, okay?

183
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:13,440
给你男朋友买个棒棒的圣诞礼物 谢谢他容忍你
Buy your boyfriend something nice for Christmas for putting up with you.

184
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:14,810
也给我买个礼物 好吗?
Get something for me too, okay?

185
00:11:14,810 --> 00:11:17,360
圣诞快乐 兰斯 圣诞快乐
Merry Christmas, Lance. Merry Christmas.

186
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:19,690
请你给我找份像样的工作 好吗?
Can you get me a decent job, please?

187
00:11:24,780 --> 00:11:27,200
阿波罗8号于今早成功发射
Apollo 8 launched successfully this morning.

188
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:32,040
这场胜利是国家航空航天局的及时雨 在越南方面 今天有更多人牺牲
A much needed win for NASA. In Vietnam, more men were lost today.

189
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:32,040
(阿波罗8号发射录影)

190
00:11:32,040 --> 00:11:33,870
二千五百万公里...
And 15 million miles...

191
00:11:33,880 --> 00:11:36,460
麻烦再来一杯 另外把晚餐菜单拿给我
I'll have another round, please, and a look at the dinner menu.

192
00:11:36,460 --> 00:11:37,750
好的 女士 谢谢
Yes, ma'am. Thanks.

193
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:44,550
今晚有两个特色菜 鸡肉馅饼和洛克菲勒牡蛎
Two specials tonight. Chicken potpie and Oysters Rockefeller.

194
00:11:46,100 --> 00:11:48,890
我们吃鸡好了 她对牡蛎过敏
We'll do the chicken. She's allergic to oysters.

195
00:11:49,430 --> 00:11:53,390
给我来一杯麦卡伦 一个柠檬和一个砧板
And I'll take a shot of Macallan, a lemon and a cutting board.

196
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:56,520
好的 先生 不好意思 我认识你吗?
Yes, sir. Oh, I'm sorry. Do I know you?

197
00:11:57,070 --> 00:12:01,650
跑车上装安全带 这个点子很不错
Seat belts in a sports car. I mean, that's a great angle.

198
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:04,450
很不幸 他们即将停止跟你合作
Unfortunately, they're about to kill the account.

199
00:12:05,410 --> 00:12:06,620
为什么?
Why would they do that?

200
00:12:06,620 --> 00:12:11,330
因为有人告诉他们 你肚子里其实没孩子
Because someone told them that you don't really have a bun in the oven.

201
00:12:15,710 --> 00:12:18,500
菲尔 让我解释一下
Phil. [chuckles] Let me explain.

202
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:20,550
我以后再也不会相信女人了
That's the last time I trust a woman.

203
00:12:20,550 --> 00:12:23,260
我还给你送了一份婴儿礼物
I actually sent you a baby gift.

204
00:12:23,260 --> 00:12:25,180
你那么做非常贴心 请让我...
Which was so sweet, by the way. Let me just...

205
00:12:25,180 --> 00:12:27,220
尼尔 让我解释一下 如果你们...
Neil, let-let me explain. If you...

206
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:29,300
怎么回事? 你为谁工作? 奥美广告?
What is this? Who do you work for, Ogilvy?

207
00:12:29,310 --> 00:12:31,180
你业绩拼不过我 就害我被解雇?
Huh? You can't outsell me, so you got me fired?

208
00:12:31,180 --> 00:12:34,440
恰恰相反 我想聘请你
Just the opposite. I wanna hire you.

209
00:12:35,810 --> 00:12:39,060
我叫莫·伯克斯 在总统办公室工作
Name's Moe Berkus. I work for the president's office.

210
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:40,190
哪家公司的?
Of what company?

211
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,950
美国总统
The president.

212
00:12:48,950 --> 00:12:54,290
我们需要一位营销专家 听说你是最厉害的
We need a, uh, marketing specialist, and word has it you are the very best.

213
00:12:55,370 --> 00:13:00,670
于是我做了些调研 发现...
So I did a little digging, and, uh...

214
00:13:00,670 --> 00:13:03,460
你的经历很有趣 凯莉
You have quite a colorful past, Kelly.

215
00:13:03,460 --> 00:13:06,340
还是说我该叫你简? 来自芝加哥的空姐
Or should I call you Jane? Stewardess from Chicago.

216
00:13:06,340 --> 00:13:11,260
也许你更喜欢被称为艾米 俄亥俄州的护士
Or perhaps you would prefer Amy, the nurse from Ohio.

217
00:13:11,930 --> 00:13:14,230
有这么漂亮的脸蛋 谁还会看推荐信?
Face like that, who's gonna check references?

218
00:13:15,350 --> 00:13:18,100
你找的那一页不在这里
Page you're looking for isn't in there.

219
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:24,740
我不知道你在说什么
I don't know what you're talking about.

220
00:13:24,740 --> 00:13:27,240
你当然不知道 我懂
Oh, sure you don't. And I get it.

221
00:13:27,240 --> 00:13:32,200
嘿 我也有几十个身份证 我的真名也不叫莫
Hey, I have dozens of IDs, and my real name's not Moe.

222
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:35,160
有那么多名字可以选 你却挑了“莫”?
With all the names you could've picked, you landed on Moe?

223
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,710
你天赋出众
You have singular talent.

224
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:41,460
可以用来成就更伟大的事业 何必浪费在卖车上呢?
Why waste it selling cars when you can think bigger?

225
00:13:43,300 --> 00:13:46,300
莫 有什么公司比福特更伟大?
Well, Moe, what's bigger than Ford?

226
00:13:50,550 --> 00:13:52,850
你去过佛罗里达州吗?
You ever been to Florida?

227
00:13:56,730 --> 00:13:59,980
他们想让你推销月球? 月球 阿波罗任务
They want you to sell the moon? The moon. The Apollo mission.

228
00:13:59,980 --> 00:14:01,560
一整套
The whole thing.

229
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:03,900
这个叫莫的家伙为国家航空航天局做事?
And this Moe guy works for NASA?

230
00:14:04,570 --> 00:14:08,450
对 不 算是吧 他是政府的人
Yeah. I mean, y... Well, no. Um, kind of. He-He-He works for the government.

231
00:14:08,450 --> 00:14:09,530
哪个部门?
Oh, which part?

232
00:14:12,280 --> 00:14:13,280
凯莉
Kelly?

233
00:14:15,410 --> 00:14:19,290
这个人... 我们在为理查德·尼克松工作?
Does this guy... Are we working for Richard Nixon?

234
00:14:19,290 --> 00:14:21,790
因为我才不会为理查德·尼克松工作 凯莉
Because, Kelly, I will not work for Richard Nixon.

235
00:14:21,790 --> 00:14:24,840
我是持证女权主义者 我真的有证
I'm a card-carrying feminist. I actually have a card.

236
00:14:24,840 --> 00:14:26,710
我甚至不相信他要当总统了
I can't even believe he's going to be president.

237
00:14:26,710 --> 00:14:29,300
我本来不知道自己对美国有这么多意见
I had no idea I disagreed with this much of the country.

238
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:33,930
我们为国家航空航天局工作 推销月球 没人对月球有意见
We are working for NASA to sell the moon. Nobody disagrees about the moon.

239
00:14:33,930 --> 00:14:35,720
不是 你我都清楚
No. You and I both know

240
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:38,890
我们身边每天都有可怕的事发生
that everywhere around us every day something terrible is happening.

241
00:14:38,890 --> 00:14:40,060
无所不在
Everywhere.

242
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:41,560
除了太空
Except in space.

243
00:14:41,560 --> 00:14:44,610
真讨厌 你说动我了 他们绝对需要我们的帮助
I hate that this is working on me. They definitely need our help.

244
00:14:44,610 --> 00:14:48,860
你知道国家航空航天局的头29次任务 只有48%的成功率吗?
Did you know of NASA's first 29 missions, only 48% have been successful?

245
00:14:49,490 --> 00:14:50,860
这不可能 太离谱了
That can't be. That's crazy.

246
00:14:50,860 --> 00:14:56,950
你知道可可海滩市的 男女比例是五比一吗? 天啊
Did you know the ratio of men to women in Cocoa Beach is 5-to-1? [chuckles] Wow.

247
00:14:57,870 --> 00:15:00,580
只要你给我们找的住处不在兄弟会街就行
As long as you got us a quiet place that's not on Frat Row.

248
00:15:01,710 --> 00:15:03,460
指南手册说那里很古雅
The... The guidebook said it's quaint.

249
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:08,340
(卫星汽车旅馆 客满)

250
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,720
你被炒鱿鱼了
You're fired.

251
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:19,770
这些都是什么人啊?
Who are all these people?

252
00:15:19,770 --> 00:15:23,350
今天星期三 他们好像在另一个星球上
It is a Wednesday. It's like they're on a different planet.

253
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:24,690
这里叫佛罗里达
They call it Florida.

254
00:15:25,270 --> 00:15:27,610
请告诉我你订了一个远离游泳池的房间
Please tell me you booked a room away from the pool.

255
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:39,910
16 21 天气
sixteen and 21... Weather!

256
00:15:39,910 --> 00:15:41,910
明天晴间多云
Clear to partly cloudy tomorrow.

257
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:44,670
下午及傍晚 局部地区有雷阵雨
A few isolated thundershowers during the afternoon and early evening.

258
00:15:41,910 --> 00:15:44,670
(佛罗里达州 可可海滩)

259
00:15:44,670 --> 00:15:46,040
今晚最低气温18至24摄氏度
A low tonight, 65 to 75.

260
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:48,340
目前月球火箭发射场周边城市 气温25摄氏度
Currently 77 in the Moonport cities.

261
00:15:48,340 --> 00:15:51,130
这里是KO2020电台 为你带来的体育新闻和天气预报
That's KO twenty-twenty news, sports and weather.

262
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:52,840
WKKO
WKKO...

263
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:55,140
(沃尔菲餐厅)

264
00:16:02,230 --> 00:16:04,690
嗨 乔 晚上好 科尔 来点什么?
Hey, Joe. Evening, Cole. What'll it be?

265
00:16:05,190 --> 00:16:06,190
黑咖啡
Coffee. Black.

266
00:16:06,190 --> 00:16:09,030
再来点最快能打包带走的吃的 朋友
And whatever takes the least amount of time to put in a bag, my friend.

267
00:16:42,730 --> 00:16:45,520
小姐 你很惹火
Uh, miss, you're on fire.

268
00:16:45,520 --> 00:16:46,730
真有创意
Very original.

269
00:16:46,730 --> 00:16:48,900
得了 我不想跟你玩干柴烈火
No, I do not wanna stop, drop and roll with you.

270
00:16:48,900 --> 00:16:50,270
不是 你的书着火了
No, your book is on fire.

271
00:16:50,860 --> 00:16:51,860
天啊
God.

272
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:58,070
好 没事的... 我的天
Okay. All right. All right. All right. Oh, my God.

273
00:16:58,070 --> 00:17:00,830
抱歉 谢谢你 我只是... 教你个经验法则
I'm sorry. Thank you. I just... Just as a rule of thumb,

274
00:17:00,830 --> 00:17:03,040
酒精和火焰 绝配
alcohol and flames, they... they like each other.

275
00:17:03,040 --> 00:17:06,000
是 天啊 我把你的外套烧坏了
Yeah. Oh, gosh. I-I-I ruined your jacket.

276
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,330
没事 这衣服跟我出生入死
No, this thing's seen worse.

277
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:09,420
经历过千锤百炼 请你喝一杯补偿你吧
Been through worse. Let me buy a drink for your troubles.

278
00:17:09,420 --> 00:17:10,590
不必了 必须的
That's not necessary. I insist.

279
00:17:10,590 --> 00:17:12,090
我不喝酒 没关系
I don't drink. It's okay.

280
00:17:12,090 --> 00:17:15,130
真的? 不喝酒的宇航员 真有意思
Oh, really? An astronaut who doesn't drink. That's very intriguing.

281
00:17:16,180 --> 00:17:17,930
你怎么会认为我是宇航员?
What makes you think I'm an astronaut?

282
00:17:18,430 --> 00:17:21,220
因为你戴着阿波罗胸针 只有宇航员才有
Because you have an Apollo pin, and only astronauts get those.

283
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:23,020
看来你对国家航空航天局略知一二
So you know a thing or two about NASA.

284
00:17:23,020 --> 00:17:27,390
是 我是新晋粉丝 我叫凯莉·琼斯
Yeah, well, I'm a recent fan. I'm Kelly Jones.

285
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:31,190
我不是宇航员 我只是在肯尼迪中心工作 科尔·戴维斯
I'm no astronaut. I just work at Kennedy. Cole Davis.

286
00:17:32,230 --> 00:17:33,610
你做什么工作?
Well, what do you do there?

287
00:17:34,110 --> 00:17:39,320
听着 我最不愿意在闲聊中谈工作
Uh... Look, the last thing I want to do is make small talk about my job. Oh.

288
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:40,570
抱歉 我不是那个意思
Sorry. That didn't sound...

289
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:43,910
我不是想... 没关系 对 你只是实话实说
I didn't mean it for it to... Uh. That's okay. No. You were being honest.

290
00:17:43,910 --> 00:17:45,540
你点的餐好了 科尔
Order up, Cole. Um...

291
00:18:12,150 --> 00:18:14,230
我没实话实说 如果我真的坦诚
I wasn't being honest. If I was being honest,

292
00:18:14,230 --> 00:18:16,440
我会跟你说 你是我记忆中
I'd have told you you're the most beautiful woman

293
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:18,110
所见过最美的女人
that I've seen in longer than I can remember,

294
00:18:18,110 --> 00:18:19,700
而我的记忆力很好
and I have a very good memory.

295
00:18:19,700 --> 00:18:22,450
我只想请你喝一杯 然后跟你聊上几小时
All I really want to do is just buy you a drink and talk to you for hours,

296
00:18:22,450 --> 00:18:25,540
但我做不到 所以我要努力忘记你在这里
but I can't so I'm trying really hard to just forget that you're here.

297
00:18:25,540 --> 00:18:27,040
很高兴认识你 凯莉
It was nice to meet you, Kelly.

298
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:29,670
非常抱歉
I really am sorry.

299
00:19:24,760 --> 00:19:26,970
欢迎来到火箭路
Welcome to Rockets Road,

300
00:19:26,970 --> 00:19:30,020
又称鳄鱼巷
also known as Alligator Alley.

301
00:19:30,690 --> 00:19:34,440
如果想保住胳膊和腿
You'll wanna keep your arms and legs inside the cart

302
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:37,940
请不要把手脚伸出车外
if you wanna keep your arms and legs.

303
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:42,150
没有啦 开个小玩笑 它们主要在水中发动攻击
No, that's just a little joke. They mostly attack in the water.

304
00:19:37,940 --> 00:19:42,150
(国家航空航天局 约翰F 肯尼迪航天中心)

305
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:46,580
好了 今天的参观大约要两个半到三小时
Now, today's tour will take approximately two and a half to three hours.

306
00:19:46,580 --> 00:19:48,950
请舒适地坐好
So let's get comfy-cozy.

307
00:19:49,700 --> 00:19:52,960
右手边是我们的测试楼
Now on the right is our testing facility.

308
00:19:52,960 --> 00:19:54,080
是世界顶尖水平的
State-of-the-art.

309
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:56,750
失火了 它经常失火
It's on fire. It is often on fire.

310
00:19:57,460 --> 00:20:01,420
前方是载具组装大楼
Up ahead, we have the vehicle assembly building.

311
00:20:01,420 --> 00:20:04,220
是组装火箭的地方
That's where they assemble the rockets.

312
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:10,890
是全世界最高的单层建筑
That is the tallest single-story building in the world.

313
00:20:10,890 --> 00:20:14,940
里面能放下四座自由女神像
You can fit four Statue of Liberties inside that building.

314
00:20:14,940 --> 00:20:17,060
天啊 《生活》杂志 完全没拍出它有多壮观
Wow. Life Magazine really doesn't do it justice.

315
00:20:17,070 --> 00:20:18,730
这也太... 我想进去看看
This is so gre... I'd love to go inside.

316
00:20:18,730 --> 00:20:21,740
这里严禁入内 抱歉 走 我们靠近点看看
It's highly restricted. I'm sorry. Come on, let's get a closer look.

317
00:20:21,740 --> 00:20:23,990
不行... 这里不得进入
Oh, no, no. No. There's no entry here.

318
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:26,450
你需要一个特殊的胸卡才能进
You need a special access badge to enter.

319
00:20:26,450 --> 00:20:28,200
比如这个? 对
Oh, like... like this one?

320
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:32,000
那... 不行... 那是我的胸卡
Yeah. That's, uh... Oh, no, no, no, that's... that's my badge.

321
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,750
嘿 看看这地方 太大了
Uh, hey... Oh. Look at this place. It's enormous!

322
00:20:34,750 --> 00:20:36,960
似乎大得多... 她们拿走了我的胸卡
It seems like it's much bigger... They took my badge!

323
00:20:36,960 --> 00:20:38,380
看看这个建筑
I mean, look at this building.

324
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:40,880
喂 那是我的胸卡 你好 先生 嗨
Hello? That's-That's my badge. Hello, sir. Hi.

325
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:43,340
我是国家航空航天局 公共事务部的凯莉·琼斯
Kelly Jones from NASA Public Affairs.

326
00:20:43,340 --> 00:20:45,720
这是我们俩的万能通行证 谢谢
Here's our all-access pass for both of us. Thank you.

327
00:20:45,720 --> 00:20:47,550
谢谢 等等... 我的胸卡
Thank you. Wait, wait. My card.

328
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:54,020
这个我能推销出去
Now, this I can sell.

329
00:21:00,820 --> 00:21:01,900
哟呼
Yoo-hoo!

330
00:21:02,940 --> 00:21:05,070
你们好 小伙子们...
Hello. Boys, boys!

331
00:21:05,070 --> 00:21:06,780
嗨 凯莉·琼斯
Hi. Kelly Jones.

332
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:09,160
我是国家航空航天局 新成立的公共事务部的
I'm from the new NASA Public Affairs team.

333
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,030
我能问你们俩几个问题吗?
Can I ask you two a few questions?

334
00:21:11,040 --> 00:21:12,790
姓名 年龄 你们在这里的工作?
Name, age, and what's your job here?

335
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:19,040
我是斯图·布莱斯 总工程师之一 24岁
Uh, I'm Stu Bryce. One of the, uh, head engineers, and I'm 24.

336
00:21:19,040 --> 00:21:20,630
我们就说35岁 好
We'll say 35. Yeah.

337
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:21,630
你呢?
And you?

338
00:21:21,630 --> 00:21:24,510
我叫唐·哈珀 我是他的手下 23岁
I'm Don Harper. I-I work for him, and I'm 23.

339
00:21:25,220 --> 00:21:26,220
你们真年轻
You guys are babies.

340
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:29,010
国家航空航天局的平均年龄是26岁
The average age at NASA is 26.

341
00:21:29,010 --> 00:21:31,510
但我们知道这里也有些老年人
But w-we do know some old people that work here as well.

342
00:21:31,510 --> 00:21:33,930
对 32 33岁的 是
Yeah, like, 32, 33. Yeah.

343
00:21:33,930 --> 00:21:36,230
听你们这么说 我很想杀了你俩
I'll try not to kill both of you for saying that.

344
00:21:36,230 --> 00:21:39,350
跟我们说说 斯图 你为什么加入这伟大的美国任务?
So, tell us, Stu, what brings you to join this great American mission?

345
00:21:39,360 --> 00:21:42,780
我在大学宿舍里看到了一张传单
Well, I s... saw a, uh, flyer in my college dorm.

346
00:21:43,780 --> 00:21:45,690
“从小就热爱群星” 很好
"A childhood love of the stars." That's good.

347
00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:47,070
非常感人 非常好
That's very moving. That's very good.

348
00:21:47,070 --> 00:21:48,450
你呢? 不好意思
And you? Excuse me?

349
00:21:51,700 --> 00:21:52,870
你怎么来了?
What are you doing here?

350
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:56,160
我特意来找你的 想给你我的电话号码
Well, I... I tracked you down to give you my phone number,

351
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:57,710
因为我感觉我们很来电
'cause I felt we had a connection.

352
00:21:58,790 --> 00:22:01,000
什么? 别紧张 我开玩笑的
What? Relax. I'm joking.

353
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,550
我现在在这里工作 莫·伯克斯招我进来 改组国家航空航天局公共事务部
I work here now. Moe Berkus brought me on to revamp NASA Public Affairs.

354
00:22:04,550 --> 00:22:07,590
你就是来自曼哈顿的广告精英
So you're the killer from Manhattan.

355
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:11,180
你一定就是发射主管 这是我的同事露比·马丁
And you must be the launch director. This is my associate, Ruby Martin.

356
00:22:11,180 --> 00:22:14,060
好 我不在乎 听着 这栋楼完全禁止进入
Yeah, I don't care. Look. This building is completely off-limits.

357
00:22:14,060 --> 00:22:16,060
这里有各种可能烧伤 冻伤 烤焦
Everything in here can burn you, freeze you, fry you,

358
00:22:16,060 --> 00:22:18,060
毒死 砸死你们的东西
poison you and crush you.

359
00:22:18,060 --> 00:22:20,520
走吧 出去 你在这里工作多久了?
So let's go. Out. How long have you worked here?

360
00:22:20,520 --> 00:22:23,070
很长时间了
A substantial amount of time. Hmm.

361
00:22:23,650 --> 00:22:25,230
你在写什么? 你的原话
What are you writing? Your quote.

362
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:27,780
这不算原话 我只是随口一说
That's not a quote. It was just a thing that I said.

363
00:22:27,780 --> 00:22:30,240
我会添油加醋的 你今天有时间接受采访吗?
I'll punch it up. Do you have time today for an interview?

364
00:22:30,240 --> 00:22:32,370
我还需要跟你的上级谈谈
And also, I need to sit down with your senior officers.

365
00:22:32,370 --> 00:22:34,870
上相的优先 我可以帮忙挑
The photogenic types first. I can help with the selection process.

366
00:22:34,870 --> 00:22:36,910
听着 我这里的人都太奇怪了 不适合采访
Look, my guys are too weird for interviews,

367
00:22:36,910 --> 00:22:38,790
而且他们真的在忙生死攸关的工作
and they're actually busy doing life-and-death work.

368
00:22:38,790 --> 00:22:42,500
好吧 我不需要你的批准
Well, you know, I don't need your permission.

369
00:22:42,500 --> 00:22:45,550
美国人跟太空之间 漫长且昂贵的蜜月期已经结束
The Americans are over their long and expensive honeymoon in space,

370
00:22:45,550 --> 00:22:48,380
我是来提醒大家当初为什么爱上太空的
and I'm here to remind them why they fell in love in the first place.

371
00:22:48,380 --> 00:22:51,930
是吗? 美国人应该心存感激
Is that right? Well, Americans should be very grateful

372
00:22:51,930 --> 00:22:54,680
这些人为了这项任务在冒生命危险
that these men are putting their lives on the line for the mission.

373
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:58,480
你并不怎么了解美国人 是吧?
Well, you don't know much about American people, do you?

374
00:22:58,480 --> 00:23:02,270
你也不怎么了解 你的办公室吧? 我带你看看
You don't know very much about your office I'm about to show you, do you?

375
00:23:09,860 --> 00:23:11,030
这是储物间吗?
Is this a storage closet?

376
00:23:11,530 --> 00:23:13,700
不是 储物间有窗户
Nope. Storage closet has a window.

377
00:23:13,700 --> 00:23:16,540
好 速溶咖啡在休息室
Okay, so, instant coffee... is in the break room.

378
00:23:16,540 --> 00:23:19,120
记得先把水龙头打开 放一分钟的水 把铁锈冲掉
Just run the tap for a minute to flush out the rust.

379
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:23,420
你们有谁会用灭火器吗?
Do either of you know how to work a fire extinguisher?

380
00:23:25,210 --> 00:23:27,630
不会? 好吧 四步口诀 很简单
No? Mkay. PASS method's pretty simple.

381
00:23:27,630 --> 00:23:30,970
拔安全销 对准火焰 压下把手 喷向火焰
Just, uh, pull the pin, aim, squeeze, sweep.

382
00:23:30,970 --> 00:23:33,220
如果你们有任何其他需要
If you need anything else,

383
00:23:33,220 --> 00:23:36,390
可以回纽约去拿 祝你们愉快
uh, maybe just go back to New York and get it. Have a good day.

384
00:23:37,680 --> 00:23:41,600
至少他还算养眼 但说话很刺耳
Well, at least he's easy on the eyes. He's hard on the ears though.

385
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:44,190
欢迎仪式很烂啊 我以为你说他们想要我们帮忙呢
Not a great welcome wagon. I thought you said they wanted our help.

386
00:23:44,190 --> 00:23:47,690
不 我说他们需要我们帮忙 这一点现在已经实锤到不能再实锤
Oh, no. I said they needed our help. And I do believe that now more than ever.

387
00:23:47,690 --> 00:23:50,070
如果我们谁都不能谈或什么都不能看
How are we supposed to do that if we can't talk to anyone

388
00:23:50,070 --> 00:23:52,570
那要怎么帮忙?
or look at anything?

389
00:23:53,160 --> 00:23:55,490
是一只猫...
Aw, it's a cat. It's a cat.

390
00:23:55,490 --> 00:23:56,780
是一只猫 是一只猫
It's a cat! It's a cat.

391
00:23:56,780 --> 00:23:58,790
你知道关于黑猫的说法吗?
You know what they say about black cats?

392
00:23:58,790 --> 00:24:01,750
如果黑猫从你面前路过 可能是要去其他地方
If they cross your path, they're probably going someplace else.

393
00:24:02,540 --> 00:24:05,340
好 该把旧名片夹翻出来了
Okay, time to dig out the old Rolodex.

394
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:08,420
创意时间到
Let's get creative.

395
00:24:29,610 --> 00:24:34,490
阿波罗11号将把我们的人送上月球
Apollo 11 will land our men on the moon,

396
00:24:34,490 --> 00:24:37,240
这会让我们成为世界第一
and that makes us first.

397
00:24:37,240 --> 00:24:40,740
如果我们完成工作 将会在那里发射
If we do our jobs, we will launch right from there,

398
00:24:40,750 --> 00:24:43,000
时间是7月16日一大早
July 16, bright and early.

399
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,620
在那之前
Between now and then,

400
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:47,500
我们要完成人类历史上
we will piece together the biggest jigsaw puzzle

401
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:49,590
最大的拼图
in the history of mankind.

402
00:24:50,380 --> 00:24:52,460
六百万个零部件散落在全国各地
Six million parts spread out around the country,

403
00:24:52,470 --> 00:24:55,680
我们要对每一个零件 进行组装 测试 再测试
and we will assemble, test, and retest every single one

404
00:24:55,680 --> 00:24:58,220
直到我们确定阿波罗11号 可以万无一失地发射
until we are certain that Apollo 11 will take off

405
00:24:58,220 --> 00:25:01,180
并飞向月球 就在...
without a hitch and head to the moon in...

406
00:25:01,770 --> 00:25:02,770
亨利 你说
Henry, sing it.

407
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:05,640
在七个月后
Seven months. Huh?

408
00:25:05,650 --> 00:25:06,940
七个月后
Seven months.

409
00:25:06,940 --> 00:25:10,480
请帮我恭喜阿波罗11号的宇航员
Please help me congratulate the astronauts of Apollo 11.

410
00:25:11,070 --> 00:25:14,610
阿姆斯特朗 奥尔德林和柯林斯
Armstrong, Aldrin and Collins.

411
00:25:25,460 --> 00:25:29,330
嘿... 伙计们 你们觉得白宫怎么样?
Hey, hey! How'd you like the White House, boys? Huh?

412
00:25:27,880 --> 00:25:28,920
(月球 我们来了)

413
00:25:29,340 --> 00:25:32,510
还不错 只可惜尼尔不让我偷那里的瓷器
Yeah, it was all right, except Neil wouldn't let me steal the china.

414
00:25:34,550 --> 00:25:39,550
好 因为在八个月后 等这一切都结束
All right. Because in eight months, when this is all over,

415
00:25:40,220 --> 00:25:43,220
他们需要新历史书 来记载我们在这里取得的成就时
and they need new history books to cover what we've accomplished here,

416
00:25:43,220 --> 00:25:46,180
你们每一个人都能说
each and every single one of you will be able to say that

417
00:25:46,190 --> 00:25:51,110
“我做了有史以来最困难的事” 对吗?
"I did the hardest thing that has ever been done." Yeah?

418
00:25:51,110 --> 00:25:52,150
对
Yeah!

419
00:25:52,150 --> 00:25:54,070
行动起来 开工
Let's do it. Let's get to it!

420
00:25:59,700 --> 00:26:01,870
漂亮 说得好 谢谢
Beautiful. Perfect. Thank you.

421
00:26:01,870 --> 00:26:03,790
是 长官
Yeah. Sir,

422
00:26:03,790 --> 00:26:07,000
你说新来的女士 只要做任何你不喜欢的事就通知你
you said to tell you when the new lady did anything you wouldn't like.

423
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:09,790
我身处肯尼迪航天中心
I'm here at the Kennedy Space Center

424
00:26:09,790 --> 00:26:12,000
有幸采访到副发射主管亨利·斯莫尔斯
with Deputy Launch Director, Henry Smalls.

425
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,920
怎么回事? 那是我的名字 他盗用了我的名字和职位
What's going on? That's my name. He's got my name and my job!

426
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:18,090
这段时间对我们所有人来说都很美好 对我来说更具个人感情
It's been a great time for all of us. You know, for me, this is very personal.

427
00:26:18,090 --> 00:26:19,430
我父亲是一位空军士兵
My father was an airman...

428
00:26:19,430 --> 00:26:20,510
这是谁啊?
Who is that?

429
00:26:21,300 --> 00:26:22,890
反正不是我 他在服役时牺牲了
It's not me. he died in the line of duty

430
00:26:22,890 --> 00:26:24,850
当时我还是个孩子 我没那么帅
when I was a child... I'm not that handsome.

431
00:26:24,850 --> 00:26:26,020
这是为了你 老爸
... so this is for you, Dad.

432
00:26:26,020 --> 00:26:27,890
真是够了 听到这个我很遗憾
Oh, that's it. So sorry to hear that.

433
00:26:27,890 --> 00:26:30,560
谢谢你的分享 这一定很... 我爸还活着呢
Thanks for sharing. That must've been... My dad's still alive.

434
00:26:32,650 --> 00:26:36,690
对 要怎样才能约在晚上6点左右呢? 好
Right. What is it that we can do to sort of make 6:00 p.m.? Yeah.

435
00:26:37,570 --> 00:26:39,700
国家航空航天局公共事务部 我是凯莉·琼斯
NASA Public Affairs, this is Kelly Jones.

436
00:26:39,700 --> 00:26:42,160
凯莉 美国广播公司 想要下周的媒体录影带
Kelly, ABC wants next week's press reel.

437
00:26:42,160 --> 00:26:44,410
还想要我们手上最好的阿波罗8号照片
They also want the best photo we have from the Apollo 8.

438
00:26:44,410 --> 00:26:46,910
跟他们说 如果让我们 上晚6点时间段就给他们
Tell them they can have it if they give us their 6:00 p.m. time slot.

439
00:26:46,910 --> 00:26:49,460
明白 如果你们播放动画片段
Got it. If you air an animated segment,

440
00:26:49,460 --> 00:26:51,750
我能给你们提供独家的... 非常感谢
I can offer you an exclusive... Thank you so much.

441
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:54,540
你父亲是个英雄 你是个英雄 我们非常感激你勤恳地...
Your father was a hero. You are a hero. We so appreciate you working at...

442
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:57,420
那是全国广播公司新闻主管 是 我不管 这人是谁?
That was the head of NBC News. Yeah, I don't care. Who is that?

443
00:26:57,420 --> 00:26:59,550
谢谢 我们月球上见
Thank you. See you on the moon.

444
00:27:00,050 --> 00:27:01,590
在公众眼里 他是亨利·斯莫尔斯
To the world, that's Henry Smalls.

445
00:27:01,590 --> 00:27:02,800
他不是亨利·斯莫尔斯
That's not Henry Smalls.

446
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:04,850
对 但你跟我说你们不接受采访
No, but you told me that your guys don't do interviews,

447
00:27:04,850 --> 00:27:06,180
所以我只能另请新人
so I had to hire new guys.

448
00:27:08,600 --> 00:27:11,810
你让两位全球最顶尖的工程师装窗户
You have two of the best engineers on the planet installing a window.

449
00:27:11,810 --> 00:27:14,480
菲尔 你再挥一下锤子 我一定会疯掉
Phil, if you hammer one more time, I swear to God I'm gonna lose my mind.

450
00:27:14,480 --> 00:27:16,440
把锤子放下 摘掉该死的工具带
Put down the hammer, take your stupid belts off

451
00:27:16,440 --> 00:27:17,650
回去测试
and get back to testing.

452
00:27:19,490 --> 00:27:20,700
动起来 走了
On the move. Here we go.

453
00:27:20,700 --> 00:27:22,280
这景色绝了吧?
Can you believe that view?

454
00:27:22,280 --> 00:27:24,660
我们拿到了阿波罗8号的第一批照片 比我的好
We got the first photos from Apollo 8. It's better than mine.

455
00:27:24,660 --> 00:27:26,580
从月球拍的第一张地球照片
The first shot of the earth from the moon.

456
00:27:26,580 --> 00:27:29,000
这是不是你见过最美的东西?
Isn't that the most beautiful thing you've ever seen?

457
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,120
你怎么比我先拿到? 他们称之为“地出”
How'd you get this before me? They're calling it "Earthrise."

458
00:27:32,130 --> 00:27:34,250
这张照片会登上今晚所有新闻的头条
It's going to be at the top of every news segment tonight.

459
00:27:34,250 --> 00:27:36,000
1968年太糟糕了
I mean, '68 has been such a terrible year.

460
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:39,170
刺杀 可憎的战争 我们见证了人类最丑恶的一面
Assassinations, this heinous war, we've seen the worst of humanity.

461
00:27:39,170 --> 00:27:42,430
这时国家航空航天局公布这张照片 一个看世界的全新视角
Now NASA gives us this? A whole new way to see the world.

462
00:27:44,470 --> 00:27:46,390
我会确保所有人都看到
And I'm gonna make sure everybody sees it.

463
00:27:49,230 --> 00:27:51,270
你不能找人冒充别人啊
You can't just fake people!

464
00:27:52,230 --> 00:27:54,020
嗨 我是来参加选角的
Hey, I'm here for the casting. Oh!

465
00:27:56,230 --> 00:27:58,900
他是谁? 是你 你这个角色可抢手了
Who's he? You. You're a juicy part.

466
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:01,280
要拍这几场戏 这里是角色生平
So, here's the scenes and the character bio.

467
00:28:01,280 --> 00:28:03,780
你要扮演的就是这位 所以最好提升一点魅力
This is the man that you're playing, so you wanna up the charisma a bit.

468
00:28:03,780 --> 00:28:05,160
好 我会提升... 明白? 好
Can do. I'll up the... Okay? Okay.

469
00:28:05,160 --> 00:28:07,530
在朝鲜执行过60次任务? 是的
Sixty missions in Korea? Yeah.

470
00:28:07,540 --> 00:28:10,790
我很荣幸 我在朝鲜飞过52次任务
It's an honor. I flew 52 missions in Korea.

471
00:28:10,790 --> 00:28:11,870
我取了个整数
I rounded up.

472
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:17,090
“我在朝鲜飞过52次任务” 怎么样?
"I flew 52 missions in Korea." How was that?

473
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:19,760
什么? 我会练习一下的
What? I'll work on it.

474
00:28:23,840 --> 00:28:25,260
她现在都找好人冒充我了
She has a fake me now.

475
00:28:25,260 --> 00:28:28,100
她已经有了个假的我 她有个假的我 假的你
She got a fake me. She got a fake me and a fake you.

476
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:29,720
不能冒充你和我 一无所获
You can't fake me and you. There's nothing here.

477
00:28:29,720 --> 00:28:32,690
没有莫·伯克斯 我每个字都看过了
There's no Moe Berkus. I checked every spelling.

478
00:28:33,390 --> 00:28:35,400
有个叫莫·伯克斯的打来电话
I have a Moe Berkus on the line.

479
00:28:38,570 --> 00:28:41,230
要我来说吗? 不... 我会很享受的
Do you want me to talk? Oh, no, no. I'm gonna enjoy this.

480
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:43,900
这将是国家航空航天局史上最快速的解雇
This is gonna be the fastest firing in NASA's history.

481
00:28:43,910 --> 00:28:47,280
嗨 莫 科尔 我听说你在找我
Hey, Moe. Cole, I hear you're looking for me.

482
00:28:47,280 --> 00:28:50,700
是的 凯莉·琼斯 聘请了演员来假扮国家航空航天局工程师
I am. Kelly Jones hired actors to play NASA engineers.

483
00:28:50,700 --> 00:28:54,120
这是不可接受的 我要她今天就走人
It is unacceptable. I want her desk cleared today.

484
00:28:54,120 --> 00:28:57,290
冷静点... 好吗?
Calm, calm, calm down, okay?

485
00:28:57,840 --> 00:29:01,340
华盛顿的政要们会看电视 阿波罗现在上电视了
Washington watches TV. Apollo is now on TV.

486
00:29:01,880 --> 00:29:03,590
每个频道 每天都播
Every channel, every day.

487
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:07,260
你们想登月吗?
So, you want to get to the moon?

488
00:29:07,260 --> 00:29:09,550
我建议你们专心做好本职工作
I suggest, focus on your job.

489
00:29:09,560 --> 00:29:10,930
也让凯莉做好本职工作
Let Kelly do hers.

490
00:29:11,430 --> 00:29:14,020
如果她把你打造成舞会上的焦点
If she's made you the belle of the ball,

491
00:29:14,020 --> 00:29:18,400
你不妨穿上芭蕾舞裙来跳一段
why don't you just slip on your tutu and do some dancing?

492
00:29:25,820 --> 00:29:27,700
炒掉她了?
She fired? Mm-mmm.

493
00:29:30,280 --> 00:29:31,580
我们被炒了?
Are we fired?

494
00:29:35,040 --> 00:29:38,380
阿波罗8号载着宇航员 博尔曼 洛弗尔和安德斯
Apollo 8, carrying astronauts Borman, Lovell and Anders

495
00:29:38,380 --> 00:29:40,840
由土星5号送入了太空
was launched into space by a Saturn V.

496
00:29:42,710 --> 00:29:44,590
每一个电视网都在播放地出照片
Every single network is airing the Earthrise shot.

497
00:29:44,590 --> 00:29:46,550
会传遍世界各地
I mean, it's... it's gonna be everywhere.

498
00:29:47,720 --> 00:29:49,470
我试着画了几笔
You know, I tried a little something on it,

499
00:29:49,470 --> 00:29:52,390
但好像效果还不行 不够吸引人 我们需要一个关联
but I just don't think it's working yet. It's not enough. We need a hook,

500
00:29:52,390 --> 00:29:55,060
一个把登月和人们日常生活挂钩的方法
a way to weave the moon landing into people's everyday lives

501
00:29:55,060 --> 00:29:56,600
还得潜移默化
without them realizing it.

502
00:29:57,190 --> 00:29:59,690
嗨 你们有类似沙拉的东西吗?
Uh, hi. Do you have anything close to a salad?

503
00:30:00,230 --> 00:30:01,270
汉堡上的腌黄瓜
Pickles come on a burger.

504
00:30:01,270 --> 00:30:04,860
不过要等一等 阿波罗的新闻一出 生意变好了
It's gonna be a minute, though. Apollo news has business picking up.

505
00:30:04,860 --> 00:30:07,740
有很多游客想来亲眼见证历史
All the tourists love to come in and see little pieces of history.

506
00:30:08,360 --> 00:30:11,410
见证历史? 对 比如那支笔
Pieces of history? Yeah, like... like that pen.

507
00:30:11,410 --> 00:30:14,620
1961年 约翰·格伦每晚都来这里用餐
John Glenn ate here every night in '61.

508
00:30:13,200 --> 00:30:14,620
(沃尔菲上太空了)

509
00:30:14,620 --> 00:30:17,370
他用我们的一支笔来写飞行手册
He would work on his flight manuals, and he'd use one of our pens.

510
00:30:17,370 --> 00:30:19,790
那支笔上过水星6号
That one ended up on Mercury 6.

511
00:30:19,790 --> 00:30:23,300
这里是全世界唯一一家 名字上过太空的餐厅
You're at the only restaurant in the world whose name's been in space.

512
00:30:23,300 --> 00:30:26,420
很酷
That's cool.

513
00:30:32,510 --> 00:30:34,180
正前方
And right up ahead,

514
00:30:34,180 --> 00:30:36,930
是著名的水星火箭
it's the famous Mercury rockets.

515
00:30:36,930 --> 00:30:39,940
一定要在这里拍照 但别站太近
Be sure to get a picture here, but don't stand too close.

516
00:30:39,940 --> 00:30:41,360
火箭可能会发射
They might go off.

517
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:45,740
那个周末过后 他就恢复了
He recovered after that weekend.

518
00:30:41,360 --> 00:30:45,740
(你能准备好吗? 距离发射还有171天)

519
00:30:50,160 --> 00:30:52,490
你每次进房间 大家都会安静下来 你感到困扰吗?
Does it bother you that a room dies every time you walk into it?

520
00:30:52,490 --> 00:30:54,240
你该待在你那边的
You're supposed to stay on your side.

521
00:30:54,790 --> 00:30:56,040
我想你了
I missed you. Hmm.

522
00:30:56,040 --> 00:30:57,790
我希望你批准我们新的推广活动
I'd like you to approve our new ad campaigns.

523
00:30:57,790 --> 00:30:59,710
你不如就像上次一样先斩后奏吧
Why don't you just sidestep me like you did last time?

524
00:30:59,710 --> 00:31:02,710
我想为那些让你措手不及的采访道歉
I wanna apologize for blindsiding you with the interviews.

525
00:31:02,710 --> 00:31:04,420
我有办法解决我们的资金问题
I have a fix for our money problems.

526
00:31:04,420 --> 00:31:09,260
我不接受你的道歉 也不接受这些莫名奇妙的东西
Well, your apology is rejected, and so is whatever this is.

527
00:31:10,840 --> 00:31:12,680
欧米茄 听着 这里不是麦迪逊大道
Omega. Look, this isn't Madison Avenue.

528
00:31:12,680 --> 00:31:14,850
我们不会为这种东西买单 不 免费的
We don't pay for this stuff. No, it's cost-free.

529
00:31:14,850 --> 00:31:16,810
品牌方能得到钱都买不到的合作机会
The brands get a tie-in money can't buy,

530
00:31:16,810 --> 00:31:19,690
而国家航空航天局 可以潜移默化去影响普通人
and NASA works its way into the minds of everyday people.

531
00:31:19,690 --> 00:31:22,230
手表广告? 这就是你的绝妙点子?
A watch ad? That's-That's your big idea?

532
00:31:22,770 --> 00:31:24,730
准备好了?
Ready? Mm-hmm.

533
00:31:24,730 --> 00:31:25,820
牙膏
Toothpaste.

534
00:31:27,490 --> 00:31:31,360
果珍 “阿波罗宇航员选择的 能量早餐饮品
Tang. "The energy breakfast drink chosen for Apollo astronauts

535
00:31:31,360 --> 00:31:33,660
专供登月之旅使用” 月球优惠券?
on their trip to the moon." Moon coupons?

536
00:31:33,660 --> 00:31:36,660
但我个人最喜欢的要属这个
But, my personal favorite,

537
00:31:37,830 --> 00:31:39,750
鲜果布衣 是吧?
Fruit of the Loom. Right?

538
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:42,290
宇航员在太空服里面总得穿点什么吧?
The guys gotta wear something under those big suits, don't they?

539
00:31:42,290 --> 00:31:43,960
鲜果布衣真的太能代表航天局了
Nothing says NASA like Fruit of the Loom.

540
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:47,460
听着 我不会把飞船变成飞行广告牌
Look, I am not turning this ship into a flying billboard

541
00:31:47,460 --> 00:31:49,380
无论你多么渴望都不行
no matter how much you want it to happen.

542
00:31:49,380 --> 00:31:52,130
还有 我们没时间在发射前测试这些东西
And by the way, we don't have time to test all this before liftoff.

543
00:31:52,140 --> 00:31:54,720
我们不必真的把这些送上太空 只要说说就好
We don't have to send any of this up into space as long as we say it went.

544
00:31:54,720 --> 00:31:56,140
所以你打算撒谎?
Oh, so you're gonna lie?

545
00:31:56,140 --> 00:31:58,100
这叫推销 我们不会欺骗顾客
It's called selling. We're not lying to the customer.

546
00:31:58,100 --> 00:32:00,310
我们在改变他们的思维方式 不 这叫撒谎
We're changing the way they think. No, it's called lying.

547
00:32:00,310 --> 00:32:03,230
所有人在你眼里都只是顾客吗?
Everyone is just a customer to you, huh?

548
00:32:03,230 --> 00:32:06,770
听着 我知道你是个厉害的广告精英
Look, I know that you're a big old fancy ad shark and everything,

549
00:32:06,770 --> 00:32:09,990
但国家航空航天局 不是能用广告曲和广告词推销的
but NASA's not something that you sell with a jingle and a slogan.

550
00:32:09,990 --> 00:32:12,400
你不知道我们是谁
You do not know who we are.

551
00:32:12,410 --> 00:32:14,950
行 好吧 玛格丽特·汉密尔顿是谁?
Yeah, okay. Who's Margaret Hamilton?

552
00:32:14,950 --> 00:32:16,990
谁? 她是你的手下
Who? She works here for you.

553
00:32:16,990 --> 00:32:19,410
有四十万人和太空计划有关
There are 400,000 people that are affiliated

554
00:32:19,410 --> 00:32:21,910
琼斯女士 她是你的工程师之一
with this space program, Ms. Jones. She's one of your engineers.

555
00:32:21,910 --> 00:32:24,120
乔安·摩根是谁? 她是点火室的
Who's JoAnn Morgan? She works in the firing room.

556
00:32:24,130 --> 00:32:27,170
你问过她当初为什么接这份工作吗? 我就问过
Did you ever ask her why she took this job in the first place? I have.

557
00:32:27,170 --> 00:32:30,340
她说因为她的血液里流的都是火箭燃料
She says it's because she has rocket fuel in her blood.

558
00:32:30,340 --> 00:32:32,510
国家航空航天局不光是个标志 也代表着人民
And NASA's not just a logo, it's people.

559
00:32:32,510 --> 00:32:34,010
那些每天早上醒来
People who wake up every morning

560
00:32:34,010 --> 00:32:36,600
决心创造奇迹的人
and commit to accomplishing the impossible.

561
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:39,600
同时跟大家穿着一样的内衣
And all while wearing the same underwear as the rest of us.

562
00:32:40,890 --> 00:32:43,190
艾拉 你有任何需要吗?
Ella, can I help you with anything at all?

563
00:32:50,070 --> 00:32:51,070
谢谢
Thank you.

564
00:32:51,610 --> 00:32:55,320
我预估了一下 如果你接受关键赞助
So I ran the projections, and this is what you stand to make

565
00:32:55,320 --> 00:32:57,240
能赚到这个数
if you accept key sponsorships.

566
00:33:00,620 --> 00:33:02,500
我们不能收私人的钱
We-We can't take private money.

567
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:04,370
无所谓的 明白吗?
It doesn't matter, okay?

568
00:33:04,370 --> 00:33:06,170
我即将让航天局变得非常受欢迎
I'm about to make NASA so popular

569
00:33:06,170 --> 00:33:09,000
国会终将重新提供资金
that Congress will finally turn the taps back on around here.

570
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:12,630
我只需让阿姆斯特朗 戴上一块欧米茄手表就行?
And all I have to do is just let Armstrong put on an Omega watch?

571
00:33:12,630 --> 00:33:15,180
不 如果我们得到资金
No. If we get the money flowing,

572
00:33:15,180 --> 00:33:17,680
那你必须向我证明
then you've gotta prove to me

573
00:33:17,680 --> 00:33:20,010
可可海滩也有不错的地方可以吃晚餐
that Cocoa Beach has a decent place to get dinner.

574
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:29,070
成交 我... 好 成交 太好了 呜呼
Deal. I... Yes! Deal! Yes! Whoo!

575
00:33:29,610 --> 00:33:33,740
不 等等 我得设置底线 手纸不行
Uh, no, wait. I'm drawing the line at toilet paper though,

576
00:33:33,740 --> 00:33:36,700
因为世人不用知道我们的人用什么擦屁股
because the world does not get to know what our guys wipe their ass with.

577
00:33:36,700 --> 00:33:38,570
真臭
Well, shit.

578
00:33:42,540 --> 00:33:45,460
你返回地球后想去度假吗?
Would you like to go for a vacation when you come back to earth?

579
00:33:45,460 --> 00:33:48,130
根据目前的情况看
The situation being what it is now,

580
00:33:48,130 --> 00:33:50,550
我最可能去的地方...
the place I would most like to go, uh...

581
00:33:51,090 --> 00:33:53,050
下次把桌子撤掉 沃尔特
Lose the table next time, Walter.

582
00:33:53,050 --> 00:33:55,800
尼尔看起来 像在做通用电气的季度盈利报告
Neil looks like he's giving GE's quarterly profit report.

583
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,550
我们一直用这张桌...
That's always been our table...

584
00:33:57,550 --> 00:33:59,430
电视让他们走进人们的起居室
TV brings them in to people's living rooms.

585
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:01,010
他们应该看起来像家中的客人
They should look like they belong there.

586
00:34:01,010 --> 00:34:03,560
那意味着我们成功了
It'd mean that we succeeded.

587
00:34:04,430 --> 00:34:06,690
你还是负责人 沃尔特 别担心
You're still in charge, Walter. Don't you worry.

588
00:34:07,230 --> 00:34:08,730
不过等我帮完忙后
When I'm done helping though,

589
00:34:08,730 --> 00:34:10,860
这些人会比披头士乐队还火
those men are gonna be bigger than The Beatles.

590
00:34:10,860 --> 00:34:14,490
我可以完成99.9%的登月之旅 我很满意
I'm getting to go 99.9% of the way there, and that suits me just fine.

591
00:34:16,450 --> 00:34:17,990
(下一站 月球)

592
00:34:19,910 --> 00:34:21,530
(阿波罗11号 最危险的航行)

593
00:34:25,160 --> 00:34:30,000
家乐氏的那个副总叫什么? 应该是哈里森·德里斯科尔
What's the name of that VP at Kellogg's? I believe it's Harrison Driscoll.

594
00:34:25,160 --> 00:34:26,160
(阿波罗登月在即)

595
00:34:30,830 --> 00:34:31,750
好 哈里森
All right, Harrison.

596
00:34:31,750 --> 00:34:36,300
不要用“辟啪 笑笑 泡泡” 改用“尼尔 巴兹和迈克” 不错吧?
So instead of "Snap, Crackle, Pop," "Neil, Buzz and Mike." It's cute, right?

597
00:34:39,680 --> 00:34:42,600
科尔
Cole!

598
00:34:45,730 --> 00:34:48,050
确保那个不会生锈 亨利 能签一下这些吗?
Make sure that doesn't rust, Henry. Can you mark these?

599
00:34:52,810 --> 00:34:54,270
嘿... 你看见了吗?
Hey, hey. Did you see that?

600
00:34:54,270 --> 00:34:55,440
你没看见那只猫?
You didn't see the cat?

601
00:34:58,450 --> 00:34:59,950
果珍的瓶子再推近些
Go closer on the Tang bottle.

602
00:34:59,950 --> 00:35:02,950
字体再大些 放上培根和鸡蛋
Make the font bigger and put bacon with the eggs.

603
00:35:02,950 --> 00:35:05,370
别忘了 我们推销的是美国
Let's not forget, we're selling America, here.

604
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:10,330
“彼得潘花生酱 丝滑到飞起 此酱只应天上有”
"Peter Pan Peanut Butter. Peanut butter that's out-of-this-world smooth."

605
00:35:11,420 --> 00:35:13,710
“哈苏 以他们的视角看世界”
"Hasselblad. See the world the way they do."

606
00:35:13,710 --> 00:35:15,800
拉里 这是欧米茄的好机会
Larry, this is Omega's big chance.

607
00:35:15,800 --> 00:35:18,680
在每一块超霸的背面 直到永远
On the back of every Speedmaster till the end of time,

608
00:35:18,680 --> 00:35:20,470
(宇航员登上月球时将佩戴欧米茄手表)

609
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:23,390
“第一块被戴上月球的手表” 对吧?
"The first watch worn on the moon." Right?

610
00:35:23,390 --> 00:35:25,060
现在我们得把它立起来
Now we just gotta stand her up.

611
00:35:25,850 --> 00:35:27,310
一切都将是值得的
It's all gonna be worth it.

612
00:35:28,310 --> 00:35:32,190
(美国靠阿波罗11号取得领先)

613
00:35:35,570 --> 00:35:39,530
嘿... 你占了我的车位 我们在为凯莉布景
Hey. Hey! You're in my spot. We're setting up a shot for Kelly.

614
00:35:50,460 --> 00:35:54,080
我们的阿波罗11号任务有三位宇航员
We've got three astronauts on the Apollo 11 mission.

615
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:57,750
他们站在三辆漂亮的美国汽车前
There they are in front of three beautiful American cars.

616
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:59,010
真棒
Oh, this is great.

617
00:35:59,010 --> 00:36:00,550
你们必须立刻前往测试楼
You gotta be in the test facility right now.

618
00:36:00,550 --> 00:36:01,510
跟凯莉说
Talk to Kelly.

619
00:36:01,510 --> 00:36:03,390
凯莉说我们花1块就能开走科尔维特
Kelly said we could take a Corvette home for a dollar.

620
00:36:03,390 --> 00:36:04,430
你来啦 1美元?
There you are. A dollar?

621
00:36:04,430 --> 00:36:06,180
我需要占用他们15分钟而已
I'm gonna need them for 15 minutes, but that's all.

622
00:36:06,180 --> 00:36:08,270
我15分钟前就需要他们了 凯莉
I needed them 15 minutes ago, Kelly.

623
00:36:08,270 --> 00:36:10,560
你知道他们穿的宇航服有多贵吗?
You know how expensive those suits are?

624
00:36:11,310 --> 00:36:14,940
别担心 他只是发射主管
Oh, don't worry. It's just the launch director.

625
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:17,980
登月舱的样子很怪 凯利先生 它的原理是什么?
This strange looking bird, the LEM, Mr. Kelly. How does it work?

626
00:36:17,980 --> 00:36:20,280
这是让人
Well, this is a spacecraft that's used

627
00:36:20,280 --> 00:36:22,240
着陆到月球表面的飞船
to take men down to the lunar surface.

628
00:36:22,990 --> 00:36:25,740
登月舱里三位宇航员中的两位...
And two of the three astronauts in the LEM...

629
00:36:29,950 --> 00:36:33,500
飞行指挥 我们错过了目标 正飘向广袤的虚空
Flight, we missed target and are drifting into the vast abyss.

630
00:36:36,920 --> 00:36:39,050
我们死了 再来 是
And we're dead. Again. Yeah.

631
00:36:39,050 --> 00:36:41,210
着陆前30秒耗尽了燃料
Ran out of fuel 30 seconds before touchdown.

632
00:36:41,220 --> 00:36:42,510
是 但是着陆本身不错
Yeah, but the landing, though,

633
00:36:42,510 --> 00:36:44,430
很顺利 很好 俯仰角度很好 继续
it was smooth... It was good. Great pitch. Forward.

634
00:36:44,430 --> 00:36:45,890
你们俩撒谎的技术真烂
You're both bad liars.

635
00:36:45,890 --> 00:36:49,470
尼尔 迈克 巴兹 能再为琼斯女士 和欧米茄多拍一张照片吗?
Neil, Mike, Buzz, if I can get one more photo for Ms. Jones and Omega?

636
00:36:49,470 --> 00:36:50,560
哥们 你谁啊?
Who are you, man?

637
00:36:53,770 --> 00:36:55,850
好 举起手表 小伙子们
All right, watches up, boys.

638
00:36:55,860 --> 00:36:57,770
给欧米茄来个微笑
And smile for Omega.

639
00:37:05,240 --> 00:37:07,530
我是戴维斯 我打扰到你了吗?
Davis. Am I interrupting?

640
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:11,790
一直在打扰 你面前应该有个盒子
Always. There should be a box in front of you.

641
00:37:11,790 --> 00:37:13,620
不如打开看看?
Why don't you open it?

642
00:37:17,710 --> 00:37:20,130
欧米茄感谢你的服务
Omega thanks you for your service.

643
00:37:20,130 --> 00:37:22,880
你的宇航员们在电视上大出风头
Your boys are all over TV,

644
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:28,890
资金又开始流入了 所以... 共进晚餐?
the taps are flowing again. So... dinner?

645
00:37:30,850 --> 00:37:33,890
好 卡纳维拉尔码头 5点
Yeah. Canaveral Pier. Five o'clock.

646
00:37:34,440 --> 00:37:35,440
戴着手表来
Wear your watch.

647
00:37:37,190 --> 00:37:40,360
下午3点是他们播放采访的 最佳时段 也是最后一个
3:00 p.m. is their best and final time slot to air the interview.

648
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:43,690
播阿姆斯特朗的独家采访? 下午3点是给小孩和闲人看的
For an exclusive with Armstrong? 3:00 p.m. is for children and deadbeats.

649
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:46,200
他们说有战争方面的突发新闻
They said they have breaking news from the war.

650
00:37:48,370 --> 00:37:50,240
敌军规模未知
Unknown size enemy force.

651
00:37:50,240 --> 00:37:52,620
敌军伤亡人数不详
Enemy casualties are unknown,

652
00:37:52,620 --> 00:37:54,330
但大家都看到过到底是怎么回事
but you've seen how it really was.

653
00:37:54,330 --> 00:37:56,460
让阿波罗任务一直有新闻的努力失败了
So much for keeping Apollo back in the news cycle.

654
00:37:56,460 --> 00:37:58,920
英雄主义 危险 恐惧 全部融为一体
Heroism, danger, fear, all rolled into one.

655
00:37:58,920 --> 00:38:00,670
无法用语言形容
Words don't describe it.

656
00:38:00,670 --> 00:38:04,090
我是哥伦比亚广播公司新闻台的 理查德·思雷尔克德 柬埔寨边境附近报道
Richard Threlkeld, CBS News. Near the Cambodian border.

657
00:38:08,430 --> 00:38:10,350
谢谢你 斯科蒂船长 感谢
Thank you, Captain Scotty. Appreciate you.

658
00:38:11,310 --> 00:38:12,310
好
Okay.

659
00:38:12,310 --> 00:38:14,220
你对女士可真是一毛不拔
Well, you spare no expense on a lady.

660
00:38:14,230 --> 00:38:15,640
尝尝看嘛
Just try it.

661
00:38:15,640 --> 00:38:17,100
虾 蛋黄酱 面包
Shrimp, mayo, bun.

662
00:38:17,100 --> 00:38:19,860
这恰好是方圆百里之内最美味的一餐
And that happens to be the best meal in a hundred miles.

663
00:38:24,360 --> 00:38:25,490
我没说错吧
Mmm. Told you.

664
00:38:26,610 --> 00:38:28,740
我怎么不知道这地方?
How'd I not know about this place?

665
00:38:29,240 --> 00:38:30,780
不是所有人都喜欢打广告
Not everybody likes to advertise.

666
00:38:32,160 --> 00:38:33,200
说得妙 有两下子嘛
Nice one. That's good.

667
00:38:39,210 --> 00:38:41,410
那是火箭发射的地方 就是那里
That's where the rocket will launch out of. Right there.

668
00:38:46,090 --> 00:38:48,800
你戴那块手表戴可真好看 你戴着很合适
That watch looks great on you. You wear it very well.

669
00:38:52,180 --> 00:38:53,180
谢谢
Thanks.

670
00:38:57,390 --> 00:38:59,850
那天晚上我在酒吧里跟你说...
That night at the bar, what I said to you...

671
00:38:59,850 --> 00:39:01,480
你的目光无法从我身上挪开
That you couldn't take your eyes off me,

672
00:39:01,480 --> 00:39:03,860
我是你见过最美的女人
and I was the most beautiful woman that you'd ever seen?

673
00:39:03,860 --> 00:39:06,240
对 就是这句 这... 对
Y-Yeah, that part. That... Yes. Mm-hmm.

674
00:39:06,940 --> 00:39:08,490
是我冲动了
It was impulsive.

675
00:39:08,490 --> 00:39:11,450
那是对陌生人说的话 可我们现在共事了
It was meant for a stranger, and we're working together now.

676
00:39:11,450 --> 00:39:13,870
我只是不希望你认为我...
So, I just don't want you to think that I was...

677
00:39:13,870 --> 00:39:14,950
对我有意思?
Interested?

678
00:39:17,250 --> 00:39:18,670
我只是想把话说清楚
I just wanted to clear the air.

679
00:39:19,170 --> 00:39:21,170
好的 说得很清楚
Oh. Well, the air was clear.

680
00:39:21,830 --> 00:39:22,840
很好
Good.

681
00:39:29,380 --> 00:39:33,100
我有个想法 对 那话只适用30秒
I had a thought. Yeah. It was perfect for 30 seconds.

682
00:39:33,100 --> 00:39:35,260
有哪个电视网是全天候报道的?
What are the networks covering night and day?

683
00:39:35,810 --> 00:39:37,390
你觉得我有时间看电视吗?
You think I have time to watch TV?

684
00:39:37,930 --> 00:39:41,190
越南 他们直接从前线报道
Vietnam. They're broadcasting straight from the action.

685
00:39:41,190 --> 00:39:43,020
人们已经不想只听新闻了
And people don't want to just hear the news anymore.

686
00:39:43,020 --> 00:39:44,980
他们想直击新闻现场
They wanna see it in the making.

687
00:39:45,650 --> 00:39:46,650
好吧
Okay.

688
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:56,280
不妨就让他们看
Why not let 'em?

689
00:39:53,160 --> 00:39:56,280
(登月现场直播 阿波罗11号)

690
00:39:56,290 --> 00:39:58,790
你想在登月舱里放个电视直播摄像机?
Oh, you want to put a live television camera on the LEM?

691
00:39:58,790 --> 00:40:00,040
是的
Yes.

692
00:40:00,040 --> 00:40:01,670
我的人在太空里努力活命
My guys are trying to survive up there.

693
00:40:01,670 --> 00:40:03,630
没时间学如何拍电影
They don't have time to figure out how to film a movie.

694
00:40:03,630 --> 00:40:06,130
我们替他们学 他们只需对准目标拍摄即可
We'll figure it out for 'em. All they have to do is point and shoot.

695
00:40:06,130 --> 00:40:08,510
你不明白 这是后勤方面的噩梦
You don't get it. It's a logistical nightmare.

696
00:40:08,510 --> 00:40:11,260
问题涉及电力 储存空间 重量
There's power issues, storage, weight.

697
00:40:11,260 --> 00:40:13,180
甚至没有摄像机能在太空里工作
There's not even a camera that would work up there

698
00:40:13,180 --> 00:40:16,720
因为夜晚温度是零下129摄氏度 白天超过121摄氏度
'cause it's negative 200 degrees at night and over 250 degrees during the daytime.

699
00:40:17,310 --> 00:40:18,810
你能想像看直播的情景吗?
Can you imagine seeing it?

700
00:40:19,520 --> 00:40:21,980
不能 我刚说了这不可能
No. I just said it's impossible.

701
00:40:21,980 --> 00:40:23,730
对 这就是重点
Yes. That's the point. Mmm.

702
00:40:23,730 --> 00:40:25,810
这将是有史以来最伟大的电视节目
It would be the greatest televised event ever.

703
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:27,530
你认为这是个综艺节目吗?
Do you think this is a game show?

704
00:40:28,150 --> 00:40:29,820
苏联人没有播出
There is a very good reason

705
00:40:29,820 --> 00:40:32,650
他们在太空行走是有充分理由的
why the Soviets aren't broadcasting their space walks.

706
00:40:32,660 --> 00:40:34,700
因为苏联是守口如瓶的独裁政权国
Because they're a tight-lipped dictatorship.

707
00:40:34,700 --> 00:40:35,990
对 我们不是 天啊
Yeah, that's not us. Wow.

708
00:40:35,990 --> 00:40:38,040
我们取得成功 是举国成功
When we succeed, we do it as a nation.

709
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:40,410
我们遭遇失败 是举国悲痛 对
And when we fail, we grieve as a nation. Right.

710
00:40:40,410 --> 00:40:42,210
这就是作为美国人的意义所在
That's what it means to be American.

711
00:40:42,210 --> 00:40:44,750
别跟我说作为美国人意味着什么
Oh, stop telling me what it means to be an American.

712
00:40:44,750 --> 00:40:47,960
我们当中只有一个人一辈子在报效祖国
There's only one of us here that has served their country their entire life.

713
00:40:51,590 --> 00:40:53,800
抱歉 登月舱里不会放摄像机的
I'm sorry. We're not putting the camera on the LEM.

714
00:40:59,560 --> 00:41:00,850
我是认真的 不放
I mean it. We're not.

715
00:41:03,060 --> 00:41:04,060
我们会放的
We are.

716
00:41:06,940 --> 00:41:08,940
(压力点)

717
00:41:10,570 --> 00:41:12,490
没有更多燃料 他不可能成功
There's no way he can do it without more fuel.

718
00:41:16,570 --> 00:41:18,200
让他再测一次 好
Have him run it again. Yeah.

719
00:41:25,080 --> 00:41:27,290
好 我时间很紧 什么事?
Okay. [sighs] I'm on a tight schedule. What is it?

720
00:41:27,290 --> 00:41:31,250
凯莉跟我说了摄像机的点子 我们很喜欢
Kelly briefed me on the camera idea, and we like it.

721
00:41:31,260 --> 00:41:33,220
非常喜欢
We like it a lot.

722
00:41:33,220 --> 00:41:35,550
她说错了 我们做不到
She misspoke. We can't do it.

723
00:41:36,140 --> 00:41:38,510
根本没有这种科技
There is no such technology that even exists.

724
00:41:38,510 --> 00:41:40,140
其实有 你知道吗?
Actually it does. You know?

725
00:41:40,720 --> 00:41:43,890
这是国防部设计的
The Department of Defense designed this

726
00:41:43,890 --> 00:41:47,310
为了夜间寻找在越南被击落的飞行员
to find downed fighter pilots in Vietnam at night.

727
00:41:47,310 --> 00:41:51,940
听着 这是机密 但国防部会给你使用
Now, it's classified but the DOD is going to let you use it

728
00:41:51,940 --> 00:41:53,780
只要没人知道它是什么即可
as long as nobody knows what it is.

729
00:41:53,780 --> 00:41:55,950
绝对没有空间装这么重的设备
There's absolutely no space for equipment that heavy.

730
00:41:55,950 --> 00:41:57,700
老天 我们连螺丝钉都称重
We are weighing screws for God's sake.

731
00:41:57,700 --> 00:41:59,570
什么... 这也就7公斤吧
What... I mean, what is this, 15 pounds?

732
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:01,450
好吧 那就用轻一些的螺丝钉
Okay. So, just, like, lighter screws.

733
00:42:01,450 --> 00:42:03,370
我们在试用另一个燃料单元
We're trying for another fuel cell.

734
00:42:03,370 --> 00:42:08,170
好让我们的人登月后 依然有足够的燃料发射
So our men, when they get to the moon, they still have enough fuel to lift off.

735
00:42:08,170 --> 00:42:11,340
她所有的馊主意当中 这个是最糟糕的
Out of all her bad ideas, this one is the worst.

736
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:14,840
其实总统很喜欢这个点子
Actually, the president loves it.

737
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:17,430
所以现在这就是个好主意
So, now it's a great idea.

738
00:42:17,430 --> 00:42:20,140
我跟你用简单的话说吧 科尔
So, let me put it to you simply, Cole.

739
00:42:20,140 --> 00:42:22,890
找个办法把这东西放进那东西
Find a way to put this on that.

740
00:42:22,890 --> 00:42:25,810
这是命令 顶头老大下达的
This is an order. From the tippy top.

741
00:42:37,570 --> 00:42:40,030
唐 斯图 请到这里来
Don, Stu. Can you come in here, please?

742
00:42:43,580 --> 00:42:46,580
谢谢 别什么事都闹别扭
Thank you. Let's not make everything so hard.

743
00:42:48,920 --> 00:42:52,170
请帮琼斯小姐把这个绝密摄像机拆出来
Please help Miss Jones strip this top secret camera down.

744
00:42:52,170 --> 00:42:54,340
我不希望他们知道这是绝密
I don't want 'em to know it's top secret.

745
00:42:54,340 --> 00:42:55,420
现在他们知道了
Well, now they do.

746
00:42:55,420 --> 00:42:57,260
请把这个绝密摄像机拆出来
Please strip this top secret camera.

747
00:42:57,260 --> 00:43:00,090
装在登月舱上 以备直播
Mount it onto the LEM for live broadcasting.

748
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:04,350
科尔 还有一件事
Cole. One last thing.

749
00:43:04,350 --> 00:43:09,310
上周 一架中情局的间谍飞机拍到几张
Last week, a CIA spy plane took some surveillance photographs

750
00:43:09,310 --> 00:43:12,110
苏联新型N1火箭的照片
of the new Russian N1 rocket.

751
00:43:12,110 --> 00:43:13,820
国会看到了
And Congress saw it,

752
00:43:13,820 --> 00:43:16,690
有些议员对最后一轮拨款
and some of the members are having cold feet

753
00:43:16,690 --> 00:43:19,360
产生了疑虑
about the final round of funding.

754
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:21,280
我们还有好几个月才能赢下登月竞赛
We're months away from winning this thing.

755
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:23,030
我会让他们来这里参观
I'm gonna send them down here,

756
00:43:23,030 --> 00:43:25,290
你要说服他们稍安勿躁
and you're gonna convince them to sit tight.

757
00:43:26,080 --> 00:43:28,210
不 我... 来写几个和他们谈话的要点
No. I'm... I'm gonna write up some talking points.

758
00:43:37,630 --> 00:43:39,760
别往心里去
Don't take it personally.

759
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:43,300
飞行员和重力对抗 这是他们的天性
Pilots fight gravity. It's part of their nature.

760
00:44:05,450 --> 00:44:06,450
亨利?
Henry?

761
00:44:11,710 --> 00:44:13,670
我... 很高兴你不是科尔
Well, I'm... I'm glad you're not Cole.

762
00:44:13,670 --> 00:44:14,750
是
Oh? Yeah.

763
00:44:15,250 --> 00:44:16,920
他不喜欢我吸烟
He don't like me smoking.

764
00:44:16,920 --> 00:44:18,920
怎么 你怕他会给你下禁足令?
What, are you worried he's gonna ground you?

765
00:44:21,760 --> 00:44:26,260
不 我... 去年做了紧急搭桥手术
Uh, no. I, uh... I had emergency bypass surgery last year.

766
00:44:26,260 --> 00:44:29,810
对 那个混蛋非常顽固 非要我活下去
Yeah. That son of a bitch. He's hell-bent on keeping me alive.

767
00:44:29,810 --> 00:44:31,520
抱歉 我不知道
I'm sorry. I didn't know.

768
00:44:31,520 --> 00:44:33,440
是 这里没人知道
Yeah. Nobody here does.

769
00:44:33,440 --> 00:44:34,730
除了科尔
Just Cole.

770
00:44:35,440 --> 00:44:40,110
对 他到医院来 安慰了我太太三天
Yeah. He came to the hospital and held my wife's hand for three days.

771
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:44,820
是的 我们认识很久了
Yeah. It's a long way from the day we met.

772
00:44:48,120 --> 00:44:49,870
当时那小子刚从朝鲜回来
Kid had just got back from Korea.

773
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:53,250
是空军最优秀的飞行员
The top pilot in the Air Force.

774
00:44:54,080 --> 00:44:56,500
银星勋章 飞行十字勋章
Silver Star. Flying Cross.

775
00:44:57,670 --> 00:45:01,300
他们当时选宇航员时 他在爱德华兹空军基地是头号人选
He was first in line at Edwards when they were looking for astronauts.

776
00:45:01,300 --> 00:45:04,970
但他最后没能入选
But, uh, he ended up not making the cut.

777
00:45:07,430 --> 00:45:10,480
为什么? 是他的脾气吧
So, what got him? It was his temper.

778
00:45:11,390 --> 00:45:14,480
不... 是他的心脏
No, no. His heart.

779
00:45:14,480 --> 00:45:15,850
医生发现他有心房颤动
Doc found an A-fib.

780
00:45:15,860 --> 00:45:20,150
这个小毛病足以让他无法参加太空计划
A little thing but enough to keep him out of the program.

781
00:45:21,740 --> 00:45:24,660
最优秀的飞行员科尔·戴维斯 却永远无法上太空
Cole Davis is the best pilot who will never get to space.

782
00:45:39,130 --> 00:45:43,300
我在过去15年里天天看这个景色
You know, I've been looking at this view every day for the last 15 years.

783
00:45:44,340 --> 00:45:48,180
但最近我有种第一次看到的感觉
But lately, it's like I'm seeing it for the first time.

784
00:45:50,850 --> 00:45:54,640
阿波罗1号给这里留下了巨大的阴影
Apollo 1 cast a big shadow on this place.

785
00:45:57,690 --> 00:46:00,690
重新看到一些光明真好
It's nice to have some light back.

786
00:46:04,280 --> 00:46:05,280
好了
Okay.

787
00:46:09,580 --> 00:46:12,200
嘿 我总看到科尔每天晚上开车去那边
Hey, I keep seeing Cole drive out there every night.

788
00:46:14,580 --> 00:46:15,580
他在做什么?
What's he doing?

789
00:46:19,590 --> 00:46:20,590
做园艺
Gardening.

790
00:47:21,190 --> 00:47:22,190
(34号发射场)

791
00:47:22,190 --> 00:47:25,280
(阿波罗1号乘组的精神永垂不朽)

792
00:47:40,920 --> 00:47:43,290
准备好了吗? 好了
You ready? Yeah.

793
00:47:50,550 --> 00:47:52,890
好 听着 我们... 带参议员参观一下
All right. Look, we just... We give the senator a tour.

794
00:47:52,890 --> 00:47:56,350
我们好好哄他30分钟 把这个地方运营下去
We play nice for 30 minutes. We keep the lights on.

795
00:47:57,270 --> 00:47:58,560
好 行吧
Okay. Fine.

796
00:47:59,810 --> 00:48:01,600
怎么了? 它在那里
What? She's just there.

797
00:48:01,600 --> 00:48:02,770
别... 跑 不...
Don't run. No, no.

798
00:48:02,770 --> 00:48:04,890
千万别跑 别... 等等 闭嘴
Just don't run. Don't... Wait. [shushing] Shut up.

799
00:48:05,650 --> 00:48:06,780
不 你看 你把它吓跑了
No. See, you scared it.

800
00:48:06,780 --> 00:48:07,860
我刚吃过东西
I just ate.

801
00:48:12,990 --> 00:48:16,160
亨利 快...
Henry, come on! Come on!

802
00:48:21,460 --> 00:48:22,670
我讨厌那只猫
I hate that cat.

803
00:48:22,670 --> 00:48:25,090
我懂你的意思
I see what y... you mean.

804
00:48:25,090 --> 00:48:28,630
这... 猫真讨厌 你看到它看我的眼神了吗?
That's an asshole cat. Did you see the look it gave me?

805
00:48:28,630 --> 00:48:30,340
它在嘲讽我
It's just taunting me now.

806
00:48:31,470 --> 00:48:33,840
这是什么? 是猫食
What is that? That's cat food.

807
00:48:33,850 --> 00:48:36,100
有人在喂它 是谁?
Somebody's feeding that thing. Who's doing that?

808
00:48:36,100 --> 00:48:38,970
找出来 立刻查出是谁 立刻炒掉
Find them. [pants] Find them immediately, and fire them immediately.

809
00:48:38,980 --> 00:48:41,560
戴维斯先生 长官 霍普参议员来了
Mr. Davis. Sir, uh, Senator Hopp is here.

810
00:48:41,560 --> 00:48:43,270
好 怎么了? 你看起来很帅
All right. What? You look fine.

811
00:48:43,270 --> 00:48:44,360
参议员
Senator.

812
00:48:44,940 --> 00:48:46,730
你好 戴维斯先生 参议员 我很荣幸
Hello, Mr. Davis. Senator. What an honor.

813
00:48:46,730 --> 00:48:49,570
我很荣幸 幸会 先生 幸会
It's an honor and a pleasure. Very nice to see you.

814
00:48:52,360 --> 00:48:54,360
阿波罗11号太空舱已经运达
Well, the Apollo 11 capsule has arrived,

815
00:48:54,370 --> 00:48:57,830
下周 我们会把它装在土星5号火箭上
and next week, we will be attaching it to the Saturn V rocket.

816
00:48:57,830 --> 00:49:01,080
也就是发射升空 带我们离开地球大气层的那个火箭
And that gets us off the ground and out of earth's atmosphere.

817
00:49:02,040 --> 00:49:05,830
这些都很了不起 但我得直说
Well, that's all very impressive, but I have to be up-front.

818
00:49:05,840 --> 00:49:09,130
佐治亚州今年洪水泛滥
Georgia had some devastating floods this year.

819
00:49:09,130 --> 00:49:12,470
我要投票把这笔钱用于赈灾
And I'm voting to put this money toward our relief fund.

820
00:49:12,470 --> 00:49:14,430
这似乎有点自私 不是吗?
That seems a little selfish, don't you think?

821
00:49:15,050 --> 00:49:16,970
你说什么? 就是一种说法
Excuse me? Uh, that's a figure of speech.

822
00:49:16,970 --> 00:49:19,600
他是这个意思 我的大多数投票人认为
Here's what he means. My voters mostly think

823
00:49:19,600 --> 00:49:22,230
我们在登月计划上花费过多
we are overspending on the moon.

824
00:49:22,230 --> 00:49:23,850
有意思 因为当我... 哟呼
That's funny, because... Yoo-hoo!

825
00:49:23,850 --> 00:49:25,940
不好意思 霍普参议员
Excuse me. Senator Hopp.

826
00:49:25,940 --> 00:49:28,360
你可能不记得我了
Oh, you probably don't remember me,

827
00:49:28,360 --> 00:49:31,530
但你在我大二时来我学校做过演讲
but you spoke at my sophomore year of college.

828
00:49:31,530 --> 00:49:33,700
佐治亚理工学院 1955级
Georgia Tech. '55.

829
00:49:33,700 --> 00:49:34,950
你是个大黄蜂校友?
You're a Buzz?

830
00:49:34,950 --> 00:49:37,070
是的 先生 我当然记得
Yes, sir. Of course I remember.

831
00:49:37,080 --> 00:49:39,280
那天 你的话激励了我
Your words inspired me that day.

832
00:49:39,290 --> 00:49:43,210
你说“承诺意味着忠于一项事业”
You said, "Commitment means staying loyal to a cause."

833
00:49:43,210 --> 00:49:46,880
两年后 我以优异的成绩毕业 现在我负责这个部门
Two years later, I graduated with honors. Now I run this department.

834
00:49:47,420 --> 00:49:50,130
1962年 你曾说过 你无论如何
You know, in '62 you said that you would fight

835
00:49:50,130 --> 00:49:53,170
都会为肯尼迪的梦想而奋斗
for Kennedy's dream no matter what.

836
00:49:53,170 --> 00:49:56,220
我知道登月任务在当时比现在受欢迎
I know that the moon mission was more popular back then,

837
00:49:56,220 --> 00:49:59,430
但如果那个激励我 在国家航空航天局工作的人
but it would be just a shame

838
00:50:00,350 --> 00:50:03,940
没能照当年的那些话去做
if the man whose words inspired me to work at NASA

839
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,770
就太可惜了
didn't live by those very same words.

840
00:50:08,690 --> 00:50:12,860
那就太可惜了 不是吗? 先生 你真是个了不起的人
It would be a shame, wouldn't it? Sir, you are just such a wonderful man.

841
00:50:12,860 --> 00:50:14,030
非常感谢
Thank you so much. Mmm.

842
00:50:14,030 --> 00:50:15,400
你真了不起
You are a wonderful man.

843
00:50:15,410 --> 00:50:17,490
她可真是个佐治亚州甜心美女
Isn't she just a wonderful Georgia peach here?

844
00:50:17,490 --> 00:50:18,570
天啊 是
Oh, my. Oh. Yes.

845
00:50:18,570 --> 00:50:20,740
你嘴真甜 是的
You are so sweet. Yes, I am.

846
00:50:20,740 --> 00:50:24,750
我带你来一次贵宾级的参观吧 这是他们的保密项目
Let me take you on the special VIP tour they didn't tell you about.

847
00:50:24,750 --> 00:50:26,710
好啊 太好了
Oh, I'd love that. Wonderful.

848
00:50:26,710 --> 00:50:28,710
你会陪我一起参观吗?
Do you go on this tour with me?

849
00:50:28,710 --> 00:50:30,250
当然会
I absolutely will.

850
00:50:30,250 --> 00:50:31,880
你真好
That's so sweet.

851
00:50:31,880 --> 00:50:33,800
她都热泪盈眶了 真吓人
She teared up. I mean, it's scary.

852
00:50:35,630 --> 00:50:36,630
挥手微笑
Wave and smile.

853
00:50:38,010 --> 00:50:39,010
拜拜
Bye-bye!

854
00:50:41,560 --> 00:50:45,390
太空计划不光臃肿又混乱
The space program is not only a bloated mess,

855
00:50:45,390 --> 00:50:49,400
阿波罗号还是对上帝
but Apollo flies in the face of our creator

856
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:53,610
和我国国父的不敬 我想提醒大家 我们不...
and the true father of this country. I would remind you that we don't...

857
00:50:53,610 --> 00:50:58,570
我们搞定了霍普 还需要两票 看起来不会是范宁了
We landed Hopp. We need two more votes. Looks like it's not gonna be Vanning.

858
00:50:58,570 --> 00:51:02,200
绝对不是范宁 接下来是库克参议员
Definitely not Vanning. Next, we have Senator Cook.

859
00:51:02,200 --> 00:51:04,040
库克有点吓人 我实话实说
Cook's a little scary. I'm not gonna lie.

860
00:51:04,040 --> 00:51:05,910
他是冷战时期的保守派
He's a Cold War conservative.

861
00:51:05,910 --> 00:51:10,710
他担心我们的预算 会从国防部的武器研发经费里出
He's worried that our budget takes away from weapons development at the DOD.

862
00:51:12,250 --> 00:51:14,300
好 参议员 有了N1火箭
Now, Senator, with the N1 rocket,

863
00:51:14,300 --> 00:51:16,720
苏联人还是有可能抢在我们前面登月
the Russians still could land on the moon before us.

864
00:51:16,720 --> 00:51:18,760
我们接下来要向你展示的最新情报
What we're about to show you is our most recent intel

865
00:51:18,760 --> 00:51:20,760
是他们登月后计划建造的东西
on what they plan to build if they do.

866
00:51:27,020 --> 00:51:28,310
这些是照片? 不是 先生
And these are photos? No, sir.

867
00:51:28,310 --> 00:51:31,400
是概念画 描绘可能的未来
Those are, uh, renderings of a possible future.

868
00:51:31,400 --> 00:51:32,940
未来的照片?
Future photos?

869
00:51:36,150 --> 00:51:37,150
那是个激光炮?
Is that a laser?

870
00:51:37,150 --> 00:51:39,030
它正对着地球开火 先生
It's going towards earth, sir.

871
00:51:39,030 --> 00:51:42,870
它叫什么? “要你命月球激光大杀器” 先生
What are they calling it? "Killer Lunar Laser Eliminator," sir.

872
00:51:43,740 --> 00:51:46,000
“要你命月球激光大杀器”? 是 先生
"Killer Lunar Laser Eliminator"? Yes, sir.

873
00:51:47,710 --> 00:51:48,710
见鬼 厉害了
Damn it. That's good.

874
00:51:48,710 --> 00:51:51,170
最后还有赫奇斯参议员
And, finally, we have Senator Hedges.

875
00:51:51,170 --> 00:51:53,420
他一直是阿波罗的粉丝
Now, he's always been a fan of Apollo,

876
00:51:53,420 --> 00:51:57,130
但州政党给他施压 叫他不得拨款
but he's getting pressure from his state party not to fund.

877
00:51:57,720 --> 00:52:00,340
他连呼吸都要对着媒体的镜头
He can't take in oxygen without a camera pointed at him,

878
00:52:00,340 --> 00:52:03,260
那我们就去请点扛摄像机的朋友来
and we're about to have a few of those around here.

879
00:52:03,850 --> 00:52:05,010
有什么问题吗?
Any questions?

880
00:52:05,010 --> 00:52:06,100
没有 女士
No, ma'am.

881
00:52:06,810 --> 00:52:08,390
那我们去搞定他吧
Well, let's get him then.

882
00:52:10,350 --> 00:52:12,730
大家好
Hello, everyone!

883
00:52:16,400 --> 00:52:17,480
先生们
Gentlemen.

884
00:52:17,490 --> 00:52:20,610
我... 很高兴能故地重游 各位
It's... It's... It's great to be back, everyone.

885
00:52:20,610 --> 00:52:23,830
你们知道我有多喜欢阿波罗计划
You know how much I love the Apollo program.

886
00:52:28,040 --> 00:52:30,710
参议员 阿波罗10号只会绕月飞行
Senator. Apollo 10 will just be orbiting the moon.

887
00:52:30,710 --> 00:52:34,290
但能给我们带来 11号在月球着陆的关键信息
But it's gonna get us information critical for the touchdown of 11.

888
00:52:34,290 --> 00:52:36,590
比如着陆条件和地点 了不起
Like landing conditions and location. Amazing.

889
00:52:36,590 --> 00:52:39,090
我们为你准备了专座 参议员 在你的支持者中间
And we've a special seat for you here, Senator, amongst your fans.

890
00:52:39,090 --> 00:52:40,680
为我吗? 谢谢
For me? Oh. Thank you.

891
00:52:41,340 --> 00:52:44,720
阿波罗发射控制中心 现在可以开始
Apollo launch control, and we are go on the countdown

892
00:52:44,720 --> 00:52:47,890
阿波罗10号登月任务的倒计时了
for the Apollo 10 lunar mission at this time.

893
00:52:51,560 --> 00:52:53,400
点火程序启动
We have ignition sequence start.

894
00:52:53,900 --> 00:52:57,280
五 四 三 二...
Five, four, three, two...

895
00:52:58,440 --> 00:53:00,240
所有引擎启动
All engines running.

896
00:53:08,870 --> 00:53:10,620
发射 火箭升空
Liftoff. We have liftoff.

897
00:53:10,620 --> 00:53:12,750
现在是整点后49分
Forty-nine minutes past the hour.

898
00:53:13,250 --> 00:53:15,340
发射塔已分离...
Tower clear. Tower clear.

899
00:53:16,040 --> 00:53:17,210
休斯敦 交给你了
Houston, she's all yours.

900
00:53:41,860 --> 00:53:45,450
壮观的发射 我都等不及回来看阿波罗11号了
Glorious launch. Can't wait to be right back here for Apollo 11.

901
00:53:45,450 --> 00:53:48,030
我们非常感谢你的支持 参议员
We cannot thank you enough for your support, Senator.

902
00:53:48,030 --> 00:53:50,370
有件事会麻烦你们一下
It's gonna cost you more than a pair of binoculars.

903
00:53:50,370 --> 00:53:53,920
我欠老家做新闻的人一个人情
I owe a favor to the news fellas back home.

904
00:53:54,620 --> 00:53:57,630
我希望你能接受他们的出镜采访
I'd like you to give them an on-camera interview.

905
00:53:57,630 --> 00:54:01,000
参议员 我是最不适合出镜的人了
Uh, Senator, I'm the very last person that you want in front of a camera.

906
00:54:01,010 --> 00:54:03,090
我... 不接受采访的
Uh, I d... I don't do interviews.

907
00:54:03,090 --> 00:54:06,390
但为你可以破例 赫奇斯参议员 我们很乐意
Except for you, Senator Hedges. We would be delighted.

908
00:54:06,390 --> 00:54:08,640
这女士很机智
Smart lady.

909
00:54:09,930 --> 00:54:11,600
晚安 晚安
Good night. Good night.

910
00:54:14,640 --> 00:54:15,650
凯莉
Kelly?

911
00:54:16,270 --> 00:54:17,730
没事的
It's okay.

912
00:54:18,940 --> 00:54:20,610
一切尽在掌握
Got it all under control. Mm-hmm.

913
00:54:24,990 --> 00:54:27,320
(好样的 阿波罗)

914
00:54:48,430 --> 00:54:50,930
嘿 嘿
Hey. Hey.

915
00:54:50,930 --> 00:54:52,810
你也可以休息一晚的
You're entitled to a night off too, you know.

916
00:54:52,810 --> 00:54:56,310
我若休息 那就是睡觉
If I am, it's to sleep.

917
00:54:56,310 --> 00:54:58,440
你真的有家吗?
Oh, you actually have a house?

918
00:54:58,440 --> 00:55:00,150
我还以为你在办公室睡呢
I thought you slept at the office.

919
00:55:00,150 --> 00:55:04,240
对 通常是 但... 我有时和珍妮一起睡
Well, yeah. Usually. But, uh... Well, I mean, sometimes I sleep with Jenny.

920
00:55:04,820 --> 00:55:08,030
好吧 是 她一定很棒
Oh, yeah. Right. Oh. I'm sure she's great.

921
00:55:09,280 --> 00:55:10,740
珍妮吗? 对 确实
Jenny? Yeah. She... She is.

922
00:55:14,160 --> 00:55:15,160
想认识一下吗?
You wanna meet her?

923
00:55:15,910 --> 00:55:17,580
好啊 好 珍妮会喜欢你的 来
Yeah. Yeah. She'll love you. Come on.

924
00:55:28,930 --> 00:55:31,680
珍妮 这是凯莉
Jenny. Jenny, uh, this is Kelly.

925
00:55:31,680 --> 00:55:33,100
凯莉 这就是珍妮
Kelly, meet Jenny.

926
00:55:34,100 --> 00:55:36,220
跟我战争中开的那架一样
She's just like the one I flew in the war.

927
00:55:36,230 --> 00:55:40,190
我把它放在这里 方便在周末开出去兜兜风 省时间
Keep her here so I can get my flight hours on the weekends. Saves time.

928
00:55:43,020 --> 00:55:44,320
很漂亮
She's quite a lady.

929
00:55:44,860 --> 00:55:46,820
是的
Yeah. She is.

930
00:55:49,070 --> 00:55:51,570
想飞一圈吗? 不了
Wanna go up? No.

931
00:55:51,570 --> 00:55:52,660
你确定? 确定
You sure? Yeah.

932
00:55:53,490 --> 00:55:55,410
好 来吧
Okay. Come on.

933
00:55:56,450 --> 00:55:57,790
我带你看第二美的景色
Show you the second-best view.

934
00:56:12,800 --> 00:56:15,180
看见那些深色的部分了吗? 看见了
You see those dark parts there? Yeah.

935
00:56:15,180 --> 00:56:16,980
我们称之为“月海”
We call them the seas.

936
00:56:17,560 --> 00:56:19,980
月海里的重力更强一些 所以...
The gravity is stronger in the seas, so...

937
00:56:19,980 --> 00:56:23,610
我们研究过在每一片月海里着陆的情况
We've looked to land in, uh, pretty much every single one of them.

938
00:56:23,610 --> 00:56:25,690
有澄海
You got the Sea of Serenity.

939
00:56:25,690 --> 00:56:28,820
危海 我们很快便排除了这个
Sea of Crises. We crossed that one off the list pretty quick.

940
00:56:28,820 --> 00:56:30,530
对 这个名字不利于宣传
Yeah. That's bad PR.

941
00:56:30,530 --> 00:56:34,660
我们最后决定在宁静海着陆
And then we finally settled on, uh, the Sea of Tranquility.

942
00:56:34,660 --> 00:56:36,080
那是最佳地点
That's the sweet spot.

943
00:56:38,330 --> 00:56:42,750
这么一想 我... 对月球的了解
You know, come to think about it, I... I know a lot more about the moon

944
00:56:42,750 --> 00:56:45,130
远远超过我对你的了解
than I know about you by a long shot.

945
00:56:46,710 --> 00:56:48,260
我甚至不知道你是哪里人
I don't even know where you're from.

946
00:56:50,630 --> 00:56:51,630
堪萨斯
Kansas.

947
00:56:54,180 --> 00:56:55,310
来自堪萨斯的凯莉
Kelly from Kansas.

948
00:56:56,310 --> 00:56:58,770
堪萨斯的凯莉 你是怎么进入广告这一行的?
How'd you get into advertising, Kelly from Kansas?

949
00:57:00,100 --> 00:57:06,270
我爸爸离开时我四岁 妈妈失去了房子
Uh, well, I was four when my dad left, and my mom lost the house.

950
00:57:06,270 --> 00:57:07,570
我们住在汽车里
We lived in a car.

951
00:57:08,110 --> 00:57:12,900
一个教堂给了她一份卖曲奇罐的工作
And... a church gave her a job selling cookie tins.

952
00:57:12,910 --> 00:57:19,080
所以她想了个点子 如果由我挨家挨户推销就能卖出更多
So, she had this idea that we'd sell more if it was me going door-to-door.

953
00:57:19,080 --> 00:57:21,250
是啊 聪明的女士
Oh, yeah. Smart lady.

954
00:57:23,250 --> 00:57:27,710
曲奇罐 然后卖吸尘器 我长大些就转而卖美容用品
Cookie tins, then it was vacuums, then beauty goods when I got older.

955
00:57:27,710 --> 00:57:30,880
是的 我和我妈周游全国
Yeah. Traveling the country, me and my mom.

956
00:57:30,880 --> 00:57:33,260
我们的生活就是这样重回正轨的
It's how we got back on our feet.

957
00:57:36,010 --> 00:57:37,760
我很遗憾你不得不经历这些
Well, I'm sorry you went through that.

958
00:57:41,350 --> 00:57:43,350
不必 我...
Well, don't be. I...

959
00:57:45,520 --> 00:57:47,520
对 我很小就学会了如何生存
Yeah. I learned early on how to survive.

960
00:57:49,940 --> 00:57:54,160
而且家家都有本难念的经
Plus, we all have our share of tough breaks.

961
00:57:58,080 --> 00:58:01,250
亨利跟我说了 心房颤动和你被计划除名的事
Henry told me about the A-fib and you getting kicked out of the program.

962
00:58:02,080 --> 00:58:05,120
我得去跟亨利聊聊
Hmm. I'm gonna have to have a little conversation with Henry.

963
00:58:10,130 --> 00:58:12,300
不过我并不完全赞同你的说法
You know, I don't totally agree with you though.

964
00:58:15,720 --> 00:58:18,260
怎么讲? 我就是不...
How's that? Well, I just don't...

965
00:58:19,180 --> 00:58:22,220
我不认为我们的悲伤故事
I don't think that our sad stories are supposed to

966
00:58:22,230 --> 00:58:23,940
就该教会我们如何在世上生存
teach us how to survive the world.

967
00:58:24,520 --> 00:58:27,690
我认为它们应该激励我们去改变世界
I think they're supposed to make us wanna change it.

968
00:58:29,650 --> 00:58:31,030
科尔
Hmm. Cole!

969
00:58:31,730 --> 00:58:34,320
巴兹正在试图短路发动你的科迈罗
Buzz is trying to hot-wire your Camaro!

970
00:58:35,150 --> 00:58:36,860
拜托 天啊
Come on, man.

971
00:58:37,820 --> 00:58:38,830
那么...
Well...

972
00:58:39,910 --> 00:58:41,330
你最好去阻止他
You better go stop him.

973
00:58:43,250 --> 00:58:44,250
是的
Yeah.

974
00:59:00,600 --> 00:59:02,770
(卫星汽车旅馆)

975
00:59:07,230 --> 00:59:09,560
老天
Jesus!

976
00:59:09,560 --> 00:59:11,190
我们得谈谈
We need to talk.

977
00:59:14,190 --> 00:59:18,110
阿凯 你的工作做得十分出色
You have done outstanding work, Kel.

978
00:59:18,700 --> 00:59:20,530
公众的兴趣大大提高了
Public interest is way up.

979
00:59:21,330 --> 00:59:25,330
你搞定了参议员们 确保发射能顺利进行
You landed the senators and secured the launch.

980
00:59:25,960 --> 00:59:28,000
所以你就闯进我的旅店房间?
And that's why you broke into my motel room?

981
00:59:28,000 --> 00:59:29,250
作为感谢吗?
As a thank you?

982
00:59:29,250 --> 00:59:31,670
现在我们知道全世界都会盯着我们看
Now that we know the whole world will be watching,

983
00:59:31,670 --> 00:59:33,840
我们不容有失
we can't afford to lose.

984
00:59:34,510 --> 00:59:40,180
我们必须准备好呈献一个备用版本的
We need to be prepared to present an alternate version

985
00:59:40,180 --> 00:59:41,760
登月任务
of the moon landing.

986
00:59:43,060 --> 00:59:44,140
一个备用版本?
An alternate version?

987
00:59:44,140 --> 00:59:47,520
阿尔忒弥斯版本
The... Artemis version.

988
00:59:48,810 --> 00:59:53,020
她是阿波罗的孪生姐姐 也就是“备胎”
She was the twin sister of Apollo, uh, you know, the backup.

989
00:59:48,810 --> 00:59:53,020
(绝密 阿尔忒弥斯计划)

990
00:59:53,020 --> 00:59:57,530
我们必须准备好拍一个小短片
So we just need to be ready to shoot a little picture.

991
00:59:57,530 --> 01:00:02,160
向人们展示宇航员在月球上行走
Something showing us, you know, up there walking around,

992
01:00:02,160 --> 01:00:03,950
朝镜头挥手
waving at the camera.

993
01:00:03,950 --> 01:00:07,160
你是说作假? 如果一切顺利 短片永远也用不上
You mean, to fake it? All goes well, we never use it.

994
01:00:08,370 --> 01:00:09,420
但万一...
But if not...

995
01:00:14,670 --> 01:00:16,510
你知道我为什么从没坐过牢吗?
You know why I never went to prison?

996
01:00:16,510 --> 01:00:20,220
大概知道 但你说吧
Probably, but humor me.

997
01:00:20,220 --> 01:00:21,800
因为我见好就收
'Cause I quit while I'm ahead.

998
01:00:22,430 --> 01:00:24,930
这么大的事没法保密 这里有成千上万的员工
Can't keep a secret this big. Thousands of people work here.

999
01:00:27,180 --> 01:00:31,850
也有成千上万人 在一个沙漠中的保密地点工作
Well, thousands of people work at a classified location in the desert

1000
01:00:31,850 --> 01:00:35,980
他们在对一个外星飞行器舰队做实验
that experiments on a fleet of extraterrestrial pods

1001
01:00:35,980 --> 01:00:38,440
是我们从海底捞上来的
that we found at the bottom of the ocean.

1002
01:00:38,440 --> 01:00:41,110
你从来没听说过吧?
And you never heard about that, did ya?

1003
01:00:41,110 --> 01:00:44,070
拜托 没这回事
Come on, that's not true.

1004
01:00:44,080 --> 01:00:48,290
也许没有 也许有
Uh, maybe it is, maybe it isn't.

1005
01:00:48,290 --> 01:00:51,120
但有一件事是可以肯定的
But the one thing you can be sure of

1006
01:00:51,120 --> 01:00:57,260
全世界都将看到美国人 在月球上插上美国国旗
is that the world will watch Americans plant an American flag on the moon.

1007
01:00:58,090 --> 01:01:01,170
你是说尼克松总统支持这么干?
And you are telling me that President Nixon supports this?

1008
01:01:01,180 --> 01:01:04,510
可能会 他还不知情
He probably would. He doesn't know about it

1009
01:01:05,560 --> 01:01:10,810
同样 科尔·戴维斯也会永远蒙在鼓里
in the same way that Cole Davis will never know about it.

1010
01:01:10,810 --> 01:01:12,600
这应该不是个问题
And that shouldn't be a problem

1011
01:01:12,600 --> 01:01:16,270
毕竟虽然你们越走越近
considering what else you haven't shared with him

1012
01:01:16,940 --> 01:01:18,990
但你还是有些事瞒着他
while you've grown closer.

1013
01:01:20,110 --> 01:01:22,570
那么帅气的一个人会怎么想...
I mean, what would a clean-cut guy like that think about...

1014
01:01:22,570 --> 01:01:23,870
你已经说得很清楚了
You made your point.

1015
01:01:24,530 --> 01:01:27,200
谁也摆脱不了自己的过往
No one can outrun their past.

1016
01:01:27,200 --> 01:01:31,160
但我可以永远抹除一个人的黑历史
But I can make it go away. Forever.

1017
01:01:31,830 --> 01:01:33,040
不必再逃亡
No more running.

1018
01:01:40,340 --> 01:01:41,630
我得需要助理帮忙
I'm gonna need my assistant.

1019
01:01:44,090 --> 01:01:45,300
当然
Of course.

1020
01:01:45,300 --> 01:01:49,220
我们会给你配一个安全特工团队
And we'll get you a team of secure agents.

1021
01:01:49,220 --> 01:01:54,850
好了 你手里最厉害 但却没人听说过的导演是谁?
Now, who's the best director you've got that no one's ever heard of?

1022
01:01:59,400 --> 01:02:00,400
你会喜欢他的
You're gonna love him.

1023
01:02:01,030 --> 01:02:02,530
(政府财产 非请莫入)

1024
01:02:02,610 --> 01:02:04,570
这是基地里最偏远的飞机库
This is the most remote hangar on the base.

1025
01:02:04,570 --> 01:02:07,240
没有我的允许 任何人不得出入
No one can go in or out without my permission.

1026
01:02:07,740 --> 01:02:09,740
等等 任何人? 连科尔都不行?
Wait, no one? Not even Cole?

1027
01:02:11,200 --> 01:02:12,410
科尔尤其不行
Especially not Cole.

1028
01:02:16,580 --> 01:02:18,090
难以置信 凯莉
Unbelievable, Kelly.

1029
01:02:18,090 --> 01:02:20,460
你找人强行把我拖上飞机
You have me... forced onto a plane,

1030
01:02:20,460 --> 01:02:22,210
把我带到这该死的佛罗里达
and brought to godforsaken Florida!

1031
01:02:22,220 --> 01:02:23,760
能松手吗?
Do you mind?

1032
01:02:23,760 --> 01:02:26,430
我是美国导演工会成员
I'm a member of the DGA.

1033
01:02:26,970 --> 01:02:28,810
不能被这样粗暴对待
I will not be treated this way.

1034
01:02:29,310 --> 01:02:31,770
我要给经纪人打电话 不行
I am calling my agent. You can't.

1035
01:02:31,770 --> 01:02:32,850
我这就打给你看
Watch me.

1036
01:02:32,850 --> 01:02:36,270
记住 我们谈过的 这是安保级别很高的政府项目
Remember we talked about this. This is a high-security government job.

1037
01:02:37,190 --> 01:02:39,400
我给你的报价翻倍 好吧
I'm doubling your quote. Okay.

1038
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:40,570
还有奖金
With a bonus. Mmm.

1039
01:02:40,570 --> 01:02:45,400
对 唯一的条件是不能让任何人知道 我们在干什么
Yes. The only caveat being that no one can ever know what we're doing.

1040
01:02:45,410 --> 01:02:47,570
这我无法接受 他们会枪毙你
I cannot accept that. They will shoot you.

1041
01:02:48,370 --> 01:02:49,370
预算是多少?
What is my budget?

1042
01:02:49,370 --> 01:02:55,120
你花多少钱都行 只要把这里变成月球
Your budget is whatever it costs to turn this into the moon

1043
01:02:55,120 --> 01:02:56,710
拍出两个半小时的片子来
for two-and-a-half hours.

1044
01:02:57,290 --> 01:02:58,630
比《宾虚》短
It's shorter than Ben-Hur.

1045
01:03:14,020 --> 01:03:16,690
我需要在那边摆一台装满汽水的冰箱
I will need a fridge full of Tab over there.

1046
01:03:18,600 --> 01:03:21,610
和一大群不会提问的手下
And an army of minions who don't ask questions.

1047
01:03:31,200 --> 01:03:35,700
凯莉 这些都不是真正的演员
Kelly, these aren't real actors.

1048
01:03:35,710 --> 01:03:37,910
你只能用他们 这是最好的情况了
Well, this is the best you're gonna get.

1049
01:03:37,920 --> 01:03:39,920
尼尔身高1.8米 谁是1.8米高?
Neil's 5'11 ". Anybody 5'11"?

1050
01:03:40,670 --> 01:03:42,290
好 其他人散了吧
Okay. The rest of you are dismissed.

1051
01:03:42,300 --> 01:03:44,340
选吧 等等 你
Take your pick. Mmm. Hold on. You.

1052
01:03:44,340 --> 01:03:45,670
你来做我的私人助理
You're gonna be my personal assistant.

1053
01:03:45,670 --> 01:03:48,050
我就叫你约瑟夫 这样有什么事你不会往心里去
I'll just call you Joseph so you can't take things personally.

1054
01:03:48,050 --> 01:03:49,340
随便站一边去吧
Go stand somewhere.

1055
01:03:49,340 --> 01:03:51,640
好 能把墨镜都摘了吗?
All right. Can we take these sunglasses off, please,

1056
01:03:51,640 --> 01:03:54,600
好让我看到你们的眼睛 相信你们的话
so I can see your eyes and believe your truth?

1057
01:03:54,600 --> 01:03:56,390
好 我要每个人来一段独白
Now, I want each of you to do a monologue.

1058
01:03:56,390 --> 01:03:59,600
最好是经典桥段 但是老天啊
Preferably something classical, and by God,

1059
01:03:59,600 --> 01:04:01,230
千万别给我来七遍《哈姆雷特》
don't make me watch seven Hamlets.

1060
01:04:01,230 --> 01:04:03,320
你到时候看不见他们的脸 都戴着头盔呢
You're not gonna see their faces. They're wearing helmets.

1061
01:04:03,320 --> 01:04:04,980
什...
Wh...

1062
01:04:06,280 --> 01:04:09,570
好吧 那我如何
All right, how do I convey

1063
01:04:09,570 --> 01:04:12,200
在不让观众看到人脸的情况下
the gripping fear of being on the moon for the first time

1064
01:04:12,200 --> 01:04:14,370
展示第一次登月那揪心的恐惧?
if we can't show a human face?

1065
01:04:14,910 --> 01:04:16,160
表演是一种运动 凯莉
Acting is a sport, Kelly.

1066
01:04:16,160 --> 01:04:18,540
需要能量 身体... 我把设备放哪?
It is energy, body, bu... Where do I set up?

1067
01:04:19,670 --> 01:04:20,710
爱德华?
Edvard? Ah.

1068
01:04:21,330 --> 01:04:23,750
你怎么进来的? 从门口走进来的
How did you get in here? I just walked through the door.

1069
01:04:23,750 --> 01:04:28,670
“此事说出去会害我们被杀” 这句话你哪儿不明白?
What part of "talking about this is gonna get us killed" do you not understand?

1070
01:04:28,680 --> 01:04:31,300
而且他是纽约动作最慢的摄影指导 我来选摄影师
And he's the slowest DP in New York. I pick the cinematographer.

1071
01:04:31,300 --> 01:04:33,680
写在合同里呢 什么? 你没有合同
It's in my contract. What? You don't have a contract.

1072
01:04:33,680 --> 01:04:35,430
他最棒 所有的摄影指导动作都慢
He's the best, and all DPs are slow.

1073
01:04:35,430 --> 01:04:39,310
凯莉 我们最需要的
What we need to have a serious conversation about, Kelly,

1074
01:04:39,310 --> 01:04:41,600
就是美术指导
is production design, hmm?

1075
01:04:41,600 --> 01:04:44,820
我们用什么材料来仿造月球表面?
What materials are we using to recreate the lunar surface?

1076
01:04:44,820 --> 01:04:46,400
月球就是块大石头 对吧?
It's just a big rock, right?

1077
01:04:54,780 --> 01:04:56,620
我没法这样工作 凯莉
I can't work like this, Kelly.

1078
01:04:58,080 --> 01:05:00,000
你是了解我这一点的
You know this about me. Hmm?

1079
01:05:00,000 --> 01:05:01,620
我需要细节
I need details.

1080
01:05:01,620 --> 01:05:04,170
我们需要细节 具体细节
We need details. Specifics.

1081
01:05:04,710 --> 01:05:08,340
是多尘 多石还是有风? 光源是怎样的?
Is it dusty, rocky, windy? What is the light source? Hmm?

1082
01:05:08,340 --> 01:05:12,340
就是太阳咯 大灯 别自作聪明 爱德华
It's the sun. Big light. Do not smart-mouth me, Edvard.

1083
01:05:13,300 --> 01:05:16,100
太阳和着陆区的位置关系是怎样的?
And what is the sun's position in relation to the landing area?

1084
01:05:16,100 --> 01:05:18,180
我们要建一个仿制版吗? 我们有计划吗?
And are we building a replica? Do we have a plan?

1085
01:05:18,180 --> 01:05:21,730
我们有宇航服吗? 演员穿上宇航服如何行动?
Do we have suits, and how do people move in those suits?

1086
01:05:21,730 --> 01:05:24,270
还有 凯莉 太空里到底什么样子?
And what, Kelly, does space even look like?

1087
01:05:24,270 --> 01:05:26,270
我... 得躺一下
You know, I gotta... I gotta lie down.

1088
01:05:26,270 --> 01:05:28,820
我的拖车呢?
Where is my trailer?

1089
01:05:31,320 --> 01:05:34,700
我们得想办法 把那个模拟室里的一切都照搬过来
We need to find a way to copy everything in that simulation room.

1090
01:05:34,700 --> 01:05:36,330
好的 尽快
Okay. ASAP.

1091
01:05:36,330 --> 01:05:38,410
等等 我有拖车吗?
Wait a second. Do I even have a trailer?

1092
01:05:39,580 --> 01:05:41,540
你不说话我也知道
Your silence tells me what I already know.

1093
01:05:41,540 --> 01:05:43,580
你还没想过怎样复刻月球
You haven't thought about how to recreate the moon,

1094
01:05:43,580 --> 01:05:46,630
怎么会想拖车的事? 我觉得我们该找库布里克了
why would you think about a trailer? I think we should've gotten Kubrick.

1095
01:05:46,630 --> 01:05:48,500
我们必须把新的飞船做对了
We've got to get this new ship right.

1096
01:05:48,500 --> 01:05:50,260
阿姆斯特朗很生气
I mean, Armstrong, he was pissed off

1097
01:05:50,260 --> 01:05:51,820
我们不能再惹他了 抱歉
and we can't have that again. Sorry.

1098
01:05:53,380 --> 01:05:54,430
伙计...
Buddy, buddy.

1099
01:05:54,430 --> 01:05:56,470
等等... 这些都是敏感材料
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa. This is sensitive material.

1100
01:05:56,470 --> 01:05:58,390
亨利... 不行 你不能待在这里
Henry. Henry. Uh-uh. You can't be here.

1101
01:05:58,390 --> 01:06:01,180
这些照片是为了企鹅出版社的档案书拍的
These photos are for the archival book that Penguin is doing.

1102
01:06:01,180 --> 01:06:02,980
什么书? 对 你没收到备忘录?
What book? Yeah, didn't you get the memo?

1103
01:06:02,980 --> 01:06:04,440
没有 什么? 你要写前言
No. What? You're writing the foreword.

1104
01:06:04,440 --> 01:06:07,270
我... 写前言? 对 是啊
I... I'm writing the foreword? Yeah, absolutely.

1105
01:06:07,270 --> 01:06:08,820
我? 没错
Me? Yes, of course.

1106
01:06:08,820 --> 01:06:11,190
我从没写过前言 编辑想听听你的话
I've never written a foreword. The editor wants to hear from you.

1107
01:06:11,190 --> 01:06:12,490
我们都想 他要我写?
We all do. He wants me to write it?

1108
01:06:12,490 --> 01:06:14,820
别这么谦虚好吗? 我们给你拍一张和...
Don't be so humble, all right? Let's get a photo of you with the...

1109
01:06:14,820 --> 01:06:16,410
登月舱的合影 我可以写 但...
with the LEM. I mean, I can do it, but...

1110
01:06:16,410 --> 01:06:17,620
说“我们要登月了”
Say, "we're going to the moon."

1111
01:06:17,620 --> 01:06:19,620
我们要登月了 真不错
We're going to the moon. There you go!

1112
01:06:20,290 --> 01:06:23,460
奥尔德林和阿姆斯特朗 每一个动作都要练习
Aldrin and Armstrong will practice every single movement that they make,

1113
01:06:23,460 --> 01:06:25,330
在这里练好几个月
um, right here for months.

1114
01:06:25,330 --> 01:06:26,710
真了不起 是
That is incredible. Yeah.

1115
01:06:26,710 --> 01:06:28,960
这就是月球表面?
So, this is, like, the surface of the moon?

1116
01:06:28,960 --> 01:06:30,090
是 这... 对
Well, yeah. It's... Yeah.

1117
01:06:30,090 --> 01:06:31,420
是我们最接近的模拟
It's our best approximation.

1118
01:06:31,970 --> 01:06:34,380
这看起来就像个肮脏的海滩 我不信 不可能
This just looks like a dirty beach. I don't believe it. No.

1119
01:06:34,380 --> 01:06:36,340
是按... 我们得到的沉积物做的 约瑟夫
It is... It's based off sediment we got. Joseph.

1120
01:06:36,340 --> 01:06:37,260
来自航天局
It's from NASA...

1121
01:06:37,260 --> 01:06:40,140
等等 我不相信这就是国家航空航天局
Wait. I do not believe this is what NASA uses

1122
01:06:40,140 --> 01:06:42,310
用来登月的装备 你别告诉我... 不行
to go to the moon. You cannot tell me... No.

1123
01:06:42,310 --> 01:06:46,400
我要你们假装抱着母亲在沙漠里行走
Want you to walk as if you're carrying your mother across the desert.

1124
01:06:46,400 --> 01:06:49,610
她很脆弱 但也很重
She's frail but also heavy.

1125
01:06:49,610 --> 01:06:51,270
等等 嘿
Oh. Whoa. Hey.

1126
01:06:51,280 --> 01:06:52,820
真抱歉 嘿 对不起 不能拍...
So sorry. Hey. Sorry. Oh, no, no. No.

1127
01:06:52,820 --> 01:06:54,610
这是机密 你不能... 斯图 没事
This is classified. You're not allow... Stu, we're good.

1128
01:06:54,610 --> 01:06:56,450
是机密 没事 这是为那本书拍的
Very classified. We're good here. This is for the book.

1129
01:06:56,450 --> 01:06:57,570
你会听说的
No, you'll hear about it.

1130
01:06:57,570 --> 01:06:58,490
我要写前言
I'm doing the foreword,

1131
01:06:58,490 --> 01:06:59,830
你很快会听说的 好吧
so you'll hear about it soon. Okay.

1132
01:06:59,830 --> 01:07:02,660
我这个阿姆斯特朗是个总爱抱怨的烂人 我们得重新选角
My Armstrong is a whiny, little bitch. We have to recast.

1133
01:07:02,660 --> 01:07:04,290
不 我们不重新选角
No... We're not recasting.

1134
01:07:04,830 --> 01:07:06,540
好吧 那就平庸着拍吧
All right. Well, mediocre it is.

1135
01:07:06,540 --> 01:07:09,000
爱德华 我的太阳呢?
Edvard! Where is my sun?

1136
01:07:09,840 --> 01:07:10,840
很好
Nice!

1137
01:07:10,840 --> 01:07:12,590
非常好 至少来个倒数啊
Very nice. A countdown at least.

1138
01:07:13,090 --> 01:07:14,340
好 再开一次
Okay. Try it again.

1139
01:07:14,340 --> 01:07:15,970
我再开一次 从三倒数
Gonna try it again. Do a three, two, one!

1140
01:07:15,970 --> 01:07:17,050
拜托 满意吗?
Come on! Ah! Happy?

1141
01:07:17,050 --> 01:07:19,340
约瑟夫 给我拿汽水来
J... Joseph, bring me my Tab.

1142
01:07:19,350 --> 01:07:21,600
你得来找我 因为我眼都瞎了
You're gonna have to find me 'cause I can't see a thing.

1143
01:07:21,600 --> 01:07:23,720
拜托 拿个汽水要多久?
Come on. How long does it take to give someone a Tab?

1144
01:07:23,730 --> 01:07:25,310
我的手就在这里
My hand's right here.

1145
01:07:25,310 --> 01:07:27,310
一定会很棒的 你们都该聚过来
Uh, this will be great. You guys should all come around

1146
01:07:27,310 --> 01:07:29,480
我们来给那本书拍一张 很好吧?
and we'll do a shot for the book. Great?

1147
01:07:29,480 --> 01:07:32,020
嘿 各位 这么说如何? “我们要登月了”
Hey, how about this? Everybody, "We're going to the moon!"

1148
01:07:32,030 --> 01:07:35,030
我们要登月了
We're going to the moon!

1149
01:07:35,900 --> 01:07:38,030
我好像眨眼了 再拍一张?
My eyes might have been closed. You wanna do one more?

1150
01:07:40,700 --> 01:07:43,330
最近没看到你
I haven't seen you around lately.

1151
01:07:43,330 --> 01:07:45,370
彼此彼此
Well, I can say the same thing about you.

1152
01:07:47,330 --> 01:07:49,040
你怎么一次就系好了?
How do you do it on the first try?

1153
01:07:49,040 --> 01:07:52,210
这又不是多复杂的事 好 准备好了吗?
It's not rocket science. Okay. You good?

1154
01:07:53,550 --> 01:07:54,760
那些问题 我... 是的
About the questions, I... Yes.

1155
01:07:54,760 --> 01:07:59,050
我都看过了 没有关于阿波罗1号的 他们答应过我 好吗?
I went over them. Nothing about Apollo 1. They promised me. Okay?

1156
01:08:00,510 --> 01:08:02,260
你会表现得很好的 明白吗?
You're gonna be great. Okay?

1157
01:08:02,260 --> 01:08:03,510
去吧
Mm-hmm. Go on.

1158
01:08:03,510 --> 01:08:04,600
好 上
Okay. Go.

1159
01:08:07,190 --> 01:08:10,100
戴维斯先生 你是我们口中的“采访困难户”
Mr. Davis. You are what we call "a tough get."

1160
01:08:10,100 --> 01:08:11,190
哪有 谢谢
Ha! No. Thank you.

1161
01:08:11,190 --> 01:08:14,480
我们将看到尼尔阿姆斯特朗 和巴兹奥尔德林走上月球表面
Is there any legal importance to what we'll be watching

1162
01:08:14,480 --> 01:08:18,110
这有什么法律方面的重要意义吗?
when Neil Armstrong and Buzz Aldrin walk on the lunar surface?

1163
01:08:18,110 --> 01:08:22,160
他们着陆的区域会被视为归美国所有吗?
Will the area they land on be considered property of the United States?

1164
01:08:22,160 --> 01:08:25,830
我们要送一块匾上去 写着“我们为全人类的和平而来”
We're sending a plaque that says, "We came in peace for all mankind."

1165
01:08:25,830 --> 01:08:27,410
那正是我们的意思
And that is precisely what we mean.

1166
01:08:27,410 --> 01:08:29,460
国家航空航天局还会留下其他什么东西?
What else will NASA leave behind?

1167
01:08:29,960 --> 01:08:32,290
足迹 一面美国国旗和12袋粪便
Footprints, an American flag and 12 bags of feces

1168
01:08:32,290 --> 01:08:35,250
他们跟我说了很多次不要提 但是...
that I was told many times that I should not bring up, but...

1169
01:08:35,250 --> 01:08:37,210
我们真该早点让他接受采访
Should've put him in front of a camera sooner.

1170
01:08:37,220 --> 01:08:38,800
你戴着一枚阿波罗胸针
You wear an Apollo pin.

1171
01:08:39,930 --> 01:08:41,430
是的
I do. Um,

1172
01:08:41,430 --> 01:08:43,810
是阿波罗1号乘组的太太们
the wives of Apollo 1's men,

1173
01:08:45,010 --> 01:08:47,100
在丈夫们牺牲后送我的
after we lost them, they gave me this.

1174
01:08:47,100 --> 01:08:50,100
在那悲剧的一天 你是发射主管
You were launch director on that tragic day.

1175
01:08:51,020 --> 01:08:53,690
阿波罗1号出了什么故障?
What went wrong with Apollo 1?

1176
01:08:56,990 --> 01:08:59,900
用你自己的话说 发生了什么?
In your own words, what happened?

1177
01:09:01,490 --> 01:09:02,530
帮我回顾一下
Take me back.

1178
01:09:06,790 --> 01:09:09,830
好 我来给你列举一些事实
Okay. Here's some facts for you.

1179
01:09:09,830 --> 01:09:11,000
《纽约时报》报道
The New York Times reported

1180
01:09:11,000 --> 01:09:13,710
那艘飞船曾有两万份安全事件报告
there were 20,000 safety reports filed about that ship.

1181
01:09:13,710 --> 01:09:17,420
实在太多 以至于加斯·格里森 用一个柠檬表示自己的不满
So many, that Gus Grissom hung a lemon outside it.

1182
01:09:19,970 --> 01:09:22,970
好了 乘组 待确认 位置
All right, crew. To be confirmed. Location.

1183
01:09:22,970 --> 01:09:23,970
着火了
Flame!

1184
01:09:23,970 --> 01:09:26,050
驾驶舱里失火了
We've got a fire in the cockpit.

1185
01:09:26,060 --> 01:09:26,970
快出去
Let's get out!

1186
01:09:26,970 --> 01:09:29,980
戴维斯先生 你读过那些报告吗?
Mr. Davis? Did you read those reports?

1187
01:09:29,980 --> 01:09:32,100
发射台主管 快进去救他们
Pad leader, get in there and help 'em.

1188
01:09:32,650 --> 01:09:34,560
发射台主管 盯着C3
Pad leader, stay on C3.

1189
01:09:40,610 --> 01:09:43,070
戴维斯先生 你读过那些报告吗?
Mr. Davis? Did you read those reports?

1190
01:09:45,320 --> 01:09:49,450
你读过那些报告吗? 我当然读过那些报告
Did you read those reports? Of course I read the reports.

1191
01:09:49,950 --> 01:09:51,460
每一份都读过
I read every single one of them.

1192
01:09:52,160 --> 01:09:55,250
独立供电测试期间 氧气压力过高的同时遇到了线路故障
Overpressured oxygen and a bad wire on a "plugs-out" test.

1193
01:09:56,170 --> 01:10:00,210
我本该查出一切问题的 我看漏了 辜负了他们
I was supposed to catch everything, and I missed it. And I failed them.

1194
01:10:00,210 --> 01:10:03,050
我余生中的每一天都会为此感到愧疚
And I will live with that every single day for the rest of my life.

1195
01:10:03,050 --> 01:10:05,680
人渣 这是你想引述的原话吗?
Is that the quote that you were looking for, you piece of shit?

1196
01:10:05,680 --> 01:10:08,220
让我跟你的老板通话 立刻 马上
Get me on the phone with your boss. Now. Now!

1197
01:10:09,390 --> 01:10:12,390
等等 你干什么? 采访还有20分钟
Oh, uh, wait. W-What are you doing? We have another 20 minutes.

1198
01:10:12,390 --> 01:10:13,480
去死吧
Go to hell.

1199
01:10:13,480 --> 01:10:16,440
别生我的气 害死三个宇航员的人不是我
Don't be angry with me. I'm not the reason three astronauts are dead.

1200
01:10:20,900 --> 01:10:22,990
你再提一句那些宇航员试试 嘿... 别冲动
Say one more thing about the astronauts. Hey, hey, hey! Whoa!

1201
01:10:22,990 --> 01:10:24,910
放开我 你再说一句试试
Get off me. Let me hear you say one more thing...

1202
01:10:24,910 --> 01:10:26,700
你再提他们一句试试
Let me hear you say one more thing about them!

1203
01:10:26,700 --> 01:10:28,870
你不认识他们 你不准再提他们
You don't know those men! You don't talk about those men!

1204
01:10:28,870 --> 01:10:30,660
放开我 放开
Get off me! Get off!

1205
01:10:30,660 --> 01:10:31,750
放开
Get off!

1206
01:10:32,250 --> 01:10:33,410
听懂了吗?
Do you understand me?

1207
01:10:40,300 --> 01:10:43,470
我跟制作人们谈过了 他们同意不播出这段采访
So, I spoke to the producers, and they've agreed to seal the film

1208
01:10:43,470 --> 01:10:47,180
条件是阿姆斯特朗着陆后 给他们独家采访
if we give them the exclusive with Armstrong after he lands.

1209
01:10:52,350 --> 01:10:54,770
不过我们失去了赫奇斯的支持 他要投反对票了
We lost Hedges though. He's voting no.

1210
01:10:55,480 --> 01:10:59,940
你说过他们不会问的 是的 他们撒谎了
You said they wouldn't ask about it. Yeah. Well... they lied.

1211
01:10:59,940 --> 01:11:01,570
人们有时是会撒谎的 科尔
You know, people do that sometimes, Cole.

1212
01:11:01,570 --> 01:11:03,570
你也许可以说点假话 那也算为自己
You could have done yourself and this program a favor

1213
01:11:03,570 --> 01:11:05,610
和这登月计划帮了个忙 对吗?
and maybe tried it yourself. Right?

1214
01:11:05,610 --> 01:11:07,450
责怪国家航空航天局
Blame NASA.

1215
01:11:07,450 --> 01:11:08,620
责怪这个体系
Blame the system.

1216
01:11:09,450 --> 01:11:12,120
事关价值五亿美元的资金啊
I mean, there was half a billion dollars worth of funding on the line.

1217
01:11:12,120 --> 01:11:14,450
撒谎对你来说一定轻而易举吧 毕竟你总在撒谎
Lying must be so easy for you when you do it all the time.

1218
01:11:14,460 --> 01:11:15,660
撒谎总是一个可选项
It's just always an option.

1219
01:11:15,670 --> 01:11:18,210
你该试试说真话 你装什么清高呢?
What you should try is the truth. What is this sanctimonious bullshit?

1220
01:11:18,210 --> 01:11:20,880
我永远不会就那些人或那一天的事撒谎
I'm never going to lie about those men or that day.

1221
01:11:20,880 --> 01:11:22,010
你明白吗?
Do you understand that?

1222
01:11:22,960 --> 01:11:24,630
随便你怎么看我
You think what you want about me,

1223
01:11:24,630 --> 01:11:28,760
但因为不冷静 而让全人类登月梦破碎的人不是我
but I didn't cost the world a dream because I lost my goddamn cool.

1224
01:11:57,330 --> 01:12:02,500
这是34号发射场 发生阿波罗1号悲剧的地方
This is Launch Complex 34, where the Apollo 1 tragedy occurred.

1225
01:12:02,500 --> 01:12:05,210
这是牺牲英雄的纪念碑
This is a tribute to our fallen heroes,

1226
01:12:05,210 --> 01:12:08,800
这些勇敢的人为我们的成功铺平了道路
the brave men who paved the road to our success.

1227
01:12:09,840 --> 01:12:12,600
请大家为他们默哀片刻
Please, let's take a moment of silence for them.

1228
01:12:23,860 --> 01:12:25,190
爱德华 真令人称奇
Edvard, that looks incredible.

1229
01:12:25,190 --> 01:12:27,030
我完全看不到线缆 你怎么做到的?
I can't see the wires at all. How did you do that?

1230
01:12:27,030 --> 01:12:29,030
我只是用了一块遮光板 很简单
I just put a flag. It's very simple.

1231
01:12:29,030 --> 01:12:29,950
老办法了
Old school. Huh.

1232
01:12:29,950 --> 01:12:32,450
不行 从头再来
No. Again. From the top.

1233
01:12:32,450 --> 01:12:35,120
这次多加一些跳跃
And maybe let's get some more bounce this time.

1234
01:12:35,120 --> 01:12:36,450
你们可是在月球上啊
You are on the moon.

1235
01:12:37,750 --> 01:12:38,870
好
Good.

1236
01:12:43,420 --> 01:12:46,880
天啊 我看不下去了 今天不行
Oh, my God. I-I can't. I can't with this day.

1237
01:12:47,880 --> 01:12:50,800
天啊 好 坚持住 约瑟夫 失火了
Oh, dear. Uh... Okay, hold on. Joseph, there's a fire.

1238
01:12:50,800 --> 01:12:51,970
我来
I got it.

1239
01:12:52,600 --> 01:12:54,100
别忘记四步口诀
Don't forget to PASS.

1240
01:13:00,900 --> 01:13:03,730
好 能放他们下来吗? 算了 挂着吧
Okay. Can you bring them down? Actually, leave them up.

1241
01:13:04,230 --> 01:13:05,980
让他们反思一下自己都干了什么
Let them think about what they did.

1242
01:13:07,320 --> 01:13:09,950
我放弃了 我去吃午饭
I give up. I'm taking lunch.

1243
01:13:13,240 --> 01:13:16,330
你们明白自己干了什么吗? 你们让她提早去吃午饭了
You see what you did? You made her take lunch early.

1244
01:13:17,370 --> 01:13:18,620
这都怪你们
That's on you.

1245
01:13:30,010 --> 01:13:32,470
我跟你赌5美元 你不擅长道歉
I'll bet you $5 you're bad at apologies.

1246
01:13:32,470 --> 01:13:33,760
我到处找你
I've been looking all over for you.

1247
01:13:33,760 --> 01:13:35,350
你欠我5块 我有个想法
You owe me five bucks. I got an idea.

1248
01:13:35,350 --> 01:13:36,430
什么?
What?

1249
01:13:36,430 --> 01:13:38,270
来 去路易斯安那州的路上告诉你
Come on. I'll tell you on the way to Louisiana.

1250
01:13:38,890 --> 01:13:41,140
不 你想尝试获得范宁的投票?
No. You wanna take a shot at Vanning?

1251
01:13:41,980 --> 01:13:44,940
我给咱们弄到了晚餐邀请 就是今晚 走吧
I got us a dinner invite, for tonight. Come on.

1252
01:13:44,940 --> 01:13:46,980
今晚? 我们不可能赶得上 有800公里呢
Tonight? We're never gonna make it. It's 500 miles away.

1253
01:13:46,980 --> 01:13:49,070
我们能赶上 来 你得相信我
We're gonna make it. Come on. You gotta trust me.

1254
01:13:49,940 --> 01:13:50,990
等等 不
Oh, wait. No.

1255
01:13:50,990 --> 01:13:52,320
不行... 什么叫“不行”?
No, no, no. What do you mean, "no"?

1256
01:13:52,320 --> 01:13:54,700
我们不能... 有其他... 我们可以... 你想不想要范宁支持?
We don't... There's other... We could... Do you want Vanning or not?

1257
01:13:54,700 --> 01:13:56,660
我不... 来 我们走
Ugh. No. I don't... Come on. Let's go.

1258
01:13:56,660 --> 01:13:58,830
我觉得我们可以乘民航 如果我们出发...
I think we could just take a commercial flight. If we left...

1259
01:13:58,830 --> 01:14:00,750
不行 现在没有民航航班
Nope. No commercial flights are flying right now.

1260
01:14:00,750 --> 01:14:02,410
来 跳上来
Come on. Just hop on in.

1261
01:14:02,420 --> 01:14:05,130
就是这样 你只管上来就行 你可以跳上来的 你行的
This is it. This is all you gotta do. You can hop up, you can get in.

1262
01:14:05,130 --> 01:14:06,920
脚踩那里 好吧 拿着我的鞋
Put your foot there. Okay, well, take these.

1263
01:14:06,920 --> 01:14:08,380
听着 我们得走了 好
Look, we gotta go. All right.

1264
01:14:08,380 --> 01:14:09,880
等等...
Hold on. Hold on.

1265
01:14:12,130 --> 01:14:13,260
完美
Perfect.

1266
01:14:13,260 --> 01:14:15,680
等等 没问题
Hold on. We're good.

1267
01:14:25,900 --> 01:14:27,270
风景不错吧?
You enjoying the view?

1268
01:14:27,270 --> 01:14:28,690
天啊 太美了
Wow! It's stunning!

1269
01:14:29,610 --> 01:14:31,240
我打赌你闭着眼呢
I bet your eyes are closed.

1270
01:14:32,240 --> 01:14:33,240
没有
No.

1271
01:14:45,170 --> 01:14:46,960
我猜你还会些其他南方口音
So, I'm betting you have some other Southern accents

1272
01:14:46,960 --> 01:14:48,920
毕竟你“多才多艺” 会路易斯安那的吗?
in that bag of tricks of yours. Can you do Louisiana?

1273
01:14:48,920 --> 01:14:50,460
会 新奥尔良还是巴吞鲁日?
Yeah. New Orleans or Baton Rouge?

1274
01:14:50,460 --> 01:14:52,050
用他老婆家乡的 好
Wherever his wife's from. Okay.

1275
01:14:54,680 --> 01:14:56,010
科尔·戴维斯
Cole Davis.

1276
01:14:56,010 --> 01:14:57,890
你一定是凯莉·琼斯小姐
And you must be Miss Kelly Jones.

1277
01:14:57,890 --> 01:14:59,300
两位请进
Please come in, y'all. Oh.

1278
01:14:59,310 --> 01:15:00,890
非常感谢你们邀请我们吃晚餐
Thank you so much for having us for dinner.

1279
01:15:00,890 --> 01:15:04,480
好... 我听说你是纽约城里人
Oh, now... now, I was told you were a New York City type.

1280
01:15:04,480 --> 01:15:06,940
天啊 不是 我只是在那里工作 我是路易斯安那人
Oh, God, no. I just work there. I'm from Louisiana.

1281
01:15:06,940 --> 01:15:08,310
土生土长的 也会落叶归根
Born and raised and, one day, buried.

1282
01:15:08,310 --> 01:15:11,070
我老家在弗吉尼亚 不会吧? 我们是亲人啊
I'm from Virginia. No? We're family.

1283
01:15:11,070 --> 01:15:14,650
特克·斯里特尔总说 弗吉尼亚是得克萨斯的母亲
You know, Tex Ritter always said Virginia was the mother of Texas.

1284
01:15:14,650 --> 01:15:17,910
我们一直不知道父亲是谁 总怀疑是路易斯安那
Well, we never knew who the father was. We always suspected it was Louisiana.

1285
01:15:17,910 --> 01:15:19,910
我妈可喜欢这个笑话了
Oh! Huh? My mother loves that one.

1286
01:15:19,910 --> 01:15:22,080
是她想出来的 太有意思了
She was the one that came up with it. Oh, just so colorful.

1287
01:15:22,080 --> 01:15:25,210
你真有趣 你家可真漂亮
You're fun. This is a beautiful home.

1288
01:15:28,330 --> 01:15:31,130
参议员 竞选活动怎么样?
So, h-how is the campaign going, Senator?

1289
01:15:31,710 --> 01:15:35,340
说实话 政治更像是我的一项爱好
Truth be told, politics is more of a hobby to me.

1290
01:15:37,090 --> 01:15:40,310
服事基督才是我的全职工作
Serving Christ, that's my full-time job.

1291
01:15:41,930 --> 01:15:44,980
现在美国正有一场针对宗教的战争
You know, there's a war on religion in this country.

1292
01:15:45,480 --> 01:15:47,650
有人说要怪科学
And some say science is to blame.

1293
01:15:48,440 --> 01:15:50,560
是科学让我们今天齐聚一堂
Well, science is what brought us to this table.

1294
01:15:50,570 --> 01:15:53,190
你从阿波罗1号的事上学到了
You learned a little lesson on the provocation of pride

1295
01:15:53,190 --> 01:15:55,860
关于骄傲的一课 科尔 不是吗?
on Apollo 1, now, didn't you, Cole?

1296
01:15:56,950 --> 01:16:01,120
其实科学让我离上帝更近了 先生
Science has actually brought me closer to God, sir.

1297
01:16:01,660 --> 01:16:05,540
上帝用了六天创造了我们所知的一切
Took the Lord six days to put forth everything that we know as creation.

1298
01:16:05,540 --> 01:16:07,910
第六天 他把这些交给我们管理
And on that sixth day he gave us dominion over it.

1299
01:16:07,920 --> 01:16:10,920
我个人认为这是一种责任
And, personally, I take that as a responsibility.

1300
01:16:12,460 --> 01:16:15,420
你听起来很虔诚
You sound like a man who knows his way to church.

1301
01:16:15,420 --> 01:16:18,840
我觉得最能体现虔诚的方法
Well, I can't think of a greater act of faith

1302
01:16:18,840 --> 01:16:20,350
莫过于追逐星辰
than pursuing the stars.

1303
01:16:21,510 --> 01:16:25,980
“诸天述说上帝的荣耀 穹苍传扬他的作为”
"The heavens declare the glory of God. And the firmament shows us his handiwork."

1304
01:16:26,520 --> 01:16:29,140
这是乔琳娜最喜欢的诗篇句子之一
That's one of Jolene's favorite Psalms.

1305
01:16:29,150 --> 01:16:31,860
是这样 等我们的人从太空归来
You see, our men, when they come back from space,

1306
01:16:32,690 --> 01:16:34,610
他们对上帝的信仰会更多 不会减少
they believe more in God, not less.

1307
01:16:35,490 --> 01:16:37,490
但我们登月时
But when we land on the moon,

1308
01:16:37,490 --> 01:16:43,160
多亏了这位琼斯小姐 全球都能看到
and thanks to Miss Jones here, the world watches us do it.

1309
01:16:43,160 --> 01:16:47,620
我希望世界各地的人都能感受到 那种圣神的存在
And it's my hope that people everywhere feel the presence of that divine.

1310
01:16:50,830 --> 01:16:52,500
好吧
Well...

1311
01:16:53,630 --> 01:16:58,970
你的话确实得让我好好想想 小伙子
you've, uh, certainly given me a lot to think about, son.

1312
01:17:07,640 --> 01:17:09,850
你这推销还真有说服力啊
You really sold the hell out of that.

1313
01:17:09,850 --> 01:17:11,350
我没在推销
I wasn't selling.

1314
01:17:12,980 --> 01:17:16,990
郑重声明 做真实的自己也能赢得人心
For the record, you can win people over just by being who you are.

1315
01:17:21,860 --> 01:17:24,870
我们现在不赶时间了 所以不必飞回去
You know, we're not in a rush, so we don't really have to fly home.

1316
01:17:24,870 --> 01:17:26,700
那可不算飞
Ooh. That wasn't flying.

1317
01:17:38,090 --> 01:17:39,800
拜托 睁开眼睛
Come on. Open your eyes.

1318
01:17:50,480 --> 01:17:51,770
相信我吗?
You trust me?

1319
01:17:54,900 --> 01:17:55,900
坐稳了
Hold tight.

1320
01:18:04,700 --> 01:18:07,370
现在才是最好玩的 滑下来就行
Now, this is the fun part. Just slide off.

1321
01:18:12,370 --> 01:18:13,540
完美
Perfect.

1322
01:18:59,750 --> 01:19:05,430
我过去对国家航空航天局的计划 有过诸多意见不一致的地方
I've had my disagreements with the NASA program in the past.

1323
01:19:05,430 --> 01:19:09,680
但经过深思熟虑和反覆祈祷后
But after a great deal of thought, and prayer,

1324
01:19:10,970 --> 01:19:12,770
我决定投赞成票
I've decided to vote yes.

1325
01:19:15,480 --> 01:19:17,650
好样的
Come on.

1326
01:19:20,110 --> 01:19:21,940
我有样东西 你一定得看看
I have something that you need to see.

1327
01:19:22,490 --> 01:19:23,570
什么... 跟我来
What... Follow me.

1328
01:19:23,570 --> 01:19:25,900
我之前不知道结果会如何
Whoo! I didn't know which way it was gonna go,

1329
01:19:25,910 --> 01:19:28,120
因为你根本看不透政客
'cause you can't tell with these guys.

1330
01:19:28,120 --> 01:19:31,080
我之前向来不喜欢这家伙
I never liked that guy before, but...

1331
01:19:31,080 --> 01:19:33,700
但我现在喜欢他了
I like him now.

1332
01:19:33,710 --> 01:19:34,960
太好了
All right!

1333
01:19:34,960 --> 01:19:37,120
这里好黑啊 你... 快到了
It's so dark in here. You... Almost there.

1334
01:19:37,130 --> 01:19:39,840
我有点害怕 好了 就在这里
I'm a little scared. Yeah, it's right around here.

1335
01:19:39,840 --> 01:19:41,920
(对你的感谢有如登月往返)

1336
01:19:42,710 --> 01:19:44,510
我们想对你表达谢意
We wanted to show you our appreciation.

1337
01:19:45,510 --> 01:19:47,880
天啊 这也太隆重了 谢谢
Oh, my gosh. This is too much. Thank you.

1338
01:19:47,890 --> 01:19:49,930
不敢相信 都是沃尔特的功劳
I can't believe it. It was all Walter.

1339
01:19:49,930 --> 01:19:51,970
沃尔特? 我知道这都是你操办的 对吧?
Oh, Walter? I know that you did all of this, didn't you?

1340
01:19:51,970 --> 01:19:53,890
出了点力而已 是 我知道是你
A little. That's all. Yeah, I know you did.

1341
01:19:53,890 --> 01:19:55,480
大家都帮忙了 还不错吧?
They all helped. Not too bad, huh?

1342
01:20:11,490 --> 01:20:13,200
趁我还没忘 给
Before I forget. Here.

1343
01:20:13,950 --> 01:20:16,500
这上面列出了 登月后你迈出第一步时可以说的话
It's a list of things for you to say when you take your first step.

1344
01:20:16,500 --> 01:20:19,460
我... 知道所有人都在问你 就是想给你些点子
I... I know everybody's asking you. I thought I'd give you some options.

1345
01:20:20,250 --> 01:20:21,590
我本来想说
Well, I was just gonna say,

1346
01:20:21,590 --> 01:20:23,710
“看这些酷酷的石头”之类的话
"Look at all those cool rocks," or something.

1347
01:20:24,960 --> 01:20:26,340
我能搞定的 凯莉 好
I got this one, Kelly. Okay.

1348
01:20:27,340 --> 01:20:28,550
不过谢谢你
And thank you, though.

1349
01:20:28,550 --> 01:20:32,060
真心的 谢谢... 你所做的一切
And I mean it. For, uh... For everything.

1350
01:20:34,140 --> 01:20:38,600
我觉得没有人比科尔·戴维斯 更在乎这个计划
You know, I don't think anyone cares about this program more than Cole Davis.

1351
01:20:40,770 --> 01:20:43,480
很高兴看见他有其他在乎的东西了
It's nice to see he's found something else to care about.

1352
01:21:02,630 --> 01:21:06,420
我知道我不是宇航员 但我能请你跳一支舞吗?
I know I'm no, uh, astronaut, but can I steal you for a dance?

1353
01:21:07,550 --> 01:21:09,260
可以 可以? 来
Yes. Yes. Yeah? Come on.

1354
01:21:18,640 --> 01:21:22,150
你在数着日子 等待回到曼哈顿的那一天吗?
So, you just counting down the days until you, uh, can get back to Manhattan?

1355
01:21:22,690 --> 01:21:23,980
并没有
Not really.

1356
01:21:23,980 --> 01:21:25,150
很好
Good.

1357
01:21:45,000 --> 01:21:48,300
往上... 很好 好了 把灯搬过来
Up, up, up. Perfect. Right, now, move the light in.

1358
01:21:48,300 --> 01:21:50,340
好 继续 别害羞
All right, keep going. Don't be shy.

1359
01:21:50,340 --> 01:21:53,430
继续...
Keep going. Keep going. Keep going. Keep going. Keep going.

1360
01:21:54,890 --> 01:21:57,060
充分利用 很好
Milk it. Good. Mm-hmm.

1361
01:21:58,680 --> 01:22:00,930
女士们 觉得如何?
Ladies, what do we think?

1362
01:22:00,940 --> 01:22:03,400
兰斯 太惊人了 很棒
Lance, it's incredible. It's great.

1363
01:22:03,400 --> 01:22:07,270
我觉得还需要再来点尘土和更好的演员
I think it needs a little more dust and better actors,

1364
01:22:07,280 --> 01:22:09,150
但我的要求被拒了
but I lost that battle.

1365
01:22:09,940 --> 01:22:10,990
我也就不纠结了
I will let it go.

1366
01:22:12,030 --> 01:22:14,450
停 好
And, stop. Okay.

1367
01:22:14,990 --> 01:22:16,160
我们有太阳了
We've got our sun.

1368
01:22:16,910 --> 01:22:19,040
我总是配合你编造的那些谎言
I always went along with every web you spun

1369
01:22:19,040 --> 01:22:23,080
要么是因为它们很有趣 要么我们是在骗坏人
because it was fun or, like, we were pulling one over on the bad guys,

1370
01:22:23,080 --> 01:22:25,130
但这次的感觉...
but this feels...

1371
01:22:25,130 --> 01:22:26,290
我知道
I know.

1372
01:22:28,000 --> 01:22:29,090
就快完工了
We're almost done.

1373
01:22:34,470 --> 01:22:35,760
这是我送你的
This is from me.

1374
01:22:35,760 --> 01:22:37,510
发射日礼物
It is for launch day.

1375
01:22:38,010 --> 01:22:40,720
答应我 到时候再拆
Promise you will wait until then.

1376
01:22:40,730 --> 01:22:42,140
我答应 好
I promise. Okay.

1377
01:22:44,770 --> 01:22:46,520
记住 你们不是怪兽
Remember, you're not monsters.

1378
01:22:48,190 --> 01:22:49,820
会跳那么高吗?
Are they gonna be that high?

1379
01:22:50,440 --> 01:22:52,690
我只需要让他们的跳跃距离
Uh, I just need to give them any length

1380
01:22:52,700 --> 01:22:55,700
看起来像在月球上即可 但谢谢你的意见
that looks like they're on the moon. But thank you for the note.

1381
01:22:55,700 --> 01:22:57,200
巴兹 动作幅度小一点
Buzz, take it down some.

1382
01:22:57,830 --> 01:22:59,990
阿姆斯特朗 不要看我寻求肯定
And, Armstrong, stop looking at me for approval.

1383
01:22:59,990 --> 01:23:03,660
专心演好身处月球 把我当空气 他排练得很开心...
Just be on the moon. I'm not here. He's having fun. He's having fun.

1384
01:23:03,670 --> 01:23:06,670
他总是和我四目相交 别暗送秋波了 专心演身处月球
He keeps locking eyes with me. Stop flirting and be on the moon.

1385
01:23:15,800 --> 01:23:18,850
昨天的科幻小说成为了今天的现实
Yesterday's science fiction is today's fact.

1386
01:23:18,850 --> 01:23:20,260
方法虽然不同
The methods are different,

1387
01:23:20,260 --> 01:23:22,810
但重要的是明天一早
but the important thing is that tomorrow morning,

1388
01:23:22,810 --> 01:23:25,230
人类将飞向月球
man will lift off toward the moon.

1389
01:23:37,820 --> 01:23:40,240
晚上好 我是沃尔特·克朗凯特
Good evening. I'm Walter Cronkite.

1390
01:23:40,240 --> 01:23:44,250
在人类首次登月之旅的前夕
And on this eve of man's first flight toward a landing on the moon,

1391
01:23:44,250 --> 01:23:46,790
所有的准备工作都很顺利
all preparations go smoothly.

1392
01:23:46,790 --> 01:23:48,210
天气预报状况良好
The weather prediction,

1393
01:23:48,210 --> 01:23:51,050
还有宇航员们的帮助 尼尔 阿姆...
along with the health of astronauts, Neil Arm...

1394
01:24:20,200 --> 01:24:21,370
怎么了?
Yes?

1395
01:24:30,750 --> 01:24:34,380
你很会伤人心啊
Well, you know how to hurt a fella.

1396
01:24:35,210 --> 01:24:36,550
礼貌性的电话都不打一个?
No courtesy call?

1397
01:24:36,550 --> 01:24:38,260
我没有你的电话号码
Well, I don't have your number.

1398
01:24:38,260 --> 01:24:39,390
你逃跑了
You ran.

1399
01:24:40,930 --> 01:24:42,560
这是你最擅长的事
That's what you do best.

1400
01:24:43,350 --> 01:24:46,100
你这个备用版本的登月是个错误 我原本就不该参与
Your alternate version is wrong. I never should've been a part of it.

1401
01:24:46,100 --> 01:24:47,230
我不干了
I quit.

1402
01:24:47,980 --> 01:24:48,980
坐
Sit.

1403
01:24:57,700 --> 01:24:59,570
今天你要扮演谁呢?
So, who are we gonna be today?

1404
01:25:00,660 --> 01:25:01,910
我来看看
Let's see.

1405
01:25:02,740 --> 01:25:03,990
(目的地 希思罗机场)

1406
01:25:04,080 --> 01:25:06,370
海伦·帕克
Ooh, Helen Parker.

1407
01:25:06,910 --> 01:25:09,210
我打赌 你的英国口音一定很纯正
I bet you do a killer British accent.

1408
01:25:10,250 --> 01:25:13,460
你想一走了之 去当海伦? 请便
You wanna take off and be Helen? Go ahead.

1409
01:25:15,630 --> 01:25:18,510
海伦不必提心吊胆地生活
Helen doesn't have to look over her shoulder.

1410
01:25:19,010 --> 01:25:20,470
没有人会来找你的
No one is coming for you.

1411
01:25:22,300 --> 01:25:23,300
除非呢?
Unless?

1412
01:25:23,300 --> 01:25:28,140
除非你向任何人透露 阿尔忒弥斯计划真实存在
Unless you ever tell anyone that Project Artemis was real,

1413
01:25:28,140 --> 01:25:31,060
登月是虚假拍摄的
and the moon landing was fake.

1414
01:25:31,060 --> 01:25:34,900
说到这个 计划有变
Oh, on that score, change of plans.

1415
01:25:37,240 --> 01:25:39,610
我们会播出备用版本的登月
we're going to air the alternate version.

1416
01:25:39,610 --> 01:25:40,740
无论如何都播
No matter what.

1417
01:25:40,740 --> 01:25:42,910
你们从来没打算播出真实的登月
Oh, you were never gonna broadcast the real thing.

1418
01:25:42,910 --> 01:25:44,910
这不光是登月竞赛
This isn't just a race for the moon.

1419
01:25:44,910 --> 01:25:50,120
而是哪一种意识形态说了算的竞赛
It is a race for which ideology gets to run things.

1420
01:25:50,920 --> 01:25:55,380
我让一个手下改装了登月舱摄像机 让它只传回声音
I got one of my men to rig the LEM camera so that it just beams back audio.

1421
01:25:55,380 --> 01:26:00,670
我们会把他们的声音同步到你的假舞台上
We're gonna sync with their sound and, uh, use your fake stage broadcast,

1422
01:26:00,680 --> 01:26:02,590
从头到尾播出
start to finish.

1423
01:26:03,090 --> 01:26:07,720
让我第一个代表美国感谢你
Let me be the first to thank you on behalf of America.

1424
01:26:11,230 --> 01:26:15,150
好了 别难过 人人都能得到想要的结果
Come on, don't feel bad. Everybody gets what they want.

1425
01:26:16,230 --> 01:26:19,780
你可以展开新生活 不必再逃避过往
You get a new life with no past to run from.

1426
01:26:19,780 --> 01:26:25,030
全世界也不必在共产主义的月光下入眠
And the world doesn't have to sleep under a communist moon.

1427
