1444
01:28:48,720 --> 01:28:49,800
你怎么来了?
What are you doing here?

1445
01:28:53,310 --> 01:28:54,680
我得给你看一样东西
I need to show you something.

1446
01:28:57,310 --> 01:28:59,770
这本来是个应急计划
It was supposed to be a contingency plan.

1447
01:28:59,770 --> 01:29:02,270
他是这样说服我的 就是个保险措施
That's how he sold it. It was an insurance policy.

1448
01:29:02,270 --> 01:29:03,480
以防我们失败
In case we failed.

1449
01:29:06,070 --> 01:29:07,150
知道了也好
It's good to know...

1450
01:29:07,700 --> 01:29:09,410
你从来没相信过我们
that you never believed in us.

1451
01:29:09,910 --> 01:29:10,990
我知道你很难过
I know you're upset.

1452
01:29:10,990 --> 01:29:12,740
我理解 你理解什么?
I understand... Oh, what do you understand?

1453
01:29:12,740 --> 01:29:14,740
请告诉我你理解什么
Please tell me what you understand.

1454
01:29:14,740 --> 01:29:16,620
因为你对真相一点都不理解
'Cause you don't understand shit about truth.

1455
01:29:16,620 --> 01:29:18,660
如果你伪造这次任务...
If you fake this mission... If you fake this mission,

1456
01:29:18,670 --> 01:29:22,170
那我们之前做出的每一次牺牲全都白费了
every single thing that we have sacrificed will have been for nothing.

1457
01:29:23,170 --> 01:29:25,510
我知道我搞砸了 我知道
I know I messed up. I know that.

1458
01:29:26,550 --> 01:29:28,840
但你心里清楚 如果没有我 你们根本走不到今天
But you know you couldn't have made it to this day without me.

1459
01:29:28,840 --> 01:29:31,340
我昨晚大可一走了之 但我没有
I could've walked away last night, but I didn't.

1460
01:29:31,340 --> 01:29:35,060
我回来是为了弥补这个错误
I came back to fix this.

1461
01:29:37,180 --> 01:29:38,310
弥补什么?
Fix what?

1462
01:29:39,390 --> 01:29:41,940
莫切断了登月舱的画面 如果我们不一起修好它
Moe cut the LEM camera, and if we don't fix this together

1463
01:29:41,940 --> 01:29:44,060
那全世界看到的将会是这个版本
then this is gonna be the version that the world sees.

1464
01:29:48,820 --> 01:29:50,410
这不是应急计划
It's not a contingency.

1465
01:29:53,950 --> 01:29:56,080
天啊 你总能让我别无选择
God, you're so good at leaving me no options.

1466
01:30:01,540 --> 01:30:03,880
好吧 我们去修好它
Fine, let's fix it.

1467
01:30:03,880 --> 01:30:07,510
但等这事结束 我再也不想看到你
But when this is over, I never wanna see your face again.

1468
01:30:21,770 --> 01:30:24,310
为理查德·尼克松做事就是这种下场
This is what happens when you work for Richard Nixon.

1469
01:30:27,650 --> 01:30:28,780
我看了你的素描本 露比
I got your book, Ruby.

1470
01:30:29,530 --> 01:30:30,570
你提早拆开了
You opened it early.

1471
01:30:31,320 --> 01:30:32,740
拆得正是时候
It came at just the right time.

1472
01:30:41,250 --> 01:30:43,500
适合发射的大气层
Proper atmosphere for launch

1473
01:30:43,500 --> 01:30:47,090
是氧气和氮气的混合物
which is a combination of oxygen and nitrogen.

1474
01:30:47,090 --> 01:30:50,920
60%的氧气和40%氮气的大气层
Sixty percent oxygen and 40% nitrogen atmosphere.

1475
01:30:50,920 --> 01:30:53,800
当然 宇航员们呼吸的是
Of course, the astronauts themselves are breathing pure oxygen

1476
01:30:53,800 --> 01:30:55,760
太空服提供的纯氧
through their space suits.

1477
01:30:57,140 --> 01:30:59,350
很快将进行另一次关键测试
Coming up shortly will be another key test

1478
01:30:59,350 --> 01:31:02,060
届时发射组...
in which both the, uh, launch crew for the...

1479
01:31:02,060 --> 01:31:04,690
发射载具组员和飞船乘组
the launch vehicle crew and the spacecraft team,

1480
01:31:04,690 --> 01:31:08,520
会和指挥官尼尔·阿姆斯特朗一起
uh, combine together with the commander, Neil Armstrong,

1481
01:31:08,520 --> 01:31:11,360
彻查紧急情况检测系统
to make a thorough check of the Emergency Detection System.

1482
01:31:11,360 --> 01:31:12,490
这就是该系统...
This is the system...

1483
01:31:12,490 --> 01:31:15,320
我们正在卡纳维拉尔角直播 这创造历史的一天天气晴好
We're live from the Cape, where it's a beautiful day to make history.

1484
01:31:15,320 --> 01:31:17,820
我们将在这里为大家直播发射的部分
We'll be handling the launch portion of the broadcast from here,

1485
01:31:17,830 --> 01:31:19,450
我们在休斯敦的同行
and our counterparts in Houston

1486
01:31:19,450 --> 01:31:21,750
将报道任务控制中心引导的
will be covering Apollo 11's historic flight,

1487
01:31:21,750 --> 01:31:23,040
阿波罗11号历史性的航程
guided by Mission Control.

1488
01:31:30,550 --> 01:31:31,590
各位
Guys!

1489
01:31:31,590 --> 01:31:33,420
坏了
It's busted.

1490
01:31:33,930 --> 01:31:35,340
摄像机的视频前置放大器
The camera's video preamplifier.

1491
01:31:35,340 --> 01:31:36,890
坏掉了 好吧 你能修好吗?
It's destroyed. Okay, can you fix that?

1492
01:31:36,890 --> 01:31:38,720
我也许能从电视上拆一个改装 但...
I could maybe repurpose a part from a TV, but...

1493
01:31:38,720 --> 01:31:40,640
好啊 这里有很多电视
Well, that's fine. There's plenty of TVs around here.

1494
01:31:40,640 --> 01:31:42,220
航天局的电视都太老旧了
NASA's TVs... They are all too old.

1495
01:31:42,230 --> 01:31:44,940
我要一台全新的晶体管彩色电视
I mean a brand-new solid-state color TV.

1496
01:31:44,940 --> 01:31:46,480
你多快能弄到一台?
Well, how fast can you get one?

1497
01:31:47,060 --> 01:31:48,690
你送我去电器商店最快要多久?
How fast can you get me to an electronics store?

1498
01:31:48,690 --> 01:31:50,690
我? 现在佛罗里达交通空前拥堵
Me? In the worst traffic in Florida history.

1499
01:31:50,690 --> 01:31:51,940
走不开 得给大家做准备
I can't. I have to prep the guys.

1500
01:31:51,940 --> 01:31:53,400
把钥匙给我
Give me the keys.

1501
01:31:54,780 --> 01:31:55,950
好吧 我来拖延
Fine, I'll stall.

1502
01:31:55,950 --> 01:31:57,950
快点 去吧...
Hurry. Go, go, go, go, go, go, go.

1503
01:32:03,620 --> 01:32:05,160
所有酒店全部爆满
Hotels are at capacity.

1504
01:32:05,160 --> 01:32:07,210
肯尼迪航天中心人满为患
Kennedy Space Center is so crowded,

1505
01:32:07,210 --> 01:32:09,920
我们听说进出几乎不可能
we're hearing it's nearly impossible to get in or out.

1506
01:32:14,380 --> 01:32:15,800
凯莉 开慢点
Kelly, slow down.

1507
01:32:15,800 --> 01:32:17,090
后面两位还好吗?
Are you guys good back there?

1508
01:32:17,090 --> 01:32:18,180
很好 不好
Yes. No.

1509
01:32:20,600 --> 01:32:22,220
请别这样...
Please, please stop. Please stop.

1510
01:32:26,600 --> 01:32:28,440
到了 就是这家店
There it is. There's the store.

1511
01:32:42,870 --> 01:32:44,500
不 关门了
No! They're closed.

1512
01:32:46,210 --> 01:32:47,660
关门了 什么?
They're closed. Oh, what?

1513
01:32:47,670 --> 01:32:49,040
不... 没关门
No, no. No, they are not.

1514
01:32:49,040 --> 01:32:51,040
凯莉
Kelly. Whoa, whoa, whoa. Whoa!

1515
01:32:52,210 --> 01:32:53,550
你们还等什么呢? 快去
What are you waiting for? Go!

1516
01:32:53,550 --> 01:32:55,130
是... 好
Oh. Yeah, yeah. Okay.

1517
01:32:56,090 --> 01:32:57,090
好
Okay.

1518
01:32:59,180 --> 01:33:00,260
好
Okay, um...

1519
01:33:00,260 --> 01:33:01,850
对 这一台 很好 对 好
Yes, this one. This is great. Yeah, okay.

1520
01:33:01,850 --> 01:33:04,560
我很想帮忙 只是我不够高 来吧 唐 好
I would help. I'm just not tall enough. Come on, Don. All right.

1521
01:33:05,310 --> 01:33:08,060
好 慢点 好的 各位 快点
All right. Slowly, all right. Guys, come on.

1522
01:33:10,400 --> 01:33:12,070
天啊 我可不能蹲监狱
Oh, my God. I can't go to jail.

1523
01:33:12,940 --> 01:33:14,280
交给我
Let me handle this.

1524
01:33:12,940 --> 01:33:14,280
(警察)

1525
01:33:27,660 --> 01:33:28,750
她真厉害
She's good.

1526
01:33:29,580 --> 01:33:30,670
是啊
Yeah.

1527
01:34:14,710 --> 01:34:16,170
一路顺风 兄弟们
Have a good ride, boys.

1528
01:34:21,220 --> 01:34:23,550
大约五分钟后
In a matter of, uh, five minutes or so

1529
01:34:23,550 --> 01:34:26,430
我们将看到飞船指挥官尼尔·阿姆斯特朗
we'll be ready for the spacecraft commander, Neil Armstrong,

1530
01:34:26,430 --> 01:34:29,730
跨过位于98米高空的舷门门槛
to come across the sill at the 320-foot level.

1531
01:34:45,490 --> 01:34:47,370
搭乘穿梭面包车... 快啊
The trip in the transfer van... Come on!

1532
01:34:47,370 --> 01:34:50,330
大约要15分钟才能抵达发射平台
Could take some 15 minutes or so to reach the pad.

1533
01:34:50,330 --> 01:34:54,460
届时 宇航员将搭乘 两部电梯中先来的那部
At which time the astronauts will board, uh, the first of two elevators

1534
01:34:54,460 --> 01:34:58,800
前往发射平台所在的98米高空
for the trip to the 320-foot level at the launchpad,

1535
01:34:58,800 --> 01:35:02,380
然后进入飞船
uh, where they will then proceed to ingress the spacecraft.

1536
01:35:06,510 --> 01:35:07,970
站住 已经准备就绪了 小伙子
Whoa. We are locked and loaded, kid.

1537
01:35:07,970 --> 01:35:09,810
不... 飞行部要把这个放进飞船
No, no. Flight Deck wants this on the ship.

1538
01:35:13,440 --> 01:35:15,440
这里飞行部 放他过去 好
This is Flight Deck. Let him through. Got it.

1539
01:35:15,440 --> 01:35:16,440
去吧
Go.

1540
01:35:19,480 --> 01:35:21,990
好 我们必须启动发射前的程序了 否则会错过窗口期
Okay, we need to initiate prelaunch, or we lose the window.

1541
01:35:21,990 --> 01:35:23,030
给他一分钟就好
Just give him one minute.

1542
01:35:23,030 --> 01:35:24,610
... 98米的高空
320-foot level,

1543
01:35:24,610 --> 01:35:27,450
三位宇航员都已登上飞船
all three astronauts now aboard the spacecraft.

1544
01:35:27,450 --> 01:35:30,870
几分钟前 宇航员巴兹·奥尔德林 进来坐在了中间的位置
A few minutes ago, Astronaut Buzz Aldrin, uh, came in and took the center seat...

1545
01:35:30,870 --> 01:35:35,460
我听说船舱已经封闭 倒计时开始了
I'm hearing the cabin's now being sealed. Countdown has begun.

1546
01:35:35,460 --> 01:35:38,540
这是他们发射时的姿态
These are the positions they will fly at liftoff.

1547
01:35:39,210 --> 01:35:41,210
指挥官 这里是飞船测试员 听得清楚吗?
CDR, STC, how do you read?

1548
01:35:41,210 --> 01:35:43,090
飞船测试员 听得很清楚
STC, loud and clear.

1549
01:35:43,090 --> 01:35:45,340
早上好 尼尔 发射架已撤开
Good morning, Neil. Gantry is cleared.

1550
01:35:45,340 --> 01:35:46,510
欢迎登船
Welcome aboard.

1551
01:35:46,510 --> 01:35:49,890
阿波罗11号准备发射 倒计时十分钟
Apollo 11 is a go for launch in T-minus ten minutes.

1552
01:35:50,600 --> 01:35:51,720
好
Okay.

1553
01:35:55,810 --> 01:35:56,810
他回来了
He's here.

1554
01:35:57,900 --> 01:35:58,980
接上了
It's connected.

1555
01:35:58,980 --> 01:36:01,280
至少我认为接上了
At least I think I connected it.

1556
01:36:01,820 --> 01:36:04,320
斯图 什么意思?
Stu, what the hell does that mean?

1557
01:36:04,860 --> 01:36:07,950
我只有几秒钟时间 没来得及进行压力测试 我...
I only had a few seconds. I didn't have time to stress test it. I...

1558
