飞船要抵达...
And, uh, the, uh, spacecraft to reach there...

1595
01:40:14,530 --> 01:40:16,070
凯莉全都告诉我了
Kelly told me everything.

1596
01:40:19,780 --> 01:40:21,370
好极了
Bravissimo.

1597
01:40:21,370 --> 01:40:23,120
省省吧 这是创造历史
Shove it. That was history.

1598
01:40:23,120 --> 01:40:25,370
嗨 海伦 抱歉 是凯莉
Hi, Helen. Uh, sorry, Kelly.

1599
01:40:25,370 --> 01:40:28,790
我听说你回来了 所以我也回来了
I heard you came back, so I came back too.

1600
01:40:30,670 --> 01:40:34,720
我... 去月球片场看了一眼
I... I took a little peeky-poo at the moon set,

1601
01:40:34,720 --> 01:40:37,510
真是完美
and it is perfection.

1602
01:40:38,010 --> 01:40:39,010
干得好
Great job.

1603
01:40:39,010 --> 01:40:42,220
如果你认为我会让你播出 这次任务的造假版本
If you think that I'm gonna let you broadcast some fake version of this,

1604
01:40:42,220 --> 01:40:43,720
那我现在就去找媒体
I'll go to the press right now.

1605
01:40:43,730 --> 01:40:45,730
科尔
Cole.

1606
01:40:46,440 --> 01:40:48,190
科尔...
Cole. Cole.

1607
01:40:52,190 --> 01:40:56,700
你... 去找媒体吧 带他们看看月球片场
You, uh... You go to the press. Bring 'em by the moon set,

1608
01:40:57,570 --> 01:41:02,530
但你要知道 今后再也不会有人相信国家航空航天局了
but just know that no one will ever trust the legitimacy of NASA again.

1609
01:41:02,540 --> 01:41:05,540
这是国家安全问题
This is a matter of national security.

1610
01:41:05,540 --> 01:41:08,790
本次直播必须在可控的情况下进行
This broadcast must take place in a controlled setting.

1611
01:41:08,790 --> 01:41:11,380
你应该最明白了
You of all people must understand that.

1612
01:41:12,210 --> 01:41:15,960
任务的重点已经不再是登月了
The mission isn't about landing on the moon anymore.

1613
01:41:15,970 --> 01:41:21,550
而是全世界在电视上观看美国战胜苏联
It is about the world watching America beat Russia on TV.

1614
01:41:27,850 --> 01:41:29,270
我得赶飞机
I got a flight to catch.

1615
01:41:31,650 --> 01:41:36,150
我会及时赶回来看登月直播的
I'll be back in time for the lunar broadcast.

1616
01:41:36,150 --> 01:41:37,650
我想在这里看
I thought I'd watch it here.

1617
01:41:38,490 --> 01:41:40,990
凯莉 和你一起在月球片场看
With you, Kelly. On the moon.

1618
01:41:49,040 --> 01:41:51,790
嘿 我们正在创造历史
Hey. We're making history.

1619
01:42:24,330 --> 01:42:26,040
你说我的那些话全都没错
Everything you said about me is true.

1620
01:42:26,700 --> 01:42:28,580
我是个骗子 一直都是
I'm a con artist, and I always have been.

1621
01:42:31,870 --> 01:42:33,460
我的真名甚至不是凯莉
My real name is not even Kelly.

1622
01:42:35,840 --> 01:42:38,380
那些我跟你讲的故事
All those stories that I told you

1623
01:42:38,380 --> 01:42:40,670
说我和我妈挨家挨户推销
about my mom and I selling products door-to-door,

1624
01:42:40,680 --> 01:42:41,800
那是真事
those were true.

1625
01:42:42,970 --> 01:42:44,140
但都是骗局
They were all scams.

1626
01:42:45,390 --> 01:42:47,720
我们开始只是小打小闹 之后越做越大
And we started out small, and then they got bigger.

1627
01:42:48,430 --> 01:42:51,350
大到涉及地产和保险什么的
Like real estate and insurance.

1628
01:42:51,350 --> 01:42:52,440
然后...
And...

1629
01:42:54,440 --> 01:42:58,860
我16岁那年 在北达科他州 有个人掏枪了
when I was 16, a guy in North Dakota pulled a gun

1630
01:42:58,860 --> 01:43:01,860
我妈比他更快掏出枪 把他打死了
and my mom pulled hers out first and she killed him.

1631
01:43:01,860 --> 01:43:04,910
她叫我逃跑 我照做了
And she told me to run and I did.

1632
01:43:05,530 --> 01:43:07,790
她进了监狱 我再也没见过她
And she went to prison and I never saw her again.

1633
01:43:11,960 --> 01:43:15,380
我伪造文件 用假名来找工作
And I forged documents and used fake names to get jobs.

1634
01:43:15,380 --> 01:43:19,380
我去纽约后发现了广告业
And when I went to New York, I found advertising.

1635
01:43:19,380 --> 01:43:23,970
就像我妈教我的骗局 但却合法
And that was like the scams that my mom taught me, but it was legal.

1636
01:43:27,390 --> 01:43:29,180
我骗了很多人
And I lied to so many people.

1637
01:43:30,350 --> 01:43:32,480
最糟糕的谎言是我对自己说的那些
The worst lies were the ones I told myself.

1638
01:43:33,560 --> 01:43:36,190
说所有人都在骗人 这只是一场大型游戏而已
That everybody does it. You know. It's just a big game.

1639
01:43:38,520 --> 01:43:40,150
但后来我来了这里
But then I came down here...

1640
01:43:43,450 --> 01:43:44,570
认识了你
I met you.

1641
01:43:50,240 --> 01:43:52,830
我了解到参与到真实事件中是什么感受
I learned what it was like to be a part of something real.

1642
01:43:56,670 --> 01:43:58,960
莫提出的条件是抹去我的黑历史
Moe offered me a way to erase my past.

1643
01:43:58,960 --> 01:44:00,800
我原以为那就是我想要的 但...
I thought that's what I wanted, but...

1644
01:44:04,380 --> 01:44:05,890
我不想再逃亡了
I don't wanna run anymore.

1645
01:44:14,020 --> 01:44:16,650
莫是个值得尊敬的对手 但他遇到旗鼓相当的人了
Moe is a worthy opponent, but he has met his match.

1646
01:44:20,820 --> 01:44:24,780
我保证这是我最后一次 用欺骗的手段来获取我想要的东西
I promise this is the last time I will trick anyone into getting what I want.

1647
01:44:26,280 --> 01:44:27,410
我保证
I promise.

1648
01:44:29,740 --> 01:44:31,620
你觉得不撒谎也能做到吗?
Do you think you can do it without lying?

1649
01:44:33,620 --> 01:44:35,620
绝对不行 好吧 我想也是
Absolutely not. Yeah, I didn't think so.

1650
01:44:41,250 --> 01:44:42,380
那你有什么计划?
So, what's the plan?

1651
01:44:45,300 --> 01:44:46,590
我们为什么在这里碰头?
Why are we meeting out here?

1652
01:44:47,180 --> 01:44:49,800
因为莫监听一切对话 这人就像个魔术师 无处不在
Because Moe bugs everything. The guy's like Houdini. He's everywhere.

1653
01:44:49,800 --> 01:44:52,720
好 莫不知道我们修好了登月舱摄像机
Okay, so, Moe doesn't know that we fixed the LEM camera.

1654
01:44:52,720 --> 01:44:54,180
我们就此来制定计划
We build a plan around that.

1655
01:44:54,180 --> 01:44:57,890
我们只需让他相信我们在直播假登月
All we have to do is convince him that we are broadcasting the fake moon landing,

1656
01:44:57,900 --> 01:45:00,020
而实际上我们在播真的
when in reality we're broadcasting the real one.

1657
01:45:00,690 --> 01:45:02,730
我们有没有办法给设备动手脚
Is there a way that we could rig the equipment

1658
01:45:02,730 --> 01:45:05,240
来播出真实的登月舱视频?
so that it actually sends out the real LEM video feed?

1659
01:45:06,240 --> 01:45:07,240
拜托 两位
Come on, boys.

1660
01:45:07,240 --> 01:45:09,700
你们连登月都搞定了 给我个假设理论啊
You figured out how to land on the moon. Give me a hypothetical.

1661
01:45:09,700 --> 01:45:13,580
好 假设的话 我们可以重新接线
Okay, um, hypothetically, we could rewire it.

1662
01:45:13,580 --> 01:45:16,250
让设备只接收任务控制中心的播出信号
So that it only picks up the broadcast signal from Mission Control.

1663
01:45:16,250 --> 01:45:18,250
好 然后和我们的信号同步 对
Sure, then sync it with our feed. Hmm. Right.

1664
01:45:24,170 --> 01:45:25,210
嘿 各位
Hey, fellas.

1665
01:45:26,050 --> 01:45:28,630
莫·伯克斯派这两位来测试播出信号
Moe Berkus sent these guys to test the broadcast feed.

1666
01:45:28,640 --> 01:45:31,300
莫... 伯克斯 对 莫·伯克斯...
Moe... Moe Berk... Yes. Moe Berk... Moe Berkus.

1667
01:45:32,390 --> 01:45:34,430
你们谁都没接到电话?
Telling me none of you got the phone call?

1668
01:45:35,100 --> 01:45:37,060
好极了 摄像机在哪?
Great. All right, where's the camera?

1669
01:45:41,230 --> 01:45:42,400
你还好吗?
Are you okay? Mmm.

1670
01:45:43,440 --> 01:45:44,860
请你们快点好吗?
Can you guys hurry up, please?

1671
01:45:45,940 --> 01:45:47,500
唐 你把烟掐了吧
Don, maybe just take the cigarette out.

1672
01:45:47,990 --> 01:45:50,910
抱歉... 我之前从没吸过烟
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I've just never smoked a cigarette before.

1673
01:45:52,120 --> 01:45:53,120
我不喜欢
I don't like it.

1674
01:45:55,450 --> 01:45:57,290
11号 这里是休斯敦
Uh, 11, this is Houston.

1675
01:45:57,290 --> 01:45:58,500
环月轨道进入就绪 完毕
Uh, you are go for LOI. Over.

1676
01:45:58,500 --> 01:46:00,250
确认 向月球前进
Confirmed. On track for the moon.

1677
01:46:00,250 --> 01:46:02,130
阿波罗11号 这里是休斯敦
Apollo 11, this is Houston.

1678
01:46:02,130 --> 01:46:04,590
你的全部系统正常 要转到月球后面了
All your systems are looking good. Going around the corner.

1679
01:46:04,590 --> 01:46:06,130
我们另一边见 完毕
We'll see you on the other side. Over.

1680
01:46:06,130 --> 01:46:08,050
我们失去了信号
And we've had loss of signal

1681
01:46:08,050 --> 01:46:10,550
因为阿波罗11号飞到了月球后面
as Apollo 11 goes behind the moon.

1682
01:46:11,180 --> 01:46:14,510
现在是东部夏令时下午3点半
It's now 3:30 Eastern Daylight Time.

1683
01:46:14,510 --> 01:46:18,680
3点46分时 我们应该能够收到 登月舱的第一个信号
At 3:46 we should be getting the first signal from the Lunar Module.

1684
01:46:18,690 --> 01:46:21,310
估计观众有上亿人
The estimated audience: hundreds of millions.

1685
01:46:21,310 --> 01:46:23,980
可能有四亿人
Perhaps 400 million persons or so are watching

1686
01:46:23,980 --> 01:46:27,820
正在观看这一重大事件的直播...
this broadcast today of, uh, the greatest event...

1687
01:46:27,820 --> 01:46:28,900
兄弟们
Boys.

1688
01:46:30,360 --> 01:46:31,740
好 开始吧
All right. Let's go.

1689
01:46:39,790 --> 01:46:42,580
再往下一点 很好 各位
A little bit more. Well done, guys.

1690
01:46:46,750 --> 01:46:50,300
伙计们 你们听到我说话 就当成是上帝的旨意
Boys, when you hear my voice, you hear God.

1691
01:46:50,800 --> 01:46:52,220
这是个假月球
Now, this is a fake moon,

1692
01:46:52,220 --> 01:46:54,090
但对于全世界 这是真的 好戏上演了
but to the world, it's real. It's showtime, folks.

1693
01:46:54,100 --> 01:46:55,640
必须... 记住我说到哪了
It needs to... Remember where I left off.

1694
01:46:55,640 --> 01:46:59,140
政府感谢你们即将付出的努力
Your government thanks you for the work you're about to do.

1695
01:47:00,060 --> 01:47:01,690
别搞砸了
Now, don't fuck it up.

1696
01:47:02,770 --> 01:47:04,980
这破烂饮料为什么放这里?
What is this nasty shit doing here?

1697
01:47:06,400 --> 01:47:08,400
天啊 不好意思
God. Excuse me.

1698
01:47:08,400 --> 01:47:10,900
这是本片场指定的汽水 这是我的椅子
This is a Tab set, and that is my chair.

1699
01:47:10,900 --> 01:47:13,280
凯莉 处理一下 兰斯 非常感谢
Kelly, let's deal with this. Lance, thank you so much.

1700
01:47:13,280 --> 01:47:15,320
这些屏幕是我们的信号
So, these screens... This is our feed.

1701
01:47:15,330 --> 01:47:17,950
好 然后...
Yeah. Okay. And then...

1702
01:47:18,790 --> 01:47:20,460
电视是直播画面 好
And the TV's a live broadcast. Okay.

1703
01:47:20,460 --> 01:47:21,790
(阿波罗11号 月球直播)

1704
01:47:22,420 --> 01:47:23,420
对
Right.

1705
01:47:23,920 --> 01:47:25,330
约瑟夫 我要坐下
Joseph, I'm sitting.

1706
01:47:25,340 --> 01:47:27,040
天啊 你认真的?
Oh, my God. Are you real?

1707
01:47:27,050 --> 01:47:29,130
我是导演 兰斯·瓦斯珀丁
I am the director, Lance Vespertine.

1708
01:47:31,920 --> 01:47:33,430
别碍事好吗?
Stay out of my way, will you?

1709
01:47:33,430 --> 01:47:36,140
好 我想说很高兴认识你 但到目前为止我不高兴
All right, I'd say it was nice to meet you, but so far, it is not.

1710
01:47:36,140 --> 01:47:37,890
鸽子已经进笼
The pigeon's in the coop.

1711
01:47:37,890 --> 01:47:39,100
收到
Copy that.

1712
01:47:42,390 --> 01:47:44,350
好 应该能收到了 休斯敦
Okay, you should have him now, Houston.

1713
01:47:44,850 --> 01:47:47,360
鹰号 我们有你的信号了 看起来不错 完毕
Eagle, we've got you now. It's looking good. Over.

1714
01:47:50,320 --> 01:47:53,360
我们从前窗就可以看到地球
We've got the Earth right out of our front window.

1715
01:47:53,360 --> 01:47:55,780
飞行指挥 我们准备着陆
Flight, we are go for landing.

1716
01:47:55,780 --> 01:47:58,490
收到 明白 准备着陆 910米
Roger. Understand. Go for landing. 3,000 feet.

1717
01:47:59,620 --> 01:48:01,540
鹰号 状态很好 可以开始着陆
Eagle, looking great. You're go.

1718
01:48:14,220 --> 01:48:17,970
位置检查显示 水平飞行距离有些过长
Position checks downrange show us to be a little long.

1719
01:48:17,970 --> 01:48:20,310
430米 状态依然很好
1,400 feet. Still looking very good.

1720
01:48:20,310 --> 01:48:23,230
P30 6加2.5
P30. Six plus two-five.

1721
01:48:23,230 --> 01:48:24,810
看起来大约250米
Looks like about 820.

1722
01:48:24,810 --> 01:48:26,350
降低引擎的功率
Throttle down.

1723
01:48:28,860 --> 01:48:30,610
飞行指挥 这里是鹰号
Flight, this is Eagle.

1724
01:48:31,110 --> 01:48:34,030
宁静海里的石头比预期中多
Sea of Tranquility is rockier than expected.

1725
01:48:34,740 --> 01:48:36,820
我们不得不再飞300米
We're gonna have to extend another thousand feet.

1726
01:48:36,820 --> 01:48:38,200
嘿 兄弟们
Hey, boys.

1727
01:48:40,490 --> 01:48:41,620
那样的话情况如何?
Where does that put us?

1728
01:48:41,620 --> 01:48:43,790
他们会剩下15秒的燃料 最好终止任务
It'll give 'em 15 seconds of fuel left. They're gonna wanna abort.

1729
01:48:43,790 --> 01:48:46,120
尼尔能做到 只要放手让他飞即可
Neil can do this, they just gotta let him.

1730
01:48:46,750 --> 01:48:48,420
待命 鹰号
Stand by, Eagle.

1731
01:48:46,750 --> 01:48:48,420
(燃料百分比)

1732
01:48:48,420 --> 01:48:51,000
我们正在计算延长飞行的耗油量
We are calculating what that will do to our fuel reserves.

1733
01:48:51,000 --> 01:48:55,170
电气 环境和耗材主管计算 是15秒以内 准备终止任务
EECOM puts that within 15 seconds. Prepare for abort.

1734
01:48:56,550 --> 01:48:57,880
飞行指挥
Flight...

1735
01:48:57,890 --> 01:49:01,260
我们曾在这个范围内 进行过成功测试 让他们着陆吧
we have run successful tests within that range. Let 'em land.

1736
01:49:03,980 --> 01:49:05,520
30秒...
Thirty. Thirty seconds.

1737
01:49:05,520 --> 01:49:07,230
这是骗人 你撒谎了
That's a lie. You lied.

1738
01:49:07,770 --> 01:49:09,440
我新学了几招 坐下
I've learned some new tricks. Sit down.

1739
01:49:09,440 --> 01:49:12,110
好 接下来只报告燃料数字
Okay, the only callouts from now on will be fuel.

1740
01:49:13,650 --> 01:49:14,690
加油啊
Come on.

1741
01:49:15,570 --> 01:49:17,450
鹰号 看起来不错 可以着陆
Eagle, looking great. You're go.

1742
01:49:17,990 --> 01:49:20,160
430米 状态依然很好
1,400 feet. Still looking very good.

1743
01:49:22,540 --> 01:49:24,450
107米 降速4
350 feet, down at four.

1744
01:49:25,200 --> 01:49:27,080
30秒...
Thirty. Thirty seconds.

1745
01:49:27,080 --> 01:49:28,710
降速2.5 前进
Down two and a half. Forward.

1746
01:49:29,250 --> 01:49:31,090
前进 好 收到
Forward. Good. Roger that.

1747
01:49:33,090 --> 01:49:34,840
前进速度11 正稳步下降
Eleven forward. Coming down nicely.

1748
01:49:34,840 --> 01:49:36,590
61米 降速4.5
200 feet, four and a half down.

1749
01:49:36,590 --> 01:49:39,300
降速5.5... 前进速度9
Five and a half down. Five and a half down, nine forward.

1750
01:49:39,300 --> 01:49:40,390
很好
That's good.

1751
01:49:52,820 --> 01:49:53,940
(月表接触)

1752
01:49:54,030 --> 01:49:55,110
接触灯亮了
Contact light.

1753
01:49:59,200 --> 01:50:00,490
关闭引擎
Engine stop.

1754
01:50:12,880 --> 01:50:14,000
飞行指挥
Flight.

1755
01:50:15,710 --> 01:50:17,340
这里是宁静海基地
Tranquility Base here.

1756
01:50:17,880 --> 01:50:19,380
鹰号已着陆
The Eagle has landed.

1757
01:50:26,100 --> 01:50:28,850
收到 宁静海基地 地面收到
Roger, Tranquility, we copy on the ground.

1758
01:50:28,850 --> 01:50:31,020
有一群人脸都快憋青了
You got a bunch of guys about to turn blue.

1759
01:50:31,020 --> 01:50:32,560
我们又能呼吸了 多谢
We're breathing again. Thanks a lot.

1760
01:50:39,360 --> 01:50:40,450
呼 老天
Whew. Boy.

1761
01:50:40,450 --> 01:50:42,200
我们要忙一会儿了
We're going to be busy for a minute.

1762
01:50:46,080 --> 01:50:47,950
好了... 可以了
All right, all right, all right. Come on.

1763
01:50:48,750 --> 01:50:51,370
集中注意力 还没完呢
Let's focus. We're only halfway there.

1764
01:50:52,710 --> 01:50:54,630
好 接下来交给我们 谢谢各位
Yeah, we've got it from here. Thank you, guys.

1765
01:50:54,630 --> 01:50:57,710
大家各就各位... 打起精神
Places. Places, everyone. Look sharp.

1766
01:50:57,710 --> 01:50:58,960
打起精神来
Let's look sharp!

1767
01:50:58,970 --> 01:51:01,260
爱德华... 走下舞台 真要命
Edvard, Edvard, off the stage. You're killing me.

1768
01:51:01,260 --> 01:51:05,180
爱德华 完事了 停 你完工了 别再调整了
Edvard, we are done. Uh-uh. You're done. No more tweaking.

1769
01:51:05,180 --> 01:51:07,510
你是复读机吗? 我不是复读机
What are you, the repeater? No, I'm not the repeater.

1770
01:51:07,520 --> 01:51:09,640
这是你来之前我们创立的系统
This is the system we created before you got here.

1771
01:51:16,820 --> 01:51:18,360
已取下摄像机
Camera is coming down.

1772
01:51:24,120 --> 01:51:25,120
(直播中)

1773
01:51:25,200 --> 01:51:29,830
三 二 一 开拍
Three, two, one, and action.

1774
01:51:32,620 --> 01:51:35,130
电视上有画面了
And we're getting a picture on the TV.

1775
01:51:36,130 --> 01:51:37,960
画面还不错吧?
You got a good picture, huh?

1776
01:51:37,960 --> 01:51:40,840
对比度很强烈
Uh, there's a great deal of contrast in it.

1777
01:51:40,840 --> 01:51:42,970
收到 电视电路断路器已接通
Roger, TV circuit breaker's in,

1778
01:51:44,220 --> 01:51:45,890
听得很清楚
and read you loud and clear.

1779
01:51:47,390 --> 01:51:48,600
收到
Roger.

1780
01:51:53,850 --> 01:51:56,520
好 请确认一下
Okay. Will you verify the position, uh,

1781
01:51:56,520 --> 01:51:58,570
摄像机镜头的位置和光圈尺寸
the, uh, opening I ought to have on the camera?

1782
01:51:58,570 --> 01:51:59,860
稍等
Stand by.

1783
01:51:59,860 --> 01:52:02,700
阿姆斯特朗 准备下飞船
Armstrong, prepare to disembark.

1784
01:52:04,070 --> 01:52:05,320
遮光面罩
Your visor.

1785
01:52:09,240 --> 01:52:11,250
我要打开舱门出去了
I am opening the door for egress.

1786
01:52:31,350 --> 01:52:34,020
好 尼尔 我们看到你正走下舷梯
Okay, Neil, we can see you coming down the ladder now.

1787
01:52:36,020 --> 01:52:37,940
好 左脚
Okay, left.

1788
01:52:39,650 --> 01:52:41,400
右脚
And right.

1789
01:52:43,780 --> 01:52:46,410
左脚 右脚
Left and right.

1790
01:52:46,410 --> 01:52:49,070
好 左脚下来...
Now, left foot off. Left foot off.

1791
01:52:49,080 --> 01:52:52,410
慢点... 下来
Easy. Easy. Step down.

1792
01:52:53,200 --> 01:52:55,870
落地
And land.

1793
01:52:55,870 --> 01:52:58,330
你怎么提前知道他要做什么?
How do you know what, uh, he's gonna do ahead of time?

1794
01:52:58,330 --> 01:53:02,050
国家航空航天局全都排练过 凯莉借鉴了一下
NASA rehearsed all of this, and Kelly appropriated it.

1795
01:53:02,920 --> 01:53:04,260
就是偷嘛
Oh, stole it.

1796
01:53:04,920 --> 01:53:06,550
我就知道我找对人了
I knew I hired the right people.

1797
01:53:07,930 --> 01:53:09,350
好 来吧
Okay, here we go.

1798
01:53:11,010 --> 01:53:12,720
(真实信号 播出信号)

1799
01:53:12,810 --> 01:53:14,810
天衣无缝 真难以置信
It's seamless. It's incredible.

1800
01:53:16,020 --> 01:53:18,100
我来到舷梯底部了
I'm at the foot of the ladder.

1801
01:53:18,600 --> 01:53:22,980
登月舱的支脚仅仅压进月球表面2到5厘米
The LEM footpads are only depressed in the surface about one or two inches,

1802
01:53:22,980 --> 01:53:28,610
不过靠近了看 月表的尘土似乎非常细腻
although the surface appears to be very, very fine-grained as you get close to it.

1803
01:53:28,610 --> 01:53:33,160
几乎就像粉末 下面的尘埃非常细
It's almost like a powder. Down there, it's very fine.

1804
01:53:34,500 --> 01:53:36,250
我要走下登月舱了
I'm gonna step off the LEM now.

1805
01:53:42,210 --> 01:53:44,800
这是个人的一小步
That's one small step for man...

1806
01:53:48,300 --> 01:53:51,720
却是人类的一大步
one giant leap for mankind.

1807
01:53:57,140 --> 01:53:59,540
这么精彩的话 我们可能得花好几年才想得出
We could have spent years coming up with something that good.

1808
01:54:00,690 --> 01:54:02,190
是的
Yeah.

1809
01:54:02,900 --> 01:54:05,570
这是剧本里的吗?
Was that, uh, in the script?

1810
01:54:05,570 --> 01:54:07,030
不是
No.

1811
01:54:08,360 --> 01:54:09,530
这句台词不错
That's a good line.

1812
01:54:14,540 --> 01:54:17,910
一级一级舷梯跳下来是很简单的
It's a very simple matter to hop down from one step to the next.

1813
01:54:18,410 --> 01:54:20,250
尼尔要展示牌匾了
Neil is now unveiling the plaque.

1814
01:54:21,380 --> 01:54:23,340
“地球的人类
"Here man, from the planet Earth,

1815
01:54:23,340 --> 01:54:28,470
于公元1969年7月首次踏上月球
first set foot upon the moon, July 1969 AD.

1816
01:54:28,470 --> 01:54:31,010
我们为全人类的和平而来”
We came in peace for all mankind."

1817
01:54:34,060 --> 01:54:35,890
准备好上镜了吗?
You ready for the camera?

1818
01:54:35,890 --> 01:54:39,310
尼尔 这里是休斯敦 视野正常
Uh, Neil, this is Houston. The field of view is okay.

1819
01:54:39,310 --> 01:54:42,020
我们希望你把摄像机对准右边一点 完毕
We'd like you to aim it a little bit more to the right. Over.

1820
01:54:42,520 --> 01:54:43,610
好
Okay.

1821
01:54:44,570 --> 01:54:46,110
太往右了
Too much to the right.

1822
01:54:46,110 --> 01:54:48,440
能往左4 5度吗?
Can you bring it back left about, uh, four or five degrees?

1823
01:54:53,620 --> 01:54:55,280
好 看起来不错 尼尔
Okay. That looks good, Neil.

1824
01:54:56,910 --> 01:54:59,410
哥伦比亚号... 这里是休斯敦 接收信号 完毕
Columbia, Columbia, this is Houston, AOS. Over.

1825
01:54:59,410 --> 01:55:01,920
尼尔阿姆斯特朗目前已经在月球表面
Neil Armstrong has been on the lunar surface now

1826
01:55:01,920 --> 01:55:03,040
停留近45分钟了
almost 45 minutes.

1827
01:55:03,580 --> 01:55:06,000
宁静海基地 这里是休斯敦
Uh, Tranquility Base, this is Houston.

1828
01:55:06,000 --> 01:55:08,460
请两位一起走进镜头一下好吗?
Could we get both of you on the camera for a minute, please?

1829
01:55:09,220 --> 01:55:13,260
美国总统想跟你们说几句 完毕
The President of the United States would like to say a few words to you. Over.

1830
01:55:13,260 --> 01:55:15,180
这是我们的荣幸
That would be an honor.

1831
01:55:15,680 --> 01:55:17,680
好 总统先生 请讲吧
All right, go ahead, Mr. President.

1832
01:55:17,680 --> 01:55:18,770
这里是休斯敦 完毕
This is Houston. Out.

1833
01:55:18,770 --> 01:55:20,560
你们好 尼尔和巴兹
Hello, Neil and Buzz.

1834
01:55:21,270 --> 01:55:25,560
我正在白宫的椭圆办公室 用电话跟你们通话
I am talking to you by telephone from the Oval Room at the White House...

1835
01:55:25,570 --> 01:55:27,730
这地方到处都是特勤局的人
They have Secret Service all over this place.

1836
01:55:27,730 --> 01:55:31,990
这绝对是有史以来最重要的一次通话
And this certainly has to be the most historic telephone call ever made.

1837
01:55:33,320 --> 01:55:34,950
你们跟我们通话的同时...
And as you talk to us...

1838
01:55:34,950 --> 01:55:37,450
我觉得你跟他真的很像
He actually reminds me a lot of you.

1839
01:55:37,450 --> 01:55:40,120
别这么说 真的 连玩笑都别开
Do not say that. No, don't even joke about that.

1840
01:55:40,710 --> 01:55:45,130
总统发表无聊讲话时我们要待命 别动
We're still holding while the president drones on. Don't move.

1841
01:55:45,130 --> 01:55:46,840
阿姆斯特朗 我主要盯着你
Armstrong, I'm watching you the most.

1842
01:55:46,840 --> 01:55:51,170
在这全人类史上无比珍贵的时刻...
For one priceless moment in the whole history of man...

1843
01:55:51,170 --> 01:55:52,760
肯尼迪航天中心 我们直接通话吧
Kennedy, let's go direct.

1844
01:55:55,220 --> 01:55:57,390
科尔 你收到画面了吗?
Cole, are you receiving picture?

1845
01:55:57,390 --> 01:55:59,180
这边的视频信号灯没亮
The video feed light isn't on up here.

1846
01:55:59,180 --> 01:56:02,350
尼尔 什么意思? 坏掉了?
Uh, what do you mean, Neil? It's not working?

1847
01:56:02,350 --> 01:56:04,400
那得你来告诉我 你能看到画面吗?
You tell me. Do you see picture?

1848
01:56:04,900 --> 01:56:07,310
我们的摄像机发出了电力过载警报
We're getting a power surge warning on the camera.

1849
01:56:07,320 --> 01:56:09,780
好像坏了 你还能看到我们吗?
I think it crapped out. Can you still see us?

1850
01:56:09,780 --> 01:56:11,780
能 还能看见
Yeah, I can still see you.

1851
01:56:13,610 --> 01:56:14,780
稍等 尼尔
Um, one second, Neil.

1852
01:56:15,280 --> 01:56:17,160
尼尔说月球上的视频信号灯没有亮
Neil's saying the video feed light isn't on up there.

1853
01:56:17,160 --> 01:56:18,490
你确定那台摄像机能用?
Are you sure that camera's working?

1854
01:56:18,490 --> 01:56:20,700
我安装了新零件 应该没问题的 但...
I installed the new part. It should be working just fine but...

1855
01:56:20,700 --> 01:56:23,120
但什么? 但我... 当时赶时间
But what? But I... I was in a rush.

1856
01:56:24,620 --> 01:56:25,710
见鬼
Shit.

1857
01:56:29,500 --> 01:56:30,500
怎么了?
What's wrong?

1858
01:56:30,510 --> 01:56:33,880
我们不确定登月舱上的 摄像机是否运作正常
We're not sure that the camera on the LEM is working.

1859
01:56:33,880 --> 01:56:36,510
我觉得播出的画面是你们的
I think that's your feed broadcasting.

1860
01:56:37,220 --> 01:56:40,140
电视上的画面和片场一样吗?
Does the feed on your TV look like your set?

1861
01:56:42,930 --> 01:56:44,810
我... 看不出是不是我们
I... I can't tell if it's us.

1862
01:56:44,810 --> 01:56:47,980
测试一下 让一个特工挥挥手什么的
Test it. Have one of your agents give a little wave or something.

1863
01:56:48,520 --> 01:56:51,440
不行 所有人都在这里
I can't. Everyone is here.

1864
01:57:08,630 --> 01:57:10,750
这是什么鬼? 我不知道
What the hell is that? I don't know.

1865
01:57:12,380 --> 01:57:14,010
他差5厘米就进镜头了
He is two inches away from being on that screen.

1866
01:57:14,010 --> 01:57:15,090
是... 2厘米
It's... It's one inch.

1867
01:57:15,090 --> 01:57:16,840
这也是你那该死的剧本里的情节?
Is that in your goddamn script?

1868
01:57:19,180 --> 01:57:20,680
约瑟夫 有新加的戏?
Joseph, were there new pages?

1869
01:57:20,680 --> 01:57:23,430
不仅代表美国
Representing not only the United States

1870
01:57:23,430 --> 01:57:25,690
也代表所有国家热爱和平的人
but men of peace of all nations...

1871
01:57:28,940 --> 01:57:32,650
是小淘气 天啊 猫咪...
Oh, Mischief! Oh, God. Kitty, kitty! Pss, kitty, kitty, kitty.

1872
01:57:32,650 --> 01:57:33,860
小淘气...
Mischief! Mischief!

1873
01:57:33,860 --> 01:57:35,320
你去哪?
Where are you going?

1874
01:57:36,280 --> 01:57:37,860
小淘气... 凯莉
Mischief. Mischief. K... Kelly.

1875
01:57:37,860 --> 01:57:39,410
过来 那只猫?
Come here. The cat?

1876
01:57:39,410 --> 01:57:40,830
过来...
Come here. Come here. Come here.

1877
01:57:49,330 --> 01:57:51,090
你认识这只猫?
Do you know this cat?

1878
01:57:52,920 --> 01:57:54,050
猫咪...
Kitty, kitty, kitty!

1879
01:57:54,050 --> 01:57:56,880
过来 小宝... 过来 你个小混蛋
Come here, you sweet... Come here, you little bitch.

1880
01:57:56,880 --> 01:57:58,430
猫咪...
Kitty, kitty, kitty.

1881
01:57:58,430 --> 01:58:00,050
给我过来 不
Come here, you! No!

1882
01:58:02,260 --> 01:58:05,180
凯莉 你那边到底怎么了?
Kelly, what the hell is going on over there?

1883
01:58:05,180 --> 01:58:06,480
凯莉?
Kelly? Kelly?

1884
01:58:06,480 --> 01:58:09,020
绕到后面去
Go round the back!

1885
01:58:09,020 --> 01:58:10,730
小淘气...
Mischief! Mischief!

1886
01:58:12,070 --> 01:58:13,110
猫咪...
Kitty, kitty, kitty!

1887
01:58:13,110 --> 01:58:15,280
抓住它... 快...
Catch him! Catch him! Oh! Go, go.

1888
01:58:15,280 --> 01:58:16,530
我们走 快
Let's go! Come on.

1889
01:58:19,110 --> 01:58:20,990
来 没事的
Come here. It's okay.

1890
01:58:20,990 --> 01:58:22,820
小淘气 过来吧
Mischief. Just come here.

1891
01:58:22,830 --> 01:58:24,240
闭嘴...
Just shut up. Just shut up!

1892
01:58:24,240 --> 01:58:27,330
过来 猫咪... 过来 小宝宝 你认识我的
Come here, kitty, kitty, kitty. Come here, little baby. You know me.

1893
01:58:28,670 --> 01:58:29,920
不
No!

1894
01:58:44,260 --> 01:58:45,850
非常感谢
And thank you very much

1895
01:58:45,850 --> 01:58:47,770
我很期待 我们都很期待
and I look forward, all of us look forward,

1896
01:58:47,770 --> 01:58:49,850
星期四在大黄蜂号上见到你们
to seeing you on the Hornet on Thursday.

1897
01:58:53,480 --> 01:58:55,480
我也很期待 先生
I look forward to that very much, sir.

1898
01:58:58,740 --> 01:58:59,990
播出的是你的人 科尔
Those are your guys, Cole.

1899
01:59:00,530 --> 01:59:02,660
太好了 是我们的人
Yes! Those are our guys!

1900
01:59:06,700 --> 01:59:08,500
对 我知道你们都知道
Yes. I know you know that.

1901
01:59:08,500 --> 01:59:10,790
就是提醒一下大家我们今天在干什么
Just reminding everybody what we're doing here today.

1902
01:59:11,790 --> 01:59:12,960
那是我们的人
Those are our guys.

1903
01:59:13,960 --> 01:59:15,040
大家继续忙吧
Carry on.

1904
01:59:21,220 --> 01:59:22,880
我看到的是什么?
What am I looking at here?

1905
01:59:22,890 --> 01:59:24,550
月球
Oh, that's the moon.

1906
01:59:26,260 --> 01:59:27,810
尼尔 这里是休斯敦
Neil, this is Houston.

1907
01:59:27,810 --> 01:59:29,390
你拿哈苏杂志...
Did you get the Hasselblad magazine...

1908
01:59:29,390 --> 01:59:30,640
真的是月球?
That's really the moon?

1909
01:59:30,640 --> 01:59:34,230
拿了 我们有大约...
Yes, I did. And we got about, uh...

1910
01:59:34,230 --> 01:59:36,940
老天 看起来好假 得有9公斤...
Jesus, it looks fake. I'd say 20 pounds of, uh...

1911
01:59:36,940 --> 01:59:40,530
精挑细选 但没有记录的样品
carefully selected, if not documented samples.

1912
01:59:41,650 --> 01:59:43,070
休斯敦 收到 好样的 完毕
Houston.

1913
01:59:43,070 --> 01:59:48,240
非官方时间 离开地面111小时37分32秒
Roger. Well done. Out. Unofficial time off the surface at 111:37:32.

1914
01:59:54,040 --> 01:59:56,630
我从没想过自己能这么近地看到月球
I never thought I would see the moon up close.

1915
01:59:56,630 --> 01:59:57,710
我也一样 沃尔特
Me neither, Walter.

1916
02:00:04,760 --> 02:00:06,850
我没搞定 天啊 抱歉
I didn't get it. Oh, my God. Sorry.

1917
02:00:06,850 --> 02:00:08,970
别和上次一样 不 别冲着我们开
Not like last time. No. Don't point it at us.

1918
02:00:09,520 --> 02:00:11,480
在波兰 我们说“na zdrowie”
In Polish, we call it "na zdrowie."

1919
02:00:11,480 --> 02:00:14,100
好 na zdrowie 好... 凯莉
All right. Na zdrowie. Okay, okay, okay. Kelly.

1920
02:00:14,100 --> 02:00:15,730
凯莉... 好点了
Kelly. Kelly. It's getting a little better.

1921
02:00:15,730 --> 02:00:19,030
什么事? 老天 说吧 就说一次
Yes? What? Christ, just say it. Just say it once.

1922
02:00:19,610 --> 02:00:21,070
你是我认识的最棒的导演
You are the best director I know.

1923
02:00:21,070 --> 02:00:24,150
是的 好了 我知道此事要保密
I am. [inhales sharply] Now, I know we're not supposed to talk about this,

1924
02:00:24,160 --> 02:00:26,700
但是凯莉 能写进我的简历就太好了 如果我... 感觉...
but, Kelly, this would be so great on my resume if I... Just feels...

1925
02:00:26,700 --> 02:00:29,160
任何人把此事透露出去
Anyone mentions this to anyone,

1926
02:00:29,160 --> 02:00:32,660
就会在一个无名岛上阴暗的牢房里
you will spend the rest of your life in a dark, dank prison cell

1927
02:00:32,660 --> 02:00:34,330
度过余生
on a nameless island.

1928
02:00:35,880 --> 02:00:38,790
好了 为了配合香槟酒
Oh. Now, to wash down the bubbly,

1929
02:00:38,800 --> 02:00:42,630
我代表美国政府请大家喝苏格兰威士忌
on behalf of the US government, have a little, uh, scotch.

1930
02:00:42,630 --> 02:00:44,010
爱德华
Hmm. Edvard.

1931
02:00:44,010 --> 02:00:45,220
我来一杯
I'll take one of those.

1932
02:00:45,220 --> 02:00:48,260
我做了一档价值十亿美元的电视节目 但观众只有一个人
I had a billion-dollar TV show for an audience of one.

1933
02:00:48,260 --> 02:00:50,310
希望你看得开心
Hope you enjoyed it.

1934
02:00:50,310 --> 02:00:53,060
干杯 这是一场完美的失败
Cheers. It was a perfect failure.

1935
02:00:53,060 --> 02:00:55,770
对 干杯... 干杯
That's right. Cheers. Cheers. Cheers.

1936
02:00:59,230 --> 02:01:01,320
能聊几句吗?
Can I talk with you a moment?

1937
02:01:03,530 --> 02:01:06,570
没有多少人违抗了我的命令
Not many people have gone against my orders

1938
02:01:06,570 --> 02:01:07,990
还能活命的
and lived to talk about it.

1939
02:01:07,990 --> 02:01:11,700
不过话说回来 也没有多少人救过我
Then again, not many people have saved my ass.

1940
02:01:11,700 --> 02:01:15,830
要解释月球上为什么有只猫 那可太难了
It would've been a real doozy to explain how the cat ended up on the moon.

1941
02:01:16,830 --> 02:01:18,920
你真是个美国英雄
You're a goddamn American hero.

1942
02:01:20,460 --> 02:01:21,460
干得好
Great job.

1943
02:01:23,670 --> 02:01:26,220
好了 现在这里到处都是媒体
Now, this place is crawling with press.

1944
02:01:26,220 --> 02:01:30,510
溅落之前 我们无法清理这里
So, uh, we can't really clear anything out until after splashdown.

1945
02:01:30,510 --> 02:01:35,100
在这期间呢 把一切和拍摄有关的文件全部销毁
In the meantime, shred any documents associated with the shoot.

1946
02:01:35,980 --> 02:01:38,690
你的名字会从史册中抹去
Your name will be wiped from the history books.

1947
02:01:38,690 --> 02:01:41,110
过往将被重写
The story, rewritten.

1948
02:01:43,400 --> 02:01:45,150
那我可以走了 是的
Then I'm free to go. You are.

1949
02:01:46,490 --> 02:01:52,080
不过呢 有个未来的项目 我需要你这样的人帮忙
Although, I could use someone like you for an upcoming project.

1950
02:01:53,790 --> 02:01:54,910
不 谢了
No, thanks.

1951
02:01:54,910 --> 02:01:57,580
你随意吧 我不理解 但没问题
Suit yourself. Hard to get, but okay.

1952
02:01:59,080 --> 02:02:05,130
如果需要我 喊一声就行 我可能会听见
If you ever need me... just holler. I'm probably listening.

1953
02:02:10,640 --> 02:02:13,060
莫
Oh. Moe.

1954
02:02:16,060 --> 02:02:17,940
真有外星人吗?
Are there really aliens out there?

1955
02:02:20,690 --> 02:02:22,190
外星人就生活在我们中间
They walk among us.

1956
02:02:26,240 --> 02:02:29,570
带我飞向月球
Fly me to the moon

1957
02:02:30,110 --> 02:02:34,240
让我们在群星中嬉戏
Let's play among the stars

1958
02:02:34,990 --> 02:02:40,500
让我看看木星和火星上春天的样子
Let me see what spring is like On Jupiter and Mars...

1959
02:02:40,500 --> 02:02:42,420
四十万公里
A quarter of a million miles.

1960
02:02:42,420 --> 02:02:44,880
想想尼尔·阿姆斯特朗的话
Just think of it as, uh, Neil Armstrong said,

1961
02:02:44,880 --> 02:02:48,380
人类踏上月球时的第一句话
the first words as man stepped foot on the moon,

1962
02:02:48,380 --> 02:02:52,930
“这是个人的一小步 却是人类的一大步”
"A small step for man, a giant leap for mankind."

1963
02:02:53,760 --> 02:02:55,930
这一天不会再有了
And a day that can never come again.

1964
02:02:55,930 --> 02:02:59,270
这一天和这一句话将永远载入史册
A day that shall forever live in history, as will those words,

1965
02:02:59,270 --> 02:03:01,310
会被学生们记住
which will be memorized by schoolboys...

1966
02:03:01,310 --> 02:03:04,940
阿姆斯特朗 你很有前途 不过不是演戏 天啊 绝对不是
Armstrong, you've got a future. Not in acting. My God, no.

1967
02:03:06,110 --> 02:03:08,360
凯莉 帕蒂... 是叫帕蒂吧?
Well, Kelly, Patty... Patty, right?

1968
02:03:08,360 --> 02:03:10,030
我叫露比 好
My name is Ruby. Uh-huh.

1969
02:03:10,030 --> 02:03:11,780
我们成功了 不 我们没成功
We did it. No, we didn't.

1970
02:03:22,000 --> 02:03:23,460
这里是近陆地单位
This is, uh, landward here.

1971
02:03:23,460 --> 02:03:26,130
游泳1号看到阿波罗号了
Uh, Swim One has Apollo visual.

1972
02:03:26,130 --> 02:03:28,590
如果它正在14.5公里外下降
Well, if it's coming down nine miles away,

1973
02:03:28,590 --> 02:03:31,970
那将会刚好落在能见度极限范围内
uh, that's just going to be at the, uh, outer limit of, uh, visibility...

1974
02:03:31,970 --> 02:03:33,760
加油... 宝贝...
Come on. Come on, baby. Come on, baby.

1975
02:03:49,940 --> 02:03:51,780
他们从月球返回了
They're back from the moon.

1976
02:03:51,780 --> 02:03:54,410
宇航员阿姆斯特朗 奥尔德林和柯林斯
Astronauts Armstrong, Aldrin and Collins

1977
02:03:54,410 --> 02:03:57,910
降落在太平洋 夏威夷的西南方
landing in the Pacific Ocean, southwest of Hawaii.

1978
02:04:03,920 --> 02:04:06,170
我想你应该抽一支烟
I guess you deserve a cigarette.

1979
02:04:07,550 --> 02:04:10,510
朋友 是... 我...
Aw, buddy. Yeah, yeah. I, uh...

1980
02:04:13,430 --> 02:04:17,180
我不想在里面失控
I didn't wanna lose it in there. You know?

1981
02:04:18,680 --> 02:04:20,850
我知道你不希望带摄像机登月
You know, I know you didn't want the camera up there,

1982
02:04:20,850 --> 02:04:24,270
但是 天啊 看到那画面...
but, man, seeing that was, uh...

1983
02:04:25,770 --> 02:04:28,070
足以改变人生
It was life-changing.

1984
02:04:29,190 --> 02:04:31,570
我们成功了 是的... 哥们
We did it. We did. We did, man.

1985
02:04:33,450 --> 02:04:36,240
嘿 现在1969年 对吧? 我们在这个十年内做到了
Hey, it's 1969, right? We got it in before the decade.

1986
02:04:36,240 --> 02:04:39,240
是啊 踩着时间线呢 是的 我们成功了
I know. Not a moment to spare. Oh. Yeah, we did.

1987
02:04:39,240 --> 02:04:41,000
瞧 那是谁 嘿
Look who it is. Hey.

1988
02:04:43,160 --> 02:04:45,250
去吧 走吧 好
Go. Get out of here. Yeah.

1989
02:04:47,290 --> 02:04:50,130
听着 你也不晚 小子
Listen, uh, it's not too late for you either, kid.

1990
02:04:51,210 --> 02:04:52,590
谢谢你 亨利 好了
Thank you, Henry. All right.

1991
02:04:56,140 --> 02:04:57,140
嘿
Hey.

1992
02:04:59,430 --> 02:05:00,640
我们成功了
We did it.

1993
02:05:02,430 --> 02:05:03,810
嗨 孩子们
Hey, guys, huh?

1994
02:05:03,810 --> 02:05:05,140
把人送上了月球
Sent a man to the moon.

1995
02:05:21,540 --> 02:05:22,540
知道吗...
You know...

1996
02:05:28,210 --> 02:05:29,500
我还不知道你的名字呢
I never did catch your name.

1997
02:05:37,140 --> 02:05:38,140
温妮
Winnie.

1998
02:05:40,970 --> 02:05:43,730
温妮 很高兴认识你 温妮
Winnie. Nice to meet you, Winnie.

1999
02:05:46,980 --> 02:05:49,020
苏联人说
You know, the Russians, they... they're saying

2000
02:05:49,020 --> 02:05:51,400
整个登月过程是我们在摄影棚里拍的
that we shot the whole thing on a soundstage.

2001
02:05:51,400 --> 02:05:53,820
真不知道这种疯狂的想法是从哪来的
I wonder where they got a crazy idea like that.

2002
02:05:55,070 --> 02:05:56,450
谁在乎他们怎么想啊?
Who cares what they think?

2003
02:05:57,990 --> 02:06:00,830
就算没人相信 真相依然是真相
Truth is still the truth even if nobody believes it.

2004
02:06:02,740 --> 02:06:05,330
就算所有人都信 谎言依然是谎言
Lie is still a lie even if everybody believes it.

2005
02:06:08,080 --> 02:06:09,670
你这次做得真完美
You know, you really nailed this.

2006
02:06:11,920 --> 02:06:13,840
连月尘都如此逼真
All the way down to the lunar dust.

2007
02:06:16,220 --> 02:06:17,630
可惜都是假的
Too bad it's all fake.

2008
02:06:24,520 --> 02:06:25,520
这是假的吗?
Was that fake?

2009
02:06:27,690 --> 02:06:29,520
不是 感觉非常真实
No, that felt very real.

2010
02:06:47,040 --> 02:06:50,460
(政府财产 非请莫入)

2011
02:07:49,270 --> 02:07:54,810
十二 十一 十 九... 点火程序 五...
Twelve, eleven, ten, nine... Ignition sequence, five...


